Name: one_methylinosine
Definition: 1-methylinosine is a modified inosine.

Name: asparagine
Definition: A polar	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons AAT and AAC.

Name: C_to_A_transversion
Definition: A transversion from cytidine to adenine.

Name: hydrophobic_region_of_peptide
Definition: Hydrophobic regions are regions with a low affinity for water.

Name: bidirectional_promoter
Definition: A promoter that can allow for transcription in both directions.

Name: V_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including more than one V-gene.

Name: proline
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codons CCN (CCT	 CCC	 CCA and CCG).

Name: polypeptide_iron_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with iron ions.

Name: stop_codon_read_through
Definition: A stop codon redefined to be a new amino acid.

Name: alternatively_spliced_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is alternatively spliced.

Name: U5_three_prime_LTR_region
Definition: The U5 segment of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: DNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 DNA molecule.

Name: inversion_derived_deficiency_plus_aneuploid
Definition: A chromosomal deletion whereby a chromosome generated by recombination between two inversions; has a deficiency at one end and presumed to have a deficiency or duplication at the other end of the inversion.

Name: H3K36_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 36th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is dimethylated.

Name: V_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one V-gene and one J-gene.

Name: sonicate_fragment
Definition: A DNA fragment generated by sonication. Sonication is a technique used to sheer DNA into smaller fragments.

Name: N6_methyl_N6_threonylcarbamoyladenosine
Definition: N6_methyl_N6_threonylcarbamoyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: QTL
Definition: A quantitative trait locus (QTL) is a polymorphic locus which contains alleles that differentially affect the expression of a continuously distributed phenotypic trait. Usually it is a marker described by statistical association to quantitative variation in the particular phenotypic trait that is thought to be controlled by the cumulative action of alleles at multiple loci.

Name: conserved_region
Definition: Region of sequence similarity by descent from a common ancestor.

Name: RNA_internal_loop
Definition: A region of double stranded RNA where the bases do not conform to WC base pairing. The loop is closed on both sides by canonical base pairing. If the interruption to base pairing occurs on one strand only	 it is known as a bulge.

Name: nucleic_acid
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases bound to repeating units. The forms found in nature are deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA)	 where the repeating units are 2-deoxy-D-ribose rings connected to a phosphate backbone	 and ribonucleic acid (RNA)	 where the repeating units are D-ribose rings connected to a phosphate backbone.

Name: miRNA_antiguide
Definition: A region of the pri miRNA that base pairs with the guide to form the hairpin.

Name: prokaryotic_promoter
Definition: A regulatory_region essential for the specific initiation of transcription at a defined location in a DNA molecule	 although this location might not be one single base. It is recognized by a specific RNA polymerase(RNAP)-holoenzyme	 and this recognition is not necessarily autonomous.

Name: hetero_compound_chromosome
Definition: A compound chromosome whereby two arms from different chromosomes are connected through the centromere of one of them.

Name: mating_type_region_replication_fork_barrier
Definition: A DNA motif that is found in eukaryotic rDNA repeats	 and is a site of replication fork pausing.

Name: sequence_location
Definition: The location of a sequence.

Name: deficient_intrachromosomal_transposition
Definition: An intrachromosomal transposition whereby a translocation in which one of the four broken ends loses a segment before re-joining.

Name: mRNA_region
Definition: A region of an mRNA.

Name: mRNA_with_plus_1_frameshift
Definition: An mRNA with a plus 1 frameshift.

Name: octamer_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters with sequence ATTGCAT that binds Pou-domain transcription factors.

Name: pre_edited_mRNA
Definition: A primary transcript that	 at least in part	 encodes one or more proteins that has not been edited.

Name: gene_with_mRNA_recoded_by_translational_bypass
Definition: A gene with mRNA recoded by translational bypass.

Name: transposable_element_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene contained within a transposable element.

Name: interchromosomal_mutation
Definition: A chromosomal structure variation whereby more than one chromosome is involved.

Name: polypeptide_repeat
Definition: A polypeptide_repeat is a single copy of an internal sequence repetition.

Name: transgene
Definition: A transgene is a gene that has been transferred naturally or by any of a number of genetic engineering techniques from one organism to another.

Name: recombination_feature
Definition: A feature where there has been exchange of genetic material in the event of mitosis or meiosis

Name: oligo_U_tail
Definition: The string of non-encoded U's at the 3' end of a guide RNA (SO:0000602).

Name: upstream_AUG_codon
Definition: A start codon upstream of the ORF.

Name: terminal_inverted_repeat_element
Definition: A DNA transposable element defined as having termini with perfect	 or nearly perfect short inverted repeats	 generally 10 - 40 nucleotides long.

Name: rRNA
Definition: RNA that comprises part of a ribosome	 and that can provide both structural scaffolding and catalytic activity.

Name: priRNA
Definition: A small RNA molecule	 22-23 nt in size	 that is the product of a longer RNA. The production of priRNAs is independent of dicer and involves binding of RNA by argonaute and trimming by triman. In fission yeast	 priRNAs trigger the establishment of heterochromatin. PriRNAs are primarily generated from centromeric transcripts (dg and dh repeats)	 but may also be produced from degradation products of primary transcripts.

Name: FRT_site
Definition: An inversion site found on the Saccharomyces cerevisiae 2 micron plasmid.

Name: five_prime_cis_splice_site
Definition: Intronic 2 bp region bordering the exon	 at the 5' edge of the intron. A splice_site that is downstream_adjacent_to exon and starts intron.

Name: IG_J_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogenic joining region which closely resembles a known functional imunoglobulin joining gene but in which the coding region has stop codons	 frameshift mutations or a mutation that effects the initiation codon that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the joining region of the variable domain of an immunoglobulin chain.

Name: pseudogenic_gene_segment
Definition: A gene segment which when incorporated by somatic recombination in the final gene transcript results in a nonfunctional product.

Name: circular_single_stranded_DNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 single-stranded	 circular DNA molecule.

Name: one_methyladenosine
Definition: 1_methyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: pi_helix
Definition: The pi helix has 4.1 residues per turn and a translation of 1.15  (=0.115 nm) along the helical axis. The N-H group of an amino acid forms a hydrogen bond with the C=O group of the amino acid five residues earlier.

Name: RprA_RNA
Definition: Translational regulation of the stationary phase sigma factor RpoS is mediated by the formation of a double-stranded RNA stem-loop structure in the upstream region of the rpoS messenger RNA	 occluding the translation initiation site. Clones carrying rprA (RpoS regulator RNA) increased the translation of RpoS. The rprA gene encodes a 106 nucleotide regulatory RNA. As with DsrA Rfam:RF00014	 RprA is predicted to form three stem-loops. Thus	 at least two small RNAs	 DsrA and RprA	 participate in the positive regulation of RpoS translation. Unlike DsrA	 RprA does not have an extensive region of complementarity to the RpoS leader	 leaving its mechanism of action unclear. RprA is non-essential.

Name: replicon
Definition: A region containing at least one unique origin of replication and a unique termination site.

Name: SVA_deletion
Definition: A deletion of an SVA mobile element.

Name: ultracontig
Definition: An ordered and oriented set of scaffolds based on somewhat weaker sets of inferential evidence such as one set of mate pair reads together with supporting evidence from ESTs or location of markers from SNP or microsatellite maps	 or cytogenetic localization of contained markers.

Name: polymer_attribute
Definition: An attribute to describe the kind of biological sequence.

Name: minus_12_signal
Definition: A conserved region about 12-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units	 involved with sigma factor 54.

Name: editing_block
Definition: Edited mRNA sequence mediated by a single guide RNA (SO:0000602).

Name: snRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a small nuclear RNA (SO:0000274).

Name: catmat_left_handed_four
Definition: A motif of 4 consecutive residues with dihedral angles as follows: res i: phi -90 bounds -120 to -60	 res i psi -10 bounds -50 to 30	 res i+1: phi -90 bounds -120 to -60	 res i+1: psi -10 bounds -50 to 30	 res i+2: phi -75 bounds -100 to -50	 res i+2: psi 140 bounds 110 to 170.  The extra restriction of the length of the O to O distance is similar	 that it be less than 5 Angstrom. In this case these two Oxygen atoms are the main chain carbonyl oxygen atoms of residues i-1 and i+2.

Name: haplotype
Definition: A haplotype is one of a set of coexisting sequence variants of a haplotype block.

Name: allelically_excluded_gene
Definition: A gene that is allelically_excluded.

Name: terminator
Definition: The sequence of DNA located either at the end of the transcript that causes RNA polymerase to terminate transcription.

Name: chromosome_band
Definition: A cytologically distinguishable feature of a chromosome	 often made visible by staining	 and usually alternating light and dark.

Name: MNP
Definition: A multiple nucleotide polymorphism with alleles of common length > 1	 for example AAA/TTT.

Name: tiling_path_clone
Definition: A clone which is part of a tiling path. A tiling path is a set of sequencing substrates	 typically clones	 which have been selected in order to efficiently cover a region of the genome in preparation for sequencing and assembly.

Name: VJ_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one VJ-gene and one C-gene.

Name: regional_centromere_outer_repeat_region
Definition: The heterochromatic outer repeat region of a modular centromere. These repeats exist in tandem arrays on both chromosome arms.

Name: Gypsy_LTR_retrotransposon
Definition: LTR retrotransposons in the Gypsy superfamily contain elements coding for specific proteins in this order: GAG	 AP	 RT	 RH	 INT. GAG is a structural protein for virus-like particles. AP is aspartic proteinase. INT is a DDE integrase. RT is a reverse transcriptase. RH is RNAse H.

Name: syntenic_region
Definition: A region in which two or more pairs of homologous markers occur on the same chromosome in two or more species.

Name: transcript_bound_by_protein
Definition: A transcript that is bound by a protein.

Name: mitochondrial_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in a mitochondria.

Name: ss_oligo
Definition: A single stranded oligonucleotide.

Name: complex_regulon
Definition: A regulon defined by considering the units of expression regulated by a specified set of regulatory gene products.

Name: sequence_conflict
Definition: Different sources report differing sequences.

Name: gene_with_polycistronic_transcript
Definition: A gene that encodes a polycistronic transcript.

Name: gene_member_region
Definition: A region of a gene.

Name: gene_cassette
Definition: A gene that can be substituted for a related gene at a different site in the genome.

Name: Transib_TIR_transposon
Definition: Terminal inverted repeat (TIR) transposons of the superfamily Transib contain the DDE motif	 which is related to the RAG1 protein involved in V(D)J recombination.

Name: pericentric_inversion
Definition: A chromosomal inversion that includes the centromere.

Name: cDNA_match
Definition: A match against cDNA sequence.

Name: consensus
Definition: A sequence produced from an aligment algorithm that uses multiple sequences as input.

Name: rRNA_16S
Definition: A large polynucleotide in Bacteria and Archaea	 which functions as the small subunit of the ribosome.

Name: polypeptide_sequence_variant
Definition: A sequence variant with in the CDS that causes a change in the resulting polypeptide sequence.

Name: edited_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is edited.

Name: five_prime_D_heptamer
Definition: 7 nucleotide recombination site (e.g. CACTGTG)	 part of a 5' D-recombination signal sequence (SO:0000556) of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: protein_coding_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript that	 at least in part	 encodes one or more proteins.

Name: bound_by_nucleic_acid
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that is bound by a nucleic acid.

Name: recoded_mRNA
Definition: The sequence of a mature mRNA transcript	 modified before translation or during translation	 usually by special cis-acting signals.

Name: attCtn_site
Definition: An attachment site located on a conjugative transposon and used for site-specific integration of a conjugative transposon.

Name: processed_transcript
Definition: A transcript for which no open reading frame has been identified and for which no other function has been determined.

Name: duplication_artifact
Definition: A duplication that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: invalidated_by_chimeric_cDNA
Definition: A cDNA clone constructed from more than one mRNA. Usually an experimental artifact.

Name: H4K20_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 20th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4histone protein is mono-methylated.

Name: lariat_intron
Definition: A kind of intron whereby the excision is driven by lariat formation.

Name: EST
Definition: A tag produced from a single sequencing read from a cDNA clone or PCR product; typically a few hundred base pairs long.

Name: TF_binding_site
Definition: A DNA site where a transcription factor binds.

Name: CCAAT_motif
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence CCAAT	 bound by a protein complex that represses transcription in response to low iron levels.

Name: cyanelle_gene
Definition: A gene from cyanelle sequence.

Name: mRNA_read
Definition: A sequencer read of an mRNA substrate.

Name: schellmann_loop_six
Definition: Common Type: A motif of six consecutive residues that contains two H-bonds in which: the main-chain CO of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+5) the main-chain CO of residue(i+1) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+4).

Name: inversion_derived_bipartite_duplication
Definition: A chromosome generated by recombination between two inversions; there is a duplication at each end of the inversion.

Name: IRLinv_site
Definition: Component of the inversion site located at the left of a region susceptible to site-specific inversion.

Name: modified_DNA_base
Definition: A modified nucleotide	 i.e. a nucleotide other than A	 T	 C. G.

Name: expressed_sequence_match
Definition: A match to an EST or cDNA sequence.

Name: T_to_A_transversion
Definition: A transversion from T to A.

Name: miR_encoding_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A tRNA primary transcript that also encodes pre-miR sequence that is processed to form functionally active miRNA.

Name: tyrosine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding tyrosyl tRNA (SO:000272).

Name: coding_transcript_with_retained_intron
Definition: A protein coding transcript containing a retained intron.

Name: flanking_three_prime_quadruplet_recoding_signal
Definition: Four base pair sequence immediately downstream of the redefined region. The redefined region is a frameshift site. The quadruplet is 2 overlapping codons.

Name: chromosome_number_variation
Definition: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is not an exact multiple of the haploid number.

Name: three_prime_RST
Definition: A tag produced from a single sequencing read from a 3'-RACE product; typically a few hundred base pairs long.

Name: beta_turn_type_six_a_one
Definition: A type VIa beta turn with the following phi and psi sngles on amino acid residues 2 and 3: phi-2 = -60 degrees	 psi-2 = 120 degrees	 phi-3 = -90 degrees	 psi-3 = 0 degrees.

Name: class_II_RNA
Definition: Small non-coding RNA (59-60 nt long) containing 5' and 3' ends that are predicted to come together to form a stem structure. Identified in the social amoeba Dictyostelium discoideum and localized in the cytoplasm.

Name: protein_hmm_match
Definition: A match to a protein HMM such as pfam.

Name: pseudogene_by_unequal_crossing_over
Definition: A pseudogene caused by unequal crossing over at recombination.

Name: polinton
Definition: A kind of DNA transposon that populates the genomes of protists	 fungi	 and animals	 characterized by a unique set of proteins necessary for their transposition	 including a protein-primed DNA polymerase B	 retroviral integrase	 cysteine protease	 and ATPase. Polintons are characterized by 6-bp target site duplications	 terminal-inverted repeats that are several hundred nucleotides long	 and 5'-AG and TC-3' termini. Polintons exist as autonomous and nonautonomous elements.

Name: dicistronic_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA that has the quality dicistronic.

Name: Y_prime_element
Definition: A Y' element is a repeat region (SO:0000657) located adjacent to telomeric repeats or X element combinatorial repeats	 either as a single copy or tandem repeat of two to four copies.

Name: undermodified_hydroxywybutosine
Definition: Undermodified_hydroxywybutosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: SVA_insertion
Definition: An insertion of sequence from the SVA family of mobile elements.

Name: chromosome_fission
Definition: A chromosome that occurred by the division of a larger chromosome.

Name: VDJ_gene_segment
Definition: Rearranged genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene including L-part1	 V-intron and V-D-J-exon	 with the 5'UTR (SO:0000204) and 3'UTR (SO:0000205).

Name: vertebrate_immune_system_gene_recombination_signal_feature
Definition: Feature used for the recombination of genomic material for the purpose of generating diversity of the immune system.

Name: pseudogenic_transcript
Definition: A non functional descendant of a transcript	 part of a pseudogene.

Name: isomiR
Definition: IsomiRs are all the bona fide variants of a mature product. IsomiRs should be connected to the ref_miRNA it is most likely to be the variant of. Some isomiRs can be variations of one or multiple ref_miRNA.

Name: rRNA_cleavage_snoRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding an rRNA cleavage snoRNA.

Name: rRNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes for ribosomal RNA.

Name: mobile_intron
Definition: An intron (mitochondrial	 chloroplast	 nuclear or prokaryotic) that encodes a double strand sequence specific endonuclease allowing for mobility.

Name: recombinationally_rearranged
Definition: A gene that is recombinationally rearranged.

Name: overlapping_EST_set
Definition: A continous experimental result region extending the length of multiple overlapping EST's.

Name: predicted_transcript
Definition: A transcript feature that has been predicted but is not yet validated.

Name: non_allelic_homologous_recombination_region
Definition: A genomic region at a non-allelic position where exchange of genetic material happens as a result of homologous recombination.

Name: mt_tRNA
Definition: Mitochondrial transfer RNA.

Name: protein_coding_gene
Definition: A gene that codes for an RNA that can be translated into a protein.

Name: restriction_enzyme_recognition_site
Definition: The nucleotide region (usually a palindrome) that is recognized by a restriction enzyme. This may or may not be equal to the restriction enzyme binding site.

Name: polyA_primed_cDNA_clone
Definition: A cDNA clone invalidated by polyA priming.

Name: nuclear_localization_signal
Definition: A polypeptide region that targets a polypeptide to the nucleus.

Name: VDJ_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one VDJ-gene and one C-gene.

Name: LNA_oligo
Definition: An oligo composed of LNA residues.

Name: forward
Definition: Forward is an attribute of the feature	 where the feature is in the 5' to 3' direction.

Name: group_IIB_intron
Definition: A group II intron that recognizes IBS1/EBS1 and IBS2/EBS2 for the 5-prime exon and IBS3/EBS3 for the 3-prime exon.

Name: gamma_turn_inverse
Definition: Gamma turns	 defined for 3 residues i	 i+1	 i+2 if a hydrogen bond exists between residues i and i+2 and the phi and psi angles of residue i+1 fall within 40 degrees: phi(i+1)=-79.0 - psi(i+1)=69.0.

Name: core_prokaryotic_promoter_element
Definition: An element that always exists within the promoter region of a prokaryotic gene.

Name: CAGE_cluster
Definition: A kind of transcription_initiation_cluster defined by the clustering of CAGE tags on a sequence region.

Name: CDS
Definition: A contiguous sequence which begins with	 and includes	 a start codon and ends with	 and includes	 a stop codon.

Name: D_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one D-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: aspartic_acid_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding aspartyl tRNA (SO:0000257).

Name: seven_deazaguanosine
Definition: 7-deazaguanosine is a modified guanosine.

Name: recombination_regulatory_region
Definition: A regulatory region that is involved in the control of the process of recombination.

Name: SL3_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL3 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL3 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: rDNA_replication_fork_barrier
Definition: A DNA motif that is found in eukaryotic rDNA repeats	 and is a site of replication fork pausing.

Name: processed_pseudogenic_rRNA
Definition: The pseudogene has arisen by reverse transcription of a mRNA into cDNA	 followed by reintegration into the genome. Therefore	 it has lost any intron/exon structure	 and it might have a pseudo-polyA-tail.

Name: trans_spliced
Definition: An attribute describing transcript sequence that is created by splicing exons from diferent genes.

Name: unoriented_intrachromosomal_transposition
Definition: An intrachromosomal transposition whereby the segment between the first two breaks listed is removed and inserted at the third break; the orientation of the insertion with respect to its flanking segments is not recorded.

Name: minisatellite
Definition: A repeat region containing tandemly repeated sequences having a unit length of 10 to 40 bp.

Name: V_D_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one V-gene	 one D-gene and one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: gene_segment
Definition: A gene component region which acts as a recombinational unit of a gene whose functional form is generated through somatic recombination.

Name: satellite_DNA
Definition: The many tandem repeats (identical or related) of a short basic repeating unit; many have a base composition or other property different from the genome average that allows them to be separated from the bulk (main band) genomic DNA.

Name: deletion_junction
Definition: The space between two bases in a sequence which marks the position where a deletion has occurred.

Name: internal_UTR
Definition: A UTR bordered by the terminal and initial codons of two CDSs in a polycistronic transcript. Every UTR is either 5'	 3' or internal.

Name: H3K36_methylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 36th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is methylated.

Name: translationally_regulated
Definition: An attribute describing a gene that is regulated as it is translated.

Name: free_chromosome_arm
Definition: A chromosome structure variation whereby an arm exists as an individual chromosome element.

Name: lnc_RNA
Definition: A non-coding RNA over 200nucleotides in length.

Name: five_taurinomethyl_two_thiouridine
Definition: 5_taurinomethyl_2_thiouridineis a modified uridine base feature.

Name: U_box
Definition: An U-box is a conserved T-rich region upstream of a retroviral polypurine tract that is involved in PPT primer creation during reverse transcription.

Name: three_prime_overlapping_ncrna
Definition: Transcript where ditag (digital gene expression profiling)and/or published experimental data strongly supports the existence of short non-coding transcripts transcribed from the 3'UTR.

Name: spurious_protein
Definition: A region of DNA that is predicted to be translated and transcribed into a protein by a protein detection algorithm that does not get transcribed in nature.

Name: topologically_associated_domain
Definition: An instance of a self-interacting DNA region flanked by left and right TAD boundaries.

Name: plus_2_translational_frameshift
Definition: The region of mRNA 2 bases long that is skipped during the process of translational frameshifting (GO:0006452)	 causing the reading frame to be different.

Name: nuclear_gene
Definition: A gene from nuclear sequence.

Name: pheromone_response_element
Definition: A PRE is a (yeast) TFBS with consensus site [TGAAAC(A/G)].

Name: N6_methyladenine
Definition: An adenine methylated at the 6 nitrogen.

Name: sense_intronic_ncRNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes a sense intronic long non-coding RNA.

Name: beta_bulge_loop_five
Definition: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet consisting of two H-bonds in which: the main-chain NH of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain CO of residue(i+4)	 the main-chain CO of residue i is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+3)	 these loops have an RL nest at residues i+2 and i+3.

Name: three_prime_LTR
Definition: The long terminal repeat found at the three-prime end of the sequence to be inserted into the host genome.

Name: five_prime_LTR_component
Definition: A component of the five-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: low_complexity
Definition: When a sequence does not contain an equal distribution of all four possible nucleotide bases or does not contain all nucleotide bases.

Name: exonic_splicing_silencer
Definition: An exonic  splicing regulatory element that functions to recruit trans acting splicing factors suppress the transcription of the gene or genes they control.

Name: symmetric_RNA_internal_loop
Definition: An internal RNA loop where the extent of the loop on both stands is the same size.

Name: CDS_fragment
Definition: A portion of a CDS that is not the complete CDS.

Name: class_I_RNA
Definition: Small non-coding RNA (55-65 nt long) containing highly conserved 5' and 3' ends (16 and 8 nt	 respectively) that are predicted to come together to form a stem structure. Identified in the social amoeba Dictyostelium discoideum and localized in the cytoplasm.

Name: H2BK12_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 12th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2B protein is acetylated.

Name: N6_isopentenyladenosine
Definition: N6_isopentenyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: diplotype
Definition: A diplotype is a pair of haplotypes from a given individual. It is a genotype where the phase is known.

Name: polyA_site
Definition: The site on an RNA transcript to which will be added adenine residues by post-transcriptional polyadenylation. The boundary between the UTR and the polyA sequence.

Name: RNApol_III_promoter_type_3
Definition: This type of promoter recruits RNA pol III to transcribe predominantly noncoding RNAs. This promoter contains a proximal sequence element (PSE) and a TATA box upstream of the gene that it regulates. Transcription can also be activated by a distal sequence element (DSE)	 which is located further upstream.

Name: mobile_element_insertion
Definition: A kind of insertion where the inserted sequence is a mobile element.

Name: iDNA
Definition: Genomic sequence removed from the genome	 as a normal event	 by a process of recombination.

Name: nucleomorph_gene
Definition: A gene from nucleomorph sequence.

Name: attB_site
Definition: An integration/excision site of a bacterial chromosome at which a recombinase acts to insert foreign DNA containing a cognate integration/excision site.

Name: histone_3_acetylation_site
Definition: A histone 3 modification where the modification is the acetylation of the residue.

Name: five_methoxyuridine
Definition: 5_methoxyuridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: C_to_T_transition
Definition: A transition of a cytidine to a thymine.

Name: elongated_polypeptide_N_terminal
Definition: An elongation of a polypeptide sequence at the N terminus deriving from a sequence variant extending the CDS.

Name: glycyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a glycine anticodon	 and a 3' glycine binding region.

Name: threonyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a threonine anticodon	 and a 3' threonine binding region.

Name: tyrosyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a tyrosine anticodon	 and a 3' tyrosine binding region.

Name: interior_intron
Definition: An intron that is not the most 3-prime or the most 5-prime in a given transcript.

Name: CDRE_motif
Definition: An RNA polymerase II promoter element found in the promoters of genes regulated by calcineurin. The consensus sequence is GNGGCKCA.

Name: heritable_phenotypic_marker
Definition: A biological_region characterized as a single heritable trait in a phenotype screen. The heritable phenotype may be mapped to a chromosome but generally has not been characterized to a specific gene locus.

Name: gene_silenced_by_DNA_modification
Definition: A gene that is silenced by DNA modification.

Name: BREu_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 located immediately upstream of some TATA box elements at -37 to -32 with respect to the TSS (+1). Consensus sequence is (G|C)(G|C)(G|A)CGCC. Binds TFIIB.

Name: histone_2AZ_acetylation_site
Definition: A histone 2AZ modification where the modification is the acetylation of the residue.

Name: stRNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a small temporal RNA (stRNA). Found in roundworm development.

Name: protein_protein_contact
Definition: A binding site that	 in the protein molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues.

Name: blunt_end_restriction_enzyme_cleavage_site
Definition: A restriction enzyme recognition site that	 when cleaved	 results in no overhangs.

Name: group_I_intron
Definition: Group I catalytic introns are large self-splicing ribozymes. They catalyze their own excision from mRNA	 tRNA and rRNA precursors in a wide range of organisms. The core secondary structure consists of 9 paired regions (P1-P9). These fold to essentially two domains	 the P4-P6 domain (formed from the stacking of P5	 P4	 P6 and P6a helices) and the P3-P9 domain (formed from the P8	 P3	 P7 and P9 helices). Group I catalytic introns often have long ORFs inserted in loop regions.

Name: C_D_box_snoRNA
Definition: Most box C/D snoRNAs also contain long (>10 nt) sequences complementary to rRNA. Boxes C and D	 as well as boxes C' and D'	 are usually located in close proximity	 and form a structure known as the box C/D motif. This motif is important for snoRNA stability	 processing	 nucleolar targeting and function. A small number of box C/D snoRNAs are involved in rRNA processing; most	 however	 are known or predicted to serve as guide RNAs in ribose methylation of rRNA. Targeting involves direct base pairing of the snoRNA at the rRNA site to be modified and selection of a rRNA nucleotide a fixed distance from box D or D'.

Name: polymerase_synthesis_read
Definition: A read produced by the polymerase based sequence by synthesis method.

Name: vertebrate_immune_system_gene_recombination_spacer
Definition: A 12 or 23 nucleotide spacer between two regions of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene that may be rearranged by recombinase.

Name: engineered_episome
Definition: An episome that is engineered.

Name: exon_of_single_exon_gene
Definition: An exon that is the only exon in a gene.

Name: gene_silenced_by_histone_modification
Definition: A gene that is silenced by histone modification.

Name: H3K9_trimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 9th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is tri-methylated.

Name: mating_type_M_box
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence ACAAT	 found in promoters of mating type M-specific genes in fission yeast and bound by the transcription factor Mat1-Mc.

Name: INR_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters required for the correct positioning of the polymerase for the start of transcription. Overlaps the TSS. The mammalian consensus sequence is YYAN(T|A)YY; the Drosophila consensus sequence is TCA(G|T)t(T|C). In each the A is at position +1 with respect to the TSS. Functionally similar to the TATA box element.

Name: chromosome_arm
Definition: A region of the chromosome between the centromere and the telomere. Human chromosomes have two arms	 the p arm (short) and the q arm (long) which are separated from each other by the centromere.

Name: silenced_by_DNA_modification
Definition: An attribute describing an epigenetic process where a gene is inactivated by DNA modifications	 resulting in repression of transcription.

Name: bound_by_factor
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that is bound by another molecule.

Name: NDM2_motif
Definition: A non directional promoter motif with consensus CGMYGYCR.

Name: splice_region
Definition: A region surrounding a cis_splice site	 either within 1-3 bases of the exon or 3-8 bases of the intron.

Name: rRNA_small_subunit_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a small ribosomal subunit RNA.

Name: loR
Definition: A short	 non coding transcript of loop-derived sequences encoded in precursor miRNA.

Name: negatively_autoregulated
Definition: The gene product is involved in its own transcriptional regulation where it decreases transcription.

Name: CDS_three_prime_extension
Definition: A sequence variant extending the CDS at the 3' end	 that causes elongation of the resulting polypeptide sequence at the C terminus.

Name: supercontig
Definition: One or more contigs that have been ordered and oriented using end-read information. Contains gaps that are filled with N's.

Name: rRNA_5S_gene
Definition: A gene which codes for 5S_rRNA	 which is a portion of the large subunit of the ribosome in both eukaryotes and prokaryotes.

Name: rearrangement_region
Definition: A region of a chromosome	 where the chromosome has undergone a large structural rearrangement that altered the genome organization. There is no longer synteny to the reference genome.

Name: possible_base_call_error
Definition: A region of sequence where the validity of the base calling is questionable.

Name: U3_snoRNA
Definition: U3 snoRNA is a member of the box C/D class of small nucleolar RNAs. The U3 snoRNA secondary structure is characterised by a small 5' domain (with boxes A and A')	 and a larger 3' domain (with boxes B	 C	 C'	 and D)	 the two domains being linked by a single-stranded hinge. Boxes B and C form the B/C motif	 which appears to be exclusive to U3 snoRNAs	 and boxes C' and D form the C'/D motif. The latter is functionally similar to the C/D motifs found in other snoRNAs. The 5' domain and the hinge region act as a pre-rRNA-binding domain. The 3' domain has conserved protein-binding sites. Both the box B/C and box C'/D motifs are sufficient for nuclear retention of U3 snoRNA. The box C'/D motif is also necessary for nucleolar localization	 stability and hypermethylation of U3 snoRNA. Both box B/C and C'/D motifs are involved in specific protein interactions and are necessary for the rRNA processing functions of U3 snoRNA.

Name: minus_35_signal
Definition: A conserved hexamer about 35-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units; consensus=TTGACa or TGTTGACA. This region is associated with sigma factor 70.

Name: gene_fragment
Definition: A portion of a gene that is not the complete gene.

Name: nucleomorphic_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in a nucleomorph.

Name: PAC
Definition: The P1-derived artificial chromosome are DNA constructs that are derived from the DNA of P1 bacteriophage. They can carry large amounts (about 100-300 kilobases) of other sequences for a variety of bioengineering purposes. It is one type of vector used to clone DNA fragments (100- to 300-kb insert size; average	 150 kb) in Escherichia coli cells.

Name: modified_L_glutamic_acid
Definition: A post translationally modified glutamic acid.

Name: H3K4_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 4th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: macronucleus_destined_segment
Definition: A sequence that is conserved	 although rearranged relative to the micronucleus	 in the macronucleus of a ciliate genome.

Name: SHP_box
Definition: A conserved Cdc48/p97 interaction motif with strict consensus sequence F[PI]GKG[TK][RK]LG[GT] and relaxed consensus sequence FXGKGX[RK]LG.

Name: silencer
Definition: A regulatory region which upon binding of transcription factors	 suppress the transcription of the gene or genes they control.

Name: DArT_marker
Definition: A genetic marker	 discovered using Diversity Arrays Technology (DArT) technology.

Name: 7SL_SINE_retrotransposon
Definition: Short interspersed elements that originated from 7SL RNAs.

Name: minus_2_frameshift
Definition: A frameshift caused by deleting two bases.

Name: untranslated_region_polycistronic_mRNA
Definition: The untranslated sequence separating the 'cistrons' of multicistronic mRNA.

Name: H3K14_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 14th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: deletion_breakpoint
Definition: The point within a chromosome where a deletion begins or ends.

Name: enhancer_bound_by_factor
Definition: An enhancer bound by a factor.

Name: DHU_loop
Definition: Non-base-paired sequence of nucleotide bases in tRNA. It contains several dihydrouracil residues.

Name: insertional_duplication
Definition: A chromosome duplication involving the insertion of a duplicated region (as opposed to a free duplication).

Name: YAC_end
Definition: A region of sequence from the end of a YAC clone that may provide a highly specific marker.

Name: RNApol_III_promoter_type_2
Definition: This type of promoter recruits RNA pol III to transcribe genes mainly for t-RNA. This promoter is intragenic and includes an A box and a B box.

Name: remark
Definition: A comment about the sequence.

Name: Viper_YR_retrotransposon
Definition: VIPER retrotransposons are members of the YR_retrotransposon (SO:0002286 superfamily with protein domains: RT	 RH	 YR. RT is a reverse transcriptase. RH is RNAse H. YR is Tyrosine recombinase. Inverted terminal repeats (ITRs) in VIPER are arranged in A-pol-B-A-B order where A and B represent ITRs. VIPER is only found in kinetoplastida genomes.

Name: linear_single_stranded_RNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 single-stranded	 linear RNA molecule.

Name: aspartic_acid
Definition: A negatively charged	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons GAT and GAC.

Name: VJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one VJ-gene and one J-gene.

Name: orthologous_region
Definition: A homologous_region that is orthologous to another region.

Name: purine_transition
Definition: A substitution of a purine	 A or G	 for another purine.

Name: retrotransposon
Definition: A transposable element that is incorporated into a chromosome by a mechanism that requires reverse transcriptase.

Name: golden_path_fragment
Definition: One of the pieces of sequence that make up a golden path.

Name: structural_variant
Definition: A sequence variant that changes one or more sequence features.

Name: SRP_RNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a signal recognition particle RNA (SRP RNA).

Name: nuclear_export_signal
Definition: A polypeptide region that targets a polypeptide to he cytoplasm.

Name: circular_double_stranded_RNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 double-stranded	 circular RNA molecule.

Name: antiparallel_beta_strand
Definition: A peptide region which hydrogen bonded to another region of peptide running in the oposite direction (one running N-terminal to C-terminal and one running C-terminal to N-terminal). Hydrogen bonding occurs between every other C=O from one strand to every other N-H on the adjacent strand. In this case	 if two atoms C-alpha (i) and C-alpha (j) are adjacent in two hydrogen-bonded beta strands	 then they form two mutual backbone hydrogen bonds to each other's flanking peptide groups; this is known as a close pair of hydrogen bonds. The peptide backbone dihedral angles (phi	 psi) are about (-140 degrees	 135 degrees) in antiparallel sheets.

Name: modified_inosine
Definition: A modified inosine is an inosine base feature that has been altered.

Name: allelic_pseudogenic_rRNA
Definition: A (unitary) pseudogene that is stable in the population but importantly it has a functional alternative allele also in the population. i.e.	 one strain may have the gene	 another strain may have the pseudogene. MHC haplotypes have allelic pseudogenes.

Name: miR_encoding_snoRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A snoRNA primary transcript that also encodes pre-miR sequence that is processed to form functionally active miRNA.

Name: recombinationally_inverted_gene
Definition: A recombinationally rearranged gene by inversion.

Name: H3R2_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 2nd residue (an arginine)	 from the start of the H3 protein is mono-methylated.

Name: asx_turn
Definition: A motif of three consecutive residues and one H-bond in which: residue(i) is Aspartate or Asparagine (Asx)	 the side-chain O of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+2).

Name: vertebrate_immunoglobulin_T_cell_receptor_segment
Definition: Germline genomic DNA with the sequence for a V	 D	 C	 or J portion of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor.

Name: molecular_contact_region
Definition: A region that is involved a contact with another molecule.

Name: clone
Definition: A piece of DNA that has been inserted in a vector so that it can be propagated in a host bacterium or some other organism.

Name: chloroplast_DNA
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a chloroplast	 a photosynthetic plastid.

Name: gene_trap_construct
Definition: A gene trap construct is a type of engineered plasmid which is designed to integrate into a genome and produce a fusion transcript between exons of the gene into which it inserts and a reporter element in the construct. Gene traps contain a splice acceptor	 do not contain promoter elements for the reporter	 and are mutagenic. Gene traps may be bicistronic with the second cassette containing a promoter driving an a selectable marker.

Name: promoter_element
Definition: An element that can exist within the promoter region of a gene.

Name: capped_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript that is capped.

Name: inducible_promoter
Definition: A promoter whereby activity is induced by the presence or absence of biotic or abiotic factors.

Name: immunoglobulin_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene derived from an immunoglobulin gene.

Name: tag
Definition: A nucleotide sequence that may be used to identify a larger sequence.

Name: trans_splice_site
Definition: Primary transcript region bordering trans-splice junction.

Name: mating_type_region
Definition: A specialized region in the genomes of some yeast and fungi	 the genes of which regulate mating type.

Name: circular_double_stranded_DNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 double-stranded	 circular DNA molecule.

Name: recoded_codon
Definition: A codon that has been redefined at translation. The redefinition may be as a result of translational bypass	 translational frameshifting or stop codon readthrough.

Name: lysine
Definition: A positively charged	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons AAA and AAG.

Name: gene_cassette_array
Definition: An array of non-functional genes whose members	 when captured by recombination form functional genes.

Name: mutated_variant_site
Definition: Site which has been experimentally altered.

Name: indel_artifact
Definition: An indel that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: internal_guide_sequence
Definition: A purine-rich sequence in the group I introns which determines the locations of the splice sites in group I intron splicing and has catalytic activity.

Name: nuclease_hypersensitive_site
Definition: A region of nucleotide sequence targeted by a nuclease enzyme that is found cleaved more than would be expected by chance.

Name: recombinationally_rearranged_gene
Definition: A gene that is recombinationally rearranged.

Name: H2B_ubiquitination_site
Definition: A histone modification site on H2B where ubiquitin may be added.

Name: enzymatic_RNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes an enzymatic RNA.

Name: aneuploid
Definition: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is not an exact multiple of the haploid number.

Name: seven_cyano_seven_deazaguanosine
Definition: 7_cyano_7_deazaguanosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: H3K9_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 9th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: homing_endonuclease_binding_site
Definition: The binding site (recognition site) of a homing endonuclease. The binding site is typically large.

Name: two_methylthio_N6_cis_hydroxyisopentenyl_adenosine
Definition: 2_methylthio_N6_cis_hydroxyisopentenyl_adenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: polypeptide_conserved_region
Definition: A subsection of sequence with biological interest that is conserved in different proteins. They may or may not have functional or structural significance within the proteins in which they are found.

Name: inversion_attribute
Definition: When a region of a chromosome is changed to the reverse order without duplication or deletion.

Name: predicted_gene
Definition: A region of the genome that has been predicted to be a gene but has not been confirmed by laboratory experiments.

Name: modified_L_arginine
Definition: A post translationally modified arginine amino acid feature.

Name: tmRNA_acceptor_piece
Definition: The acceptor region of a two-piece tmRNA that when mature is charged at its 3' end with alanine. The tmRNA gene undergoes circular permutation in some groups of bacteria; processing of the transcripts from such a gene leaves the mature tmRNA in two pieces	 base-paired together.

Name: intrachromosomal_transposition
Definition: A chromosome structure variation whereby a transposition occurred within a chromosome.

Name: GAGA_motif
Definition: A non directional promoter motif with consensus sequence GAGAGCG.

Name: S_GNA
Definition: An attribute describing a GNA sequence in the (S)-GNA enantiomer.

Name: restriction_enzyme_cleavage_junction
Definition: The boundary at which a restriction enzyme breaks the nucleotide sequence.

Name: PCR_product
Definition: A region amplified by a PCR reaction.

Name: wyosine
Definition: Wyosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: VJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one VJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: mini_exon_donor_RNA
Definition: A primary transcript that donates the spliced leader to other mRNA.

Name: extended_intronic_splice_region
Definition: Region of intronic sequence within 10 bases of an exon.

Name: promoter
Definition: A regulatory_region composed of the TSS(s) and binding sites for TF_complexes of the core transcription machinery. A region (DNA) to which RNA polymerase binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: foreign
Definition: An attribute to describe a region from another species.

Name: DRE_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 usually located between -10 and -60 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is WATCGATW.

Name: inversion
Definition: A continuous nucleotide sequence is inverted in the same position.

Name: V_VDJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one VDJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: three_prime_D_recombination_signal_sequence
Definition: Recombination signal of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene	 including the 3' D-heptamer (SO:0000493)	 3' D-spacer	 and 3' D-nonamer (SO:0000494) in 3' of the D-region of a D-gene.

Name: modified_L_aspartic_acid
Definition: A post translationally modified aspartic acid amino acid feature.

Name: chloroplast_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in a chloroplast.

Name: double
Definition: When a nucleotide polymer has two strands that are reverse-complement to one another and pair together.

Name: allelic_pseudogenic_tRNA
Definition: A (unitary) pseudogene that is stable in the population but importantly it has a functional alternative allele also in the population. i.e.	 one strain may have the gene	 another strain may have the pseudogene. MHC haplotypes have allelic pseudogenes.

Name: asx_turn_left_handed_type_two
Definition: Left handed type II (dihedral angles):- Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi (1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 +80 degrees < psi +120 degrees < +180 degrees. Residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees	 -40 degrees < psi < +90 degrees.

Name: H_pseudoknot
Definition: A pseudoknot which contains two stems and at least two loops.

Name: vertebrate_immune_system_gene_recombination_feature
Definition: A feature where recombination has occurred for the purpose of generating a diversity in the immune system.

Name: RNA
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases bound to a repeating unit made of a D-ribose ring connected to a phosphate backbone.

Name: two_prime_O_ribosylguanosine_phosphate
Definition: 2prime_O_ribosylguanosine_phosphate is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: interior_coding_exon
Definition: A coding exon that is not the most 3-prime or the most 5-prime in a given transcript.

Name: post_translationally_modified_region
Definition: A region where a transformation occurs in a protein after it has been synthesized. This which may regulate	 stabilize	 crosslink or introduce new chemical functionalities in the protein.

Name: regional_centromere
Definition: A regional centromere is a large modular centromere found in fission yeast and higher eukaryotes. It consist of a central core region flanked by inverted inner and outer repeat regions.

Name: U1_snRNA
Definition: U1 is a small nuclear RNA (snRNA) component of the spliceosome (involved in pre-mRNA splicing). Its 5' end forms complementary base pairs with the 5' splice junction	 thus defining the 5' donor site of an intron. There are significant differences in sequence and secondary structure between metazoan and yeast U1 snRNAs	 the latter being much longer (568 nucleotides as compared to 164 nucleotides in human). Nevertheless	 secondary structure predictions suggest that all U1 snRNAs share a 'common core' consisting of helices I	 II	 the proximal region of III	 and IV.

Name: three_prime_coding_exon
Definition: The coding exon that is most 3-prime on a given transcript.

Name: tRNA_SINE_retrotransposon
Definition: Short interspersed elements that originated from tRNAs.

Name: three_prime_intron
Definition: An intron that is the most 3-prime in a given transcript.

Name: isowyosine
Definition: Isowyosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: IG_V_gene
Definition: A variable gene that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the variable region of the variable domain of an Immunoglobulin chain.

Name: maternal_uniparental_disomy
Definition: Uniparental disomy is a sequence_alteration where a diploid individual receives two copies for all or part of a chromosome from the mother and no copies of the same chromosome or region from the father.

Name: proline_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding prolyl tRNA (SO:0000268).

Name: vertebrate_immunoglobulin_T_cell_receptor_rearranged_segment
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in partially rearranged genomic DNA.

Name: H2BK20_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 20th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2B histone protein is acetylated.

Name: silenced_by_histone_modification
Definition: An attribute describing an epigenetic process where a gene is inactivated by histone modification.

Name: V_VDJ_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene and one VDJ-gene.

Name: inverted_ring_chromosome
Definition: A ring chromosome is a chromosome whose arms have fused together to form a ring in an inverted fashion	 often with the loss of the ends of the chromosome.

Name: immature_peptide_region
Definition: An immature_peptide_region is the extent of the peptide after it has been translated and before any processing occurs.

Name: IRRinv_site
Definition: Component of the inversion site located at the right of a region susceptible to site-specific inversion.

Name: transcription_termination_signal
Definition: Termination signal preferentially observed downstream of polyadenylation signal

Name: MCB
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence ACGCGT	 bound by the transcription factor complex MBF (MCB-binding factor) and found in promoters of genes expressed during the G1/S transition of the cell cycle.

Name: chromosomal_duplication
Definition: An extra chromosome.

Name: H3K27_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 27th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is di-methylated.

Name: telomerase_RNA_gene
Definition: A telomerase RNA gene is a non coding RNA gene the RNA product of which is a component of telomerase.

Name: five_methylaminomethyl_two_thiouridine
Definition: 5_methylaminomethyl_2_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: endogenous_retroviral_gene
Definition: A proviral gene with origin endogenous retrovirus.

Name: allelic_pseudogene
Definition: A (unitary) pseudogene that is stable in the population but importantly it has a functional alternative allele also in the population. i.e.	 one strain may have the gene	 another strain may have the pseudogene. MHC haplotypes have allelic pseudogenes.

Name: topologically_defined_region
Definition: A DNA region within which self-interaction occurs more often than expected by chance because of DNA-looping.

Name: mRNA_with_plus_2_frameshift
Definition: An mRNA with a plus 2 frameshift.

Name: V_region
Definition: The variable region of an immunoglobulin polypeptide sequence.

Name: eukaryotic_terminator
Definition: A signal for RNA polymerase to terminate transcription.

Name: phenylalanine
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codons TTT and TTC.

Name: scRNA_gene
Definition: A small noncoding RNA that is generally found only in the cytoplasm.

Name: catmat_right_handed_four
Definition: A motif of 4 consecutive residues with dihedral angles as follows: res i: phi -90 bounds -120 to -60	 res i: psi -10 bounds -50 to 30	 res i+1: phi -90 bounds -120 to -60	 res i+1: psi -10 bounds -50 to 30	 res i+2: phi -75 bounds -100 to -50	 res i+2: psi 140 bounds 110 to 170. The extra restriction of the length of the O to O distance is similar	 that it be less than 5 Angstrom. In this case these two Oxygen atoms are the main chain carbonyl oxygen atoms of residues i-1 and i+2.

Name: asx_turn_left_handed_type_one
Definition: Left handed type I (dihedral angles):- Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi (1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi +120 degrees < +40 degrees. Residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees.

Name: group_IIC_intron
Definition: A group II intron that recognizes IBS1/EBS1 for the 5-prime exon and IBS3/EBS3 for the 3-prime exon and may also recognize a stem-loop in the RNA.

Name: beta_turn_right_handed_type_two
Definition: Right handed type II:A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. It is characterized by the dihedral angles: Residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 +80 degrees < psi < +180 degrees. Residue(i+2): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees	 -40 degrees < psi < +90 degrees.

Name: deficient_inversion
Definition: A chromosomal deletion whereby three breaks occur in the same chromosome; one central region is lost	 and the other is inverted.

Name: oligo
Definition: A short oligonucleotide sequence	 of length on the order of 10's of bases; either single or double stranded.

Name: plasmid_vector
Definition: A plasmid that has been generated to act as a vector for foreign sequence.

Name: polyadenylated_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA that is polyadenylated.

Name: alanine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding alanyl tRNA.

Name: polymorphic_pseudogene_processed_transcript
Definition: A processed transcript that does not contain a CDS that fullfills annotation criteria and not necessarily functionally non-coding.

Name: sequence_assembly
Definition: A sequence of nucleotides that has been algorithmically derived from an alignment of two or more different sequences.

Name: five_prime_UTR_intron
Definition: An intron located in the 5' UTR.

Name: PNA_oligo
Definition: Peptide nucleic acid	 is a chemical not known to occur naturally but is artificially synthesized and used in some biological research and medical treatments. The PNA backbone is composed of repeating N-(2-aminoethyl)-glycine units linked by peptide bonds. The purine and pyrimidine bases are linked to the backbone by methylene carbonyl bonds.

Name: iron_responsive_element
Definition: A regulatory sequence found in the 5' and 3' UTRs of many mRNAs which encode iron-binding proteins. It has a hairpin structure and is recognized by trans-acting proteins known as iron-regulatory proteins.

Name: circular_single_stranded_RNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 single-stranded	 circular DNA molecule.

Name: tasiRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a tasiRNA.

Name: polypeptide_nest_motif
Definition: A motif of two consecutive residues with dihedral angles. Nest should not have Proline as any residue. Nests frequently occur as parts of other motifs such as Schellman loops.

Name: gene_array
Definition: An array includes two or more genes	 or two or more gene subarrays	 contiguously arranged where the individual genes	 or subarrays	 are either identical in sequence	 or essentially so.

Name: two_prime_O_methylcytidine
Definition: 2'-O-methylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: ARRET
Definition: A non coding RNA transcript	 complementary to subtelomeric tract of TERRA transcript but devoid of the repeats.

Name: DCE_SII
Definition: A sub element of the DCE core promoter element with consensus sequence CTGT.

Name: protein_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide molecules.

Name: sequence_length_alteration
Definition: A kind of kind of sequence alteration where the copies of a region present varies across a population.

Name: contig_read
Definition: A DNA sequencer read which is part of a contig.

Name: substitution_artifact
Definition: A substitution that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: direct
Definition: A quality of an insertion where the insert is not in a cytologically inverted orientation.

Name: miRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a micro RNA.

Name: H4K5_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 5th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: three_ten_helix
Definition: The 3-10 helix has 3 residues per turn with a translation of 2.0 angstroms (=0.2 nm) along the helical axis. The N-H group of an amino acid forms a hydrogen bond with the C=O group of the amino acid three residues earlier.

Name: H2AZK13_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 13th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2AZ histone protein is acetylated.

Name: genomic_clone
Definition: A clone of a DNA region of a genome.

Name: alpha_helix
Definition: The helix has 3.6 residues per turn which corresponds to a translation of 1.5 angstroms (= 0.15 nm) along the helical axis. Every backbone N-H group donates a hydrogen bond to the backbone C=O group of the amino acid four residues earlier.

Name: unit_of_gene_expression
Definition: Transcription units or transcribed coding sequences.

Name: mitochondrial_contig
Definition: A contig of mitochondria derived sequences.

Name: RNApol_III_promoter_type_1
Definition: This type of promoter recruits RNA pol III. This promoter is intragenic and includes an A box	 an intermediate element	 and a C box. This is well conserved in the 5s rRNA promoters across species.

Name: restriction_enzyme_region
Definition: A region related to restriction enzyme function.

Name: distal_duplication
Definition: A duplication of the distal region of a chromosome.

Name: V_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one V-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: SL9_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL9 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL9 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: N6_2_prime_O_dimethyladenosine
Definition: N6_2prime_O_dimethyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: valyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a valine anticodon	 and a 3' valine binding region.

Name: LTR_retrotransposon
Definition: A retrotransposon flanked by long terminal repeat sequences.

Name: miRNA_loop
Definition: The loop of the hairpin loop formed by folding of the pre-miRNA.

Name: uninverted_interchromosomal_transposition
Definition: An interchromosomal transition where the segment between the first two breaks listed is removed and inserted at the third break; the insertion is in cytologically the same orientation as its flanking segments.

Name: invalidated_by_partial_processing
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that is invalidated due to partial processing.

Name: V_gene_recombination_feature
Definition: Recombination signal including V-heptamer	 V-spacer and V-nonamer in 3' of V-region of a V-gene or V-sequence of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: central_hydrophobic_region_of_signal_peptide
Definition: The central	 hydrophobic region of the signal peptide (approx 7-15 aa).

Name: non_cytoplasmic_polypeptide_region
Definition: Polypeptide region that is localized outside of a lipid bilayer and outside of the cytoplasm.

Name: non_terminal_residue
Definition: The residue at an extremity of the sequence is not the terminal residue.

Name: vertebrate_immunoglobulin_T_cell_receptor_gene_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration.

Name: histone_acylation_region
Definition: A histone modification	 whereby the histone protein is acylated at multiple sites in a region.

Name: trans_splice_acceptor_site
Definition: The 3' splice site of the acceptor primary transcript.

Name: foreign_transposable_element
Definition: A transposable element that is foreign.

Name: signal_anchor
Definition: A signal sequence that is not cleaved from the polypeptide. Anchors a Type II membrane protein to the membrane.

Name: five_carboxyhydroxymethyl_uridine_methyl_ester
Definition: 5_carboxyhydroxymethyl_uridine_methyl_ester is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: non_transcribed_region
Definition: A region of the gene which is not transcribed.

Name: TR_J_Gene
Definition: A joining gene that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the joining region of the variable domain of aT-cell receptor chain.

Name: homologous_chromosome_recognition_and_pairing_locus
Definition: A chromosomal locus where complementary lncRNA and associated proteins accumulate at the corresponding lncRNA gene loci to tether homologous chromosome during chromosome pairing at meiosis I.

Name: piRNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes for an piwi associated RNA.

Name: transposable_element
Definition: A transposon or insertion sequence. An element that can insert in a variety of DNA sequences.

Name: LINE1_deletion
Definition: A deletion of a LINE1 mobile element with respect to a reference.

Name: large_subunit_rRNA
Definition: Ribosomal RNA transcript that structures the large subunit of the ribosome.

Name: bacterial_RNApol_promoter
Definition: A DNA sequence to which bacterial RNA polymerase binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: glycine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding glycyl tRNA (SO:0000263).

Name: cyanelle_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a cyanelle	 a photosynthetic plastid found in algae.

Name: polyA_signal_sequence
Definition: The recognition sequence necessary for endonuclease cleavage of an RNA transcript that is followed by polyadenylation; consensus=AATAAA.

Name: TSS
Definition: The first base where RNA polymerase begins to synthesize the RNA transcript.

Name: polypeptide_zinc_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with zinc ions.

Name: stem_loop
Definition: A double-helical region of nucleic acid formed by base-pairing between adjacent (inverted) complementary sequences.

Name: two_thiocytidine
Definition: 2-thiocytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: paralogous
Definition: An attribute describing a kind of homology where divergence occurred after a duplication event.

Name: gene_attribute
Definition: An attribute describing a gene.

Name: FLEX_element
Definition: A promoter element that has consensus sequence GTAAACAAACAAAM and contains a heptameric core GTAAACA	 bound by transcription factors with a forkhead DNA-binding domain.

Name: recombinationally_rearranged_vertebrate_immune_system_gene
Definition: A recombinationally rearranged gene of the vertebrate immune system.

Name: microsatellite
Definition: A repeat_region containing repeat_units of 2 to 10 bp repeated in tandem.

Name: PIP_box
Definition: A polypeptide region that mediates binding to PCNA. The consensus sequence is QXX(hh)XX(aa)	 where (h) denotes residues with moderately hydrophobic side chains and (a) denotes residues with highly hydrophobic aromatic side chains.

Name: chromoplast_gene
Definition: A gene from chromoplast_sequence.

Name: Z2_region
Definition: A mating type region motif	 the rightmost segment of homology in the HML and MAT mating loci (not present in HMR).

Name: RNA_sequence_secondary_structure
Definition: A folded RNA sequence.

Name: Phage_RNA_Polymerase_Promoter
Definition: A region (DNA) to which Bacteriophage RNA polymerase binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: stem_loop_region
Definition: A portion of a stem loop secondary structure in RNA.

Name: teb1_recognition_motif
Definition: A binding motif with the consensus sequence TTAGGG to which Teb1 binds.

Name: LARD
Definition: Large Retrotransposon Derivative elements are long-terminal repeats that contain reverse transcriptase priming sites and are conserved in sequence but contain no open reading frames encoding typical retrotransposon proteins . The LARDs identified in barley and other Triticeae have LTRs ~5.5 kb and an interal domain of ~3.5 kb. LARDs lack coding domains and thus do not encode proteins.

Name: cis_acting_homologous_chromosome_pairing_region
Definition: A genome region where chromosome pairing occurs preferentially during homologous chromosome pairing during early meiotic prophase of Meiosis I.

Name: INR1_motif
Definition: A promoter motif with consensus sequence TCATTCG.

Name: ribozyme
Definition: An RNA with catalytic activity.

Name: cross_genome_match
Definition: A nucleotide match against a sequence from another organism.

Name: consensus_AFLP_fragment
Definition: A consensus AFLP fragment is an AFLP sequence produced from any alignment algorithm which uses assembled multiple AFLP sequences as input.

Name: metal_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with metal ions.

Name: maternally_imprinted
Definition: The maternal copy of the gene is modified	 rendering it transcriptionally silent.

Name: minor_TSS
Definition: A tanscription start site that is not the most frequently used for transcription of a gene.

Name: ASPE_primer
Definition:
A primer containing an SNV at the 3' end for accurate genotyping.	SO:0000112

Name: DDB_box
Definition: A conserved polypeptide motif that mediates protein-protein interaction and defines adaptor proteins for DDB1/cullin 4 ubiquitin ligases.

Name: novel_sequence_insertion
Definition: An insertion the sequence of which cannot be mapped to the reference genome.

Name: tmRNA_coding_piece
Definition: The region of a two-piece tmRNA that bears the reading frame encoding the proteolysis tag. The tmRNA gene undergoes circular permutation in some groups of bacteria. Processing of the transcripts from such a gene leaves the mature tmRNA in two pieces	 base-paired together.

Name: foreign_gene
Definition: A gene that is foreign.

Name: codon_redefined
Definition: An attribute describing the alteration of codon meaning.

Name: STS
Definition: Short (typically a few hundred base pairs) DNA sequence that has a single occurrence in a genome and whose location and base sequence are known.

Name: N6_N6_2_prime_O_trimethyladenosine
Definition: N6_N6_2prime_O_trimethyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: genomic_island
Definition: A genomic island is an integrated mobile genetic element	 characterized by size (over 10 Kb). It that has features that suggest a foreign origin. These can include nucleotide distribution (oligonucleotides signature	 CG content etc.) that differs from the bulk of the chromosome and/or genes suggesting DNA mobility.

Name: N6_glycinylcarbamoyladenosine
Definition: N6_glycinylcarbamoyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: rRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a ribosomal RNA.

Name: three_prime_flanking_region
Definition: A flanking region located three prime of a specific region.

Name: TNA_oligo
Definition: An oligo composed of TNA residues.

Name: J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: phagemid
Definition: A plasmid which carries within its sequence a bacteriophage replication origin. When the host bacterium is infected with "helper" phage	 a phagemid is replicated along with the phage DNA and packaged into phage capsids.

Name: decayed_exon
Definition: A non-functional descendant of an exon.

Name: inert_DNA_spacer
Definition: Sequences that decrease regulatory interactions between a promoter	 its 5' context and/or the translational unit(s) it regulated. Spacers can affect both translation and transcription.

Name: UAG_stop_codon_signal
Definition: A stop codon signal for a UAG stop codon redefinition.

Name: transition
Definition: Change of a pyrimidine nucleotide	 C or T	 into an other pyrimidine nucleotide	 or change of a purine nucleotide	 A or G	 into an other purine nucleotide.

Name: bidirectional_promoter_lncRNA
Definition: A non-coding locus that originates from within the promoter region of a protein-coding gene	 with transcription proceeding in the opposite direction on the other strand.

Name: apicoplast_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in an apicoplast.

Name: three_prime_stem_loop_structure
Definition: A recoding stimulatory region	 the stem-loop secondary structural element is downstream of the redefined region.

Name: deficient_interchromosomal_transposition
Definition: An interchromosomal transposition whereby a translocation in which one of the four broken ends loses a segment before re-joining.

Name: fingerprint_map
Definition: A fingerprint_map is a physical map composed of restriction fragments.

Name: transposon_fragment
Definition: A portion of a transposon	 interrupted by the insertion of another element.

Name: distant_three_prime_recoding_signal
Definition: A recoding signal that is found many hundreds of nucleotides 3' of a redefined stop codon.

Name: H3K36_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 36th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is mono-methylated.

Name: UNAAAC_motif
Definition: A hexameric RNA motif consisting of nucleotides UNAAAC (where N can be any nucleotide) that targets the RNA for degradation.

Name: engineered_rescue_region
Definition: A rescue region that is engineered.

Name: V_VJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one VJ-gene and one J-gene.

Name: endogenous_retroviral_sequence
Definition: Endogenous DNA sequence that are likely to have arisen from retroviruses.

Name: transposable_element_insertion_site
Definition: The junction in a genome where a transposable_element has inserted.

Name: restriction_fragment
Definition: A region of polynucleotide sequence produced by digestion with a restriction endonuclease.

Name: H3K79_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 79th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is mono- methylated.

Name: chromosomal_inversion
Definition: An interchromosomal mutation where a region of the chromosome is inverted with respect to wild type.

Name: five_carboxymethylaminomethyluridine
Definition: 5_carboxymethylaminomethyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: bacterial_RNApol_promoter_sigma54_element
Definition: A DNA sequence to which bacterial RNA polymerase sigma 54 binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: polyadenylated
Definition: A attribute describing the addition of a poly A tail to the 3' end of a mRNA molecule.

Name: noncoding_region_of_exon
Definition: The maximal intersection of exon and UTR.

Name: non_complimentary_stem
Definition: A region of a stem in a stem loop structure where the sequences are non-complimentary.

Name: three_prime_cis_splice_site
Definition: Intronic 2 bp region bordering the exon	 at the 3' edge of the intron. A splice_site that is upstream_adjacent_to exon and finishes intron.

Name: V_VJ_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene and one VJ-gene.

Name: N4_N4_2_prime_O_trimethylcytidine
Definition: N4_N4_2_prime_O_trimethylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: coiled_coil
Definition: A coiled coil is a structural motif in proteins	 in which alpha-helices are coiled together like the strands of a rope.

Name: translationally_regulated_gene
Definition: A gene that is translationally regulated.

Name: one_two_prime_O_dimethylinosine
Definition: 1	2'-O-dimethylinosine is a modified inosine.

Name: snoRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding one or more small nucleolar RNAs (SO:0000275).

Name: reverse
Definition: Reverse is an attribute of the feature	 where the feature is in the 3' to 5' direction. Again could be applied to primer.

Name: unoriented_interchromosomal_transposition
Definition: An interchromosomal transposition whereby a copy of the segment between the first two breaks listed is inserted at the third break; the orientation of the insertion with respect to its flanking segments is not recorded.

Name: rescue_gene
Definition: A gene that rescues.

Name: substitution
Definition: A sequence alteration where the length of the change in the variant is the same as that of the reference.

Name: paternally_imprinted
Definition: The paternal copy of the gene is modified	 rendering it transcriptionally silent.

Name: boundary_element
Definition: Boundary elements are DNA motifs that prevent heterochromatin from spreading into neighboring euchromatic regions.

Name: allele
Definition: An allele is one of a set of coexisting sequence variants of a gene.

Name: IG_C_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogenic constant region of an immunoglobulin gene which closely resembles a known functional Imunoglobulin constant gene but in which the coding region has stop codons	 frameshift mutations or a mutation that effects the initiation codon.

Name: three_prime_UST
Definition: A UST located in the 3'UTR of a protein-coding transcript.

Name: five_methylaminomethyluridine
Definition: 5_methylaminomethyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: telomeric_repeat
Definition: The telomeric repeat is a repeat region	 part of the chromosome	 which in yeast	 is a G-rich terminal sequence of the form (TG(1-3))n or more precisely ((TG)(1-6)TG(2-3))n.

Name: supported_by_domain_match
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that has been predicted using sequence similarity of a known domain.

Name: three_prime_sticky_end_restriction_enzyme_cleavage_site
Definition: A restriction enzyme recognition site that	 when cleaved	 results in 3 prime overhangs.

Name: MTE
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 usually located between +20 and +30 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is CSARCSSAACGS. Tends to co-occur with INR motif (SO:0000014). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or DMv5 (SO:0001159).

Name: RNase_P_RNA
Definition: The RNA component of Ribonuclease P (RNase P)	 a ubiquitous endoribonuclease	 found in archaea	 bacteria and eukarya as well as chloroplasts and mitochondria.
