Its best characterized activity is the generation of mature 5 prime ends of tRNAs by cleaving the 5 prime leader elements of precursor-tRNAs. Cellular RNase Ps are ribonucleoproteins. RNA from bacterial RNase Ps retains its catalytic activity in the absence of the protein subunit	 i.e. it is a ribozyme. Isolated eukaryotic and archaeal RNase P RNA has not been shown to retain its catalytic function	 but is still essential for the catalytic activity of the holoenzyme. Although the archaeal and eukaryotic holoenzymes have a much greater protein content than the bacterial ones	 the RNA cores from all the three lineages are homologous. Helices corresponding to P1	 P2	 P3	 P4	 and P10/11 are common to all cellular RNase P RNAs. Yet	 there is considerable sequence variation	 particularly among the eukaryotic RNAs.

Name: intergenic_region
Definition: A region containing or overlapping no genes that is bounded on either side by a gene	 or bounded by a gene and the end of the chromosome.

Name: deletion_artifact
Definition: A deletion that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: edited_transcript_by_A_to_I_substitution
Definition: A transcript that has been edited by A to I substitution.

Name: five_hydroxyuridine
Definition: 5_hydroxyuridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: conjugative_transposon
Definition: A transposon that encodes function required for conjugation.

Name: silenced_gene
Definition: A gene that is silenced.

Name: methylinosine
Definition: A modified RNA base in which methylhypoxanthine is bound to the ribose ring.

Name: RST_match
Definition: A match against an RST sequence.

Name: chromosomal_translocation
Definition: A chromosomal mutation. Rearrangements that alter the pairing of telomeres are classified as translocations.

Name: edited
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that is modified by editing.

Name: iron_repressed_GATA_element
Definition: A GATA promoter element with consensus sequence WGATAA	 found in promoters of genes repressed in the presence of iron.

Name: inversion_site
Definition: A region specifically recognised by a recombinase	 which inverts the region flanked by a pair of sites.

Name: RNA_polymerase_II_TATA_box
Definition: A TATA box core promoter of a gene transcribed by RNA polymerase II.

Name: DPE_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters; Positioned from +28 to +32 with respect to the TSS (+1). Experimental results suggest that the DPE acts in conjunction with the INR_motif to provide a binding site for TFIID in the absence of a TATA box to mediate transcription of TATA-less promoters. Consensus sequence (A|G)G(A|T)(C|T)(G|A|C).

Name: binding_site
Definition: A biological_region of sequence that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with other molecules. A region on the surface of a molecule that may interact with another molecule. When applied to polypeptides: Amino acids involved in binding or interactions. It can also apply to an amino acid bond which is represented by the positions of the two flanking amino acids.

Name: modified_L_threonine
Definition: A post translationally modified threonine amino acid feature.

Name: beta_turn_type_eight
Definition: A motif of four consecutive peptide residues that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth and is characterized by the dihedral angles: Residue(i+1): phi ~ -60 degrees	 psi ~ -30 degrees. Residue(i+2): phi ~ -120 degrees	 psi ~ 120 degrees.

Name: virtual_sequence
Definition: A continuous piece of sequence similar to the 'virtual contig' concept of the Ensembl database.

Name: chromosomal_variation_attribute
Definition: An attribute of a change in the structure or number of a chromosomes.

Name: five_prime_terminal_inverted_repeat
Definition: An inverted repeat (SO:0000294) occurring at the 5-prime termini of a DNA transposon.

Name: gene_silenced_by_histone_methylation
Definition: A gene that is silenced by histone methylation.

Name: H4K16_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 16th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: Crypton_YR_transposon
Definition: Crypton is a superfamily of DNA transposons that use tyrosine recombinase (YR) to cut and rejoin the recombining DNA molecules.

Name: histidine
Definition: A positively charged	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons CAT and CAC.

Name: hyperploid
Definition: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is not an exact multiple of the haploid number as extra chromosomes are present.

Name: LINE_element
Definition: A dispersed repeat family with many copies	 each from 1 to 6 kb long. New elements are generated by retroposition of a transcribed copy. Typically the LINE contains 2 ORF's one of which is reverse transcriptase	 and 3'and 5' direct repeats.

Name: scRNA
Definition: A small non coding RNA sequence	 present in the cytoplasm.

Name: polypeptide_structural_region
Definition: Region of polypeptide with a given structural property.

Name: mobile
Definition: An attribute describing a feature that has either intra-genome or intracellular mobility.

Name: leucine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding leucyl tRNA (SO:0000264).

Name: transcription_factor_regulatory_site
Definition: A TF_binding_site that is involved in regulation of expression.

Name: translational_product_structure_variant
Definition: A sequence variant within the transcript that changes the structure of the translational product.

Name: probe
Definition: A DNA sequence used experimentally to detect the presence or absence of a complementary nucleic acid.

Name: rRNA_23S_gene
Definition: A gene which codes for 23S_rRNA	 which functions as a component of the large subunit of the ribosome in prokaryotes.

Name: genomic_DNA_read
Definition: A sequencer read of a genomic DNA substrate.

Name: glutamine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding glutamyl tRNA (SO:0000260).

Name: paracentric
Definition: An inversion event that does not include the centromere.

Name: rRNA_16S_gene
Definition: A gene which codes for 16S_rRNA	 which functions as the small subunit of the ribosome in prokaryotes.

Name: possible_assembly_error
Definition: A region of sequence where there may have been an error in the assembly.

Name: reagent
Definition: A sequence used in experiment.

Name: polypeptide_calcium_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with calcium ions.

Name: five_prime_flanking_region
Definition: A flanking region located five prime of a specific region.

Name: T_loop
Definition: Non-base-paired sequence of three nucleotide bases in tRNA. It has sequence T-Psi-C.

Name: kozak_sequence
Definition: A kind of ribosome entry site	 specific to Eukaryotic organisms that overlaps part of both 5' UTR and CDS sequence.

Name: bipartite_duplication
Definition: An interchromosomal mutation whereby the (large) region between the first two breaks listed is lost	 and the two flanking segments (one of them centric) are joined as a translocation to the free ends resulting from the third break.

Name: extrachromosomal_mobile_genetic_element
Definition: An MGE that is not integrated into the host chromosome.

Name: rRNA_cleavage_RNA
Definition: An ncRNA that is part of a ribonucleoprotein that cleaves the primary pre-rRNA transcript in the process of producing mature rRNA molecules.

Name: H3K4_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification	 whereby the 4th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 protein is mono-methylated.

Name: transcript_bound_by_nucleic_acid
Definition: A transcript that is bound by a nucleic acid.

Name: low_complexity_region
Definition: A region where the DNA does not contain an equal distrubution of all four possible nucleotides or does not contain all four nucleotides.

Name: two_prime_O_ribosyladenosine_phosphate
Definition: 2prime_O_ribosyladenosine_phosphate is a modified adenosine.

Name: repeat_component
Definition: A region of a repeated sequence.

Name: dye_terminator_read
Definition: A read produced by the dye terminator method of sequencing.

Name: DJ_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one DJ-gene and one C-gene.

Name: histone_2B_acetylation_site
Definition: A histone 2B modification where the modification is the acetylation of the residue.

Name: Mat3M
Definition: A gene cassette array containing H- mating type specific information.

Name: modified_L_phenylalanine
Definition: A post translationally modified phenylalanine amino acid feature.

Name: positional_candidate_gene
Definition: A candidate gene whose association with a trait is based on the gene's location on a chromosome.

Name: J_spacer
Definition: 12 or 23 nucleotide spacer between the J-nonamer and the J-heptamer of a J-gene recombination feature of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: hydroxywybutosine
Definition: Hydroxywybutosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: retron
Definition: Sequence coding for a short	 single-stranded	 DNA sequence via a retrotransposed RNA intermediate; characteristic of some microbial genomes.

Name: locus_control_region
Definition: A DNA region that includes DNAse hypersensitive sites located near a gene that confers the high-level	 position-independent	 and copy number-dependent expression to that gene.

Name: copy_number_variation
Definition: A variation that increases or decreases the copy number of a given region.

Name: inverted_insertional_duplication
Definition: An insertional duplication where a copy of the segment between the first two breaks listed is inserted at the third break; the insertion is in cytologically inverted orientation with respect to its flanking segments.

Name: nuclear_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in a nucleus.

Name: C_to_T_transition_at_pCpG_site
Definition: The transition of cytidine to thymine occurring at a pCpG site as a consequence of the spontaneous deamination of 5'-methylcytidine.

Name: N4_acetyl_2_prime_O_methylcytidine
Definition: N4-acetyl-2'-O-methylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: CDS_extension
Definition: A sequence variant extending the CDS	 that causes elongation of the resulting polypeptide sequence.

Name: exon
Definition: A region of the transcript sequence within a gene which is not removed from the primary RNA transcript by RNA splicing.

Name: tiling_path
Definition: A set of regions which overlap with minimal polymorphism to form a linear sequence.

Name: selection_marker
Definition: A genetic feature that encodes a trait used for artificial selection of a subpopulation.

Name: five_two_prime_O_dimethylcytidine
Definition: 5	2'-O-dimethylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: arginyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has an arginine anticodon	 and a 3' arginine binding region.

Name: paralogous_region
Definition: A homologous_region that is paralogous to another region.

Name: five_carboxymethylaminomethyl_two_thiouridine
Definition: 5_carboxymethylaminomethyl_2_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: proplastid_gene
Definition: A gene from proplastid sequence.

Name: tRNA
Definition: Transfer RNA (tRNA) molecules are approximately 80 nucleotides in length. Their secondary structure includes four short double-helical elements and three loops (D	 anti-codon	 and T loops). Further hydrogen bonds mediate the characteristic L-shaped molecular structure. Transfer RNAs have two regions of fundamental functional importance: the anti-codon	 which is responsible for specific mRNA codon recognition	 and the 3' end	 to which the tRNA's corresponding amino acid is attached (by aminoacyl-tRNA synthetases). Transfer RNAs cope with the degeneracy of the genetic code in two manners: having more than one tRNA (with a specific anti-codon) for a particular amino acid; and 'wobble' base-pairing	 i.e. permitting non-standard base-pairing at the 3rd anti-codon position.

Name: st_turn_right_handed_type_one
Definition: The peptide twists in an clockwise	 right handed manner. The dihedral angles for this turn are: Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi(1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees psi +120 degrees < +40 degrees	 residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 < psi < +40 degrees.

Name: stop_codon
Definition: In mRNA	 a set of three nucleotides that indicates the end of information for protein synthesis.

Name: sequence_comparison
Definition: A position or feature where two sequences have been compared.

Name: Endogenous_Retrovirus_LTR_retrotransposon
Definition: Endogenous retrovirus (ERV) retrotransposons are abundant in the genomes of jawed vertebrates. Human ERVs (HERVs) are classified based on their homologies to animal retroviruses. Class I families are similar in sequence to mammalian Gammaretroviruses (type C) and Epsilonretroviruses (Type E). Class II families show homology to mammalian Betaretroviruses (Type B) and Deltaretroviruses (Type D). F-Class III families are similar to foamy viruses.

Name: accessible_DNA_region
Definition: A region of DNA that is depleted of nucleosomes and accessible to DNA-binding proteins including transcription factors and nucleases.

Name: H2BK120_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 120th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2B histone protein is acetylated.

Name: negative_sense_ssRNA_viral_sequence
Definition: A negative_sense_RNA_viral_sequence is a ss_RNA_viral_sequence that is the sequence of a single stranded RNA virus that is complementary to mRNA and must be converted to positive sense RNA by RNA polymerase before translation.

Name: two_methylthio_N6_isopentenyladenosine
Definition: 2_methylthio_N6_isopentenyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: D_loop
Definition: Displacement loop; a region within mitochondrial DNA in which a short stretch of RNA is paired with one strand of DNA	 displacing the original partner DNA strand in this region; also used to describe the displacement of a region of one strand of duplex DNA by a single stranded invader in the reaction catalyzed by RecA protein.

Name: valine
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codons GTN (GTT	 GTC	 GTA and GTG).

Name: plastid_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a plastid such as a chloroplast.

Name: GT_dinucleotide_repeat
Definition: A dinucleotide repeat region composed of GT repeating elements.

Name: T_to_G_transversion
Definition: A transversion from T to G.

Name: presence_absence_variation
Definition: A variation qualifying the presence of a sequence in a genome which is entirely missing in another genome.

Name: double_stranded_DNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 double-stranded DNA molecule.

Name: interchromosomal
Definition: A change in chromosomes that occurs between two sections of the same chromosome or between homologous chromosomes.

Name: promoter_trap_construct
Definition: A promoter trap construct is a type of engineered plasmid which is designed to integrate into a genome and express a reporter when inserted in close proximity to a promoter element. Promoter traps typically do not contain promoter elements and are mutagenic.

Name: translation_regulatory_region
Definition: A regulatory region that is involved in the control of the process of translation.

Name: snoRNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a small nucleolar RNA (snoRNA).

Name: V_D_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one V-gene	 one D-gene and one J-gene.

Name: TCS_element
Definition: A TCS element is a (yeast) transcription factor binding site	 bound by the TEA DNA binding domain (DBD) of transcription factors. The consensus site is CATTCC or CATTCT.

Name: chromosome_variation
Definition: A deviation in chromosome structure or number.

Name: TFRS_collection
Definition: The possible discontinous stretch of DNA that encompass all the TFRSs that regulate a promoter.

Name: E_box_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 usually located between -60 and +1 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is AWCAGCTGWT. Tends to co-occur with DMv2 (SO:0001161). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015).

Name: recursive_splice_site
Definition: A recursive splice site is a splice site which subdivides a large intron. Recursive splicing is a mechanism that splices large introns by sub dividing the intron at non exonic elements and alternate exons.

Name: strand_attribute
Definition: The attribute of how many strands are present in a nucleotide polymer.

Name: flanking_repeat
Definition: A repeat lying outside the sequence for which it has functional significance (eg. transposon insertion target sites).

Name: sncRNA
Definition: A non-coding RNA less than 200 nucleotides in length.

Name: regional_centromere_inner_repeat_region
Definition: The inner inverted repeat region of a modular centromere and part of the central core surrounding a non-conserved central region. This region is adjacent to the central core	 on each chromosome arm.

Name: histone_2A_acetylation_site
Definition: A histone 2A modification where the modification is the acetylation of the residue.

Name: telomere
Definition: A specific structure at the end of a linear chromosome	 required for the integrity and maintenance of the end.

Name: polypeptide_structural_motif
Definition: Motif is a three-dimensional structural element within the chain	 which appears also in a variety of other molecules. Unlike a domain	 a motif does not need to form a stable globular unit.

Name: transcription_start_cluster
Definition: A region defined by a cluster of experimentally determined transcription starting sites.

Name: threonine
Definition: A polar	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons ACN (ACT	 ACC	 ACA and ACG).

Name: reverse_primer
Definition: A single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction.

Name: one_two_prime_O_dimethylguanosine
Definition: 1_2prime_O_dimethylguanosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: SL6_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL6 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL6 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: engineered_gene
Definition: A gene that is engineered.

Name: cap
Definition: A structure consisting of a 7-methylguanosine in 5'-5' triphosphate linkage with the first nucleotide of an mRNA. It is added post-transcriptionally	 and is not encoded in the DNA.

Name: RNA_thermometer
Definition: An RNA_thermometer is a cis element in the 5' end of an mRNA that can change its secondary structure in response to temperature and coordinate temperature-dependent gene expression.

Name: V_DJ_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one DJ-gene and one C-gene.

Name: insertion_sequence
Definition: A terminal_inverted_repeat_element that is bacterial and only encodes the functions required for its transposition between these inverted repeats.

Name: unspecified_indel
Definition: A sequence alteration which includes an insertion or a deletion. This describes a sequence length change when the direction of the change is unspecified or when such changes are pooled into one category.

Name: R_five_prime_LTR_region
Definition: The R segment of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: sequence_feature
Definition: Any extent of continuous biological sequence.

Name: peptide_localization_signal
Definition: A region of peptide sequence used to target the polypeptide molecule to a specific organelle.

Name: beta_bulge_loop
Definition: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet consisting of two H-bonds. Beta bulge loops often occur at the loop ends of beta-hairpins.

Name: partially_processed_cDNA_clone
Definition: A cDNA invalidated clone by partial processing.

Name: U2_snRNA
Definition: U2 is a small nuclear RNA (snRNA) component of the spliceosome (involved in pre-mRNA splicing). Complementary binding between U2 snRNA (in an area lying towards the 5' end but 3' to hairpin I) and the branchpoint sequence (BPS) of the intron results in the bulging out of an unpaired adenine	 on the BPS	 which initiates a nucleophilic attack at the intronic 5' splice site	 thus starting the first of two transesterification reactions that mediate splicing.

Name: intron
Definition: A region of a primary transcript that is transcribed	 but removed from within the transcript by splicing together the sequences (exons) on either side of it.

Name: group_IIA_intron
Definition: A group II intron that recognizes IBS1/EBS1 and IBS2/EBS2 for the 5-prime exon and gamma/gamma-prime for the 3-prime exon.

Name: chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a nucleic acid molecule which controls its own replication through the interaction of specific proteins at one or more origins of replication.

Name: polymorphic_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene in the reference genome	 though known to be intact in the genomes of other individuals of the same species. The annotation process has confirmed that the pseudogenisation event is not a genomic sequencing error.

Name: R2_LINE_retrotransposon
Definition: R2 retrotransposons are LINE elements (SO:0000194) that insert site-specifically into the host organism's 28S ribosomal RNA (rRNA) genes.

Name: polypeptide_region
Definition: Biological sequence region that can be assigned to a specific subsequence of a polypeptide.

Name: seryl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a serine anticodon	 and a 3' serine binding region.

Name: nucleotide_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with nucleotide residues.

Name: sequence_difference
Definition: A region where the sequence differs from that of a specified sequence.

Name: topologically_associated_domain_boundary
Definition: A DNA region enriched in DNA loop anchors and across which DNA loops occur less often than expected by chance.

Name: chloroplast_DNA_read
Definition: A sequencer read of a chloroplast DNA sample.

Name: supported_by_sequence_similarity
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that has been predicted using sequence similarity techniques.

Name: N2_7_2prirme_O_trimethylguanosine
Definition: N2_7_2prirme_O_trimethylguanosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: H_ACA_box_snoRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a small nucleolar RNA of the box H/ACA family.

Name: alanine
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codons GCN (GCT	 GCC	 GCA and GCG).

Name: 4_methylcytosine
Definition: A cytosine methylated at the 4 nitrogen.

Name: R_LTR_region
Definition: The R segment of the long terminal repeats.

Name: inversion_site_part
Definition: A region located within an inversion site.

Name: lambda_vector
Definition: The lambda bacteriophage is the vector for the linear lambda clone. The genes involved in the lysogenic pathway are removed from the from the viral DNA. Up to 25 kb of foreign DNA can then be inserted into the lambda genome.

Name: orthologous
Definition: An attribute describing a kind of homology where divergence occurred after a speciation event.

Name: UTR
Definition: Messenger RNA sequences that are untranslated and lie five prime or three prime to sequences which are translated.

Name: engineered_foreign_gene
Definition: A gene that is engineered and foreign.

Name: UPD
Definition: Uniparental disomy is a sequence_alteration where a diploid individual receives two copies for all or part of a chromosome from one parent and no copies of the same chromosome or region from the other parent.

Name: UAA_stop_codon_signal
Definition: A stop codon signal for a UAA stop codon redefinition.

Name: polyploid
Definition: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is an exact multiple of the haploid number and is greater than the diploid number.

Name: N2_2_prime_O_dimethylguanosine
Definition: N2_2prime_O_dimethylguanosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: ncRNA
Definition: An RNA transcript that does not encode for a protein rather the RNA molecule is the gene product.

Name: A_box_type_1
Definition: An A box within an RNA polymerase III type 1 promoter.

Name: I_LINE_retrotransposon
Definition: Elements of the LINE I superfamily are similar to the Jockey and L1 superfamily. They contains two ORFs	 the.second of which includesB  Apurinic endonuclease (APE) andB  reverse transcriptase (RT). The I superfamily encodes an RH (RNase H) domain downstream of the RT domain.

Name: centromere
Definition: A region of chromosome where the spindle fibers attach during mitosis and meiosis.

Name: five_carboxymethylaminomethyl_two_prime_O_methyluridine
Definition: 5_carboxymethylaminomethyl_2_prime_O_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: RNApol_II_promoter
Definition: A DNA sequence in eukaryotic DNA to which RNA polymerase II binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: RR_tract
Definition: A polypurine tract within an LTR_retrotransposon.

Name: foldback_element
Definition: A transposable element with extensive secondary structure	 characterized by large modular imperfect long inverted repeats.

Name: CSL_response_element
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence GTGRGAA	 bound by CSL (CBF1/RBP-JK/Suppressor of Hairless/LAG-1) transcription factors.

Name: snoRNA_gene
Definition: A small noncoding RNA that guides chemical modification of other RNAs.

Name: exemplar_mRNA
Definition: An exemplar is a representative cDNA sequence for each gene. The exemplar approach is a method that usually involves some initial clustering into gene groups and the subsequent selection of a representative from each gene group.

Name: ribozymic
Definition: An attribute describing the sequence of a transcript that has catalytic activity even without an associated ribonucleoprotein.

Name: active_peptide
Definition: Active peptides are proteins which are biologically active	 released from a precursor molecule.

Name: gene_with_recoded_mRNA
Definition: A gene that encodes an mRNA that is recoded.

Name: natural_transposable_element
Definition: TE that exists (or existed) in nature.

Name: alpha_beta_motif
Definition: A motif of five consecutive residues and two H-bonds in which: H-bond between CO of residue(i) and NH of residue(i+4)	 H-bond between CO of residue(i) and NH of residue(i+3)	Phi angles of residues(i+1)	 (i+2) and (i+3) are negative.

Name: IG_C_gene
Definition: A constant (C) gene	 a gene that codes the constant region of an immunoglobulin chain.

Name: tasiRNA
Definition: The sequence of a 21 nucleotide double stranded	 polyadenylated non coding RNA	 transcribed from the TAS gene.

Name: long_terminal_repeat_transcript
Definition: An RNA that is transcribed from a long terminal repeat.

Name: androgen_response_element
Definition: A non-palindromic sequence found in the promoters of genes whose expression is regulated in response to androgen.

Name: DNA
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases bound to a repeating unit made of a 2-deoxy-D-ribose ring connected to a phosphate backbone.

Name: cryptic_gene
Definition: A gene that is not transcribed under normal conditions and is not critical to normal cellular functioning.

Name: prophage
Definition: A phage genome after it has established in the host genome in a latent/immune state either as a plasmid or as an integrated "island".

Name: alternate_sequence_site
Definition: Description of sequence variants produced by alternative splicing	 alternative promoter usage	 alternative initiation and ribosomal frameshifting.

Name: pyrrolysyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a pyrrolysine anticodon	 and a 3' pyrrolysine binding region.

Name: UTR_intron
Definition: Intron located in the untranslated region.

Name: inversion_breakpoint
Definition: The point within a chromosome where an inversion begins or ends.

Name: edited_CDS
Definition: A CDS that is edited.

Name: silenced
Definition: An attribute describing an epigenetic process where a gene is inactivated at transcriptional or translational level.

Name: tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a transfer RNA (SO:0000253).

Name: i_motif
Definition: A cytosine rich domain whereby strands associate both inter- and intramolecularly at moderately acidic pH.

Name: AUG_initiated_uORF
Definition: A uORF beginning with the canonical start codon AUG.

Name: TR_J_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogenic joining region which closely resembles a known functional T receptor (TR) joining gene but in which the coding region has stop codons	 frameshift mutations or a mutation that effects the initiation codon that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the joining region of the variable domain of an immunoglobulin chain.

Name: nested_tandem_repeat
Definition: An NTR is a nested repeat of two distinct tandem motifs interspersed with each other.

Name: phenylalanine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding phenylalanyl tRNA (SO:0000267).

Name: sarcin_like_RNA_motif
Definition: A loop in ribosomal RNA containing the sites of attack for ricin and sarcin.

Name: V_D_DJ_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one D-gene	 one DJ-gene.

Name: Y_RNA
Definition: Y RNAs are components of the Ro ribonucleoprotein particle (Ro RNP)	 in association with Ro60 and La proteins. The Y RNAs and Ro60 and La proteins are well conserved	 but the function of the Ro RNP is not known. In humans the RNA component can be one of four small RNAs: hY1	 hY3	 hY4 and hY5. These small RNAs are predicted to fold into a conserved secondary structure containing three stem structures. The largest of the four	 hY1	 contains an additional hairpin.

Name: C_region
Definition: The constant region of an immunoglobulin polypeptide sequence.

Name: pseudogenic_transcript_with_retained_intron
Definition: A transcript supported by EST and/or mRNA evidence that aligns unambiguously to the pseudogene locus; has retained intronic sequence compared to a reference transcript sequence.

Name: aptamer
Definition: DNA or RNA molecules that have been selected from random pools based on their ability to bind other molecules.

Name: morpholino_backbone
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence composed of nucleobases bound to a morpholino backbone. A morpholino backbone consists of morpholine (CHEBI:34856) rings connected by phosphorodiamidate linkages.

Name: beta_turn_left_handed_type_one
Definition: Left handed type I:A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. It is characterized by the dihedral angles:- Residue(i+1): -140 degrees > phi > -20 degrees	 -90 degrees > psi > +40 degrees. Residue(i+2): -140 degrees > phi > -20 degrees	 -90 degrees > psi > +40 degrees.

Name: histone_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the nucleotide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues of a histone.

Name: inversion_derived_bipartite_deficiency
Definition: A chromosomal deletion whereby a chromosome generated by recombination between two inversions; has a deficiency at each end of the inversion.

Name: H2AZK11_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 11th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2AZ histone protein is acetylated.

Name: DJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one DJ-gene	 and one J-gene.

Name: BAC
Definition: Bacterial Artificial Chromosome	 a cloning vector that can be propagated as mini-chromosomes in a bacterial host.

Name: positively_autoregulated
Definition: The gene product is involved in its own transcriptional regulation	 where it increases transcription.

Name: T_cell_receptor_gene
Definition: A T-cell receptor germline gene.

Name: three_two_prime_O_dimethyluridine
Definition: 3_2prime_O_dimethyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: uninverted_insertional_duplication
Definition: An insertional duplication where a copy of the segment between the first two breaks listed is inserted at the third break; the insertion is in cytologically the same orientation as its flanking segments.

Name: reciprocal_chromosomal_translocation
Definition: A chromosomal translocation with two breaks; two chromosome segments have simply been exchanged.

Name: mRNA_recoded_by_codon_redefinition
Definition: A recoded_mRNA that was modified by an alteration of codon meaning.

Name: restriction_enzyme_assembly_scar
Definition: A region of DNA sequence formed from the ligation of two sticky ends where the palindrome is broken and no longer comprises the recognition site and thus cannot be re-cut by the restriction enzymes used to create the sticky ends.

Name: transit_peptide_region_of_CDS
Definition: CDS region corresponding to a transit peptide region of a polypeptide.

Name: modified_cytidine
Definition: A modified cytidine is a cytidine base feature which has been altered.

Name: H2BK5_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 5th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2B protein is methylated.

Name: beta_turn
Definition: A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. It is characterized by the dihedral angles of the second and third residues	 which are the basis for sub-categorization.

Name: modified_L_asparagine
Definition: A post translationally modified asparagine amino acid feature.

Name: H2BK5_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 5th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2B histone protein is acetylated.

Name: free_duplication
Definition: A chromosome structure variation whereby the duplicated sequences are carried as a free centric element.

Name: wobble_base_pair
Definition: A type of non-canonical base pairing	 most commonly between G and U	 which is important for the secondary structure of RNAs. It has similar thermodynamic stability to the Watson-Crick pairing. Wobble base pairs only have two hydrogen bonds. Other wobble base pair possibilities are I-A	 I-U and I-C.

Name: free_ring_duplication
Definition: A ring chromosome which is a copy of another chromosome.

Name: transposable_element_flanking_region
Definition: The region of sequence surrounding a transposable element.

Name: lncRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a  lncRNA.

Name: polypeptide_DNA_contact
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with DNA.

Name: methionyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a methionine anticodon	 and a 3' methionine binding region.

Name: editing_domain
Definition: Edited mRNA sequence mediated by two or more overlapping guide RNAs (SO:0000602).

Name: linear_single_stranded_DNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 single-stranded	 linear DNA molecule.

Name: scRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: The primary transcript of any one of several small cytoplasmic RNA molecules present in the cytoplasm and sometimes nucleus of a Eukaryote.

Name: nucleomorphic_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a plastid such as a chloroplast. The nucleomorph is the nuclei of the plastic.

Name: duplicated_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene that arose via gene duplication. Generally duplicated pseudogenes have the same structure as the original gene	 including intron-exon structure and some regulatory sequence.

Name: edited_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA that is edited.

Name: rRNA_large_subunit_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a large ribosomal subunit RNA.

Name: pericentric
Definition: An inversion event that includes the centromere.

Name: reference_genome
Definition: A collection of sequences (often chromosomes) taken as the standard for a given organism and genome assembly.

Name: W_region
Definition: The leftmost segment of homology in the HML and MAT mating loci	  but not present in HMR.

Name: MNV
Definition: An MNV is a multiple nucleotide variant (substitution) in which the inserted sequence is the same length as the replaced sequence.

Name: U6atac_snRNA
Definition: U6atac_snRNA is an snRNA required for the splicing of the minor U12-dependent class of eukaryotic nuclear introns. It forms a base paired complex with U4atac_snRNA (SO:0000394).

Name: three_prime_D_spacer
Definition: A 12 or 23 nucleotide spacer between the 3'D-HEPTAMER and 3'D-NONAMER of a 3'D-RS.

Name: homo_compound_chromosome
Definition: A compound chromosome whereby two copies of the same chromosomal arm attached to a common centromere. The chromosome is diploid for the arm involved.

Name: interchromosomal_duplication
Definition: A chromosome duplication involving an insertion from another chromosome.

Name: ribozyme_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes a ribozyme.

Name: three_prime_repeat_recoding_signal
Definition: A recoding stimulatory signal	 downstream sequence important for recoding that contains repetitive elements.

Name: recoded
Definition: An attribute describing an mRNA sequence that has been reprogrammed at translation	 causing localized alterations.

Name: G_quartet
Definition: G-quartets are unusual nucleic acid structures consisting of a planar arrangement where each guanine is hydrogen bonded by hoogsteen pairing to another guanine in the quartet.

Name: mRNA_with_minus_2_frameshift
Definition: A mRNA with a minus 2 frameshift.

Name: membrane_structure
Definition: Arrangement of the polypeptide with respect to the lipid bilayer.

Name: V_VJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one VJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: cloned_cDNA_insert
Definition: A clone insert made from cDNA.

Name: rRNA_18S_gene
Definition: A gene which codes for 18S_rRNA	 which functions as the small subunit of the ribosome in eukaryotes.

Name: A_to_T_transversion
Definition: A transversion from adenine to thymine.

Name: N2_N2_2_prime_O_trimethylguanosine
Definition: N2_N2_2prime_O_trimethylguanosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: three_prime_D_heptamer
Definition: 7 nucleotide recombination site like CACAGTG	 part of a 3' D-recombination signal sequence of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: recombination_signal_sequence
Definition: A region recognized by a recombinase.

Name: YAC
Definition: Yeast Artificial Chromosome	 a vector constructed from the telomeric	 centromeric	 and replication origin sequences needed for replication in yeast cells.

Name: polycistronic_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA that encodes multiple proteins from at least two non-overlapping regions.

Name: J_gene_recombination_feature
Definition: Recombination signal including J-heptamer	 J-spacer and J-nonamer in 5' of J-region of a J-gene or J-sequence.

Name: RAPD
Definition: RAPD is a 'PCR product' where a sequence variant is identified through the use of PCR with random primers.

Name: beta_strand
Definition: A beta strand describes a single length of polypeptide chain that forms part of a beta sheet. A single continuous stretch of amino acids adopting an extended conformation of hydrogen bonds between the N-O and the C=O of another part of the peptide. This forms a secondary protein structure in which two or more extended polypeptide regions are hydrogen-bonded to one another in a planar array.

Name: SRP_RNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a signal recognition particle RNA.

Name: small_regulatory_ncRNA
Definition: A non-coding RNA less than 200 nucleotides long	 usually with a specific secondary structure	 that acts to regulate gene expression. These include short ncRNAs such as piRNA	 miRNA and siRNAs (among others).

Name: duplication
Definition: An insertion which derives from	 or is identical in sequence to	 nucleotides present at a known location in the genome.

Name: mannosyl_queuosine
Definition: Mannosyl_queuosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: histone_methylation_site
Definition: A histone modification site where the modification is the methylation of the residue.

Name: Crick_strand
Definition: An absolute reference to the strand. When a chromosome has p and q arms	 the Crick strand is the strand whose 5'-end is on the long arm of the chromosome. Of note	 the term 'minus strand' is typically based on a reference sequence where it's preferred for the minus strand to be the Crick strand	 but might not be and 'minus strand' is therefore not an exact synonym.

Name: dicistronic_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript that has the quality dicistronic.

Name: predicted
Definition: An attribute describing an unverified region.

Name: destruction_box
Definition: A conserved polypeptide motif that can be recognized by both Fizzy/Cdc20- and FZR/Cdh1-activated anaphase-promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C) and targets a protein for ubiquitination and subsequent degradation by the APC/C. The consensus sequence is RXXLXXXXN.

Name: gene_rearranged_at_DNA_level
Definition: An epigenetically modified gene	 rearranged at the DNA level.

Name: rho_dependent_bacterial_terminator
Definition: A transcription terminator that is dependent upon Rho.

Name: intein
Definition: A region of a peptide that is able to excise itself and rejoin the remaining portions with a peptide bond.

Name: D_DJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one D-gene	 one DJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: vertebrate_immune_system_gene
Definition: The configuration of the  IG and TR variable (V)	 diversity (D) and joining (J) germline genes before DNA rearrangements  (with or without constant (C) genes in undefined configuration. (germline	 non rearranged regions of the IG DNA loci).

Name: plus_1_translational_frameshift
Definition: The region of mRNA 1 base long that is skipped during the process of translational frameshifting (GO:0006452)	 causing the reading frame to be different.

Name: assortment_derived_aneuploid
Definition: A multi-chromosome aberration generated by reassortment of other aberration components; presumed to have a deficiency or a duplication.

Name: five_methyluridine
Definition: 5_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: consensus_region
Definition: A region that has a known consensus sequence.

Name: nuclease_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 of a nucleotide molecule	 that interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues of a nuclease.

Name: sticky_end_restriction_enzyme_cleavage_site
Definition: A site where restriction enzymes can cleave that will produce an overhang or 'sticky end'.

Name: matrix_attachment_site
Definition: A DNA region that is required for the binding of chromatin to the nuclear matrix.

Name: direct_repeat
Definition: A repeat where the same sequence is repeated in the same direction. Example: GCTGA-followed by-GCTGA.

Name: adaptive_island
Definition: An adaptive island is a genomic island that provides an adaptive advantage to the host.

Name: mature_transcript_region
Definition: A region of a mature transcript.

Name: transcription_pause_site
Definition: Transcription pause sites are regions of a gene where RNA polymerase may pause during transcription. The functional role of pausing may be to facilitate factor recruitment	 RNA folding	 and synchronization with translation. Consensus transcription pause site have been observed in E. coli.

Name: noncoding_exon
Definition: An exon that does not contain any codons.

Name: chromosomal_transposition
Definition: A chromosome structure variant whereby a region of a chromosome has been transferred to another position. Among interchromosomal rearrangements	 the term transposition is reserved for that class in which the telomeres of the chromosomes involved are coupled (that is to say	 form the two ends of a single DNA molecule) as in wild-type.

Name: enhancer_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the enhancer region of a nucleotide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues.

Name: H3K4_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 4th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is di-methylated.

Name: transcribed_fragment
Definition: An experimental region	 defined by a tiling array experiment to be transcribed at some level.

Name: WC_base_pair
Definition: The canonical base pair	 where two bases interact via WC edges	 with glycosidic bonds oriented cis relative to the axis of orientation.

Name: ChIP_seq_region
Definition: A region of sequence identified by CHiP seq technology to contain a protein binding site.

Name: CuRE
Definition: A promoter element bound by copper ion-sensing transcription factors such as S. cerevisiae Mac1p or S. pombe Cuf1; the consensus sequence is HTHNNGCTGD (more specifically TTTGCKCR in budding yeast).

Name: modified_L_valine
Definition: A post translationally modified valine amino acid feature.

Name: dCAPS_primer
Definition: A primer with one or more mismatches to the DNA template corresponding to a position within a restriction enzyme recognition site.

Name: major_TSS
Definition: The tanscription start site that is most frequently used for transcription of a gene.

Name: G_to_A_transition
Definition: A transition of a guanine to an adenine.

Name: template_region
Definition: A region of a guide_RNA that specifies the insertions and deletions of bases in the editing of a target mRNA.

Name: modified_adenine
Definition: A modified adenine DNA base feature.

Name: mitochondrial_D_loop
Definition: Mitochondrial displacement loop; a region within mitochondrial DNA in which a short stretch of RNA is paired with one strand of DNA	 displacing the original partner DNA strand in this region.

Name: five_methylcytidine
Definition: 5-methylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: coding_start
Definition: The first base to be translated into protein.

Name: exemplar
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence is representative of a class of similar sequences.

Name: Penelope_retrotransposon
Definition: Penelope is a subclass of non_LTR_retrotransposons (SO:0000189). Penelope retrotransposons contains structural features of TR	 RT	 EN	 TR	 terminal repeats which can be in tandem or inverse orientation in different Penelope copies. RT is reverse transcriptase. EN is endonuclease.

Name: three_prime_LTR_component
Definition: A component of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: RNase_MRP_RNA
Definition: The RNA molecule essential for the catalytic activity of RNase MRP	 an enzymatically active ribonucleoprotein with two distinct roles in eukaryotes. In mitochondria it plays a direct role in the initiation of mitochondrial DNA replication. In the nucleus it is involved in precursor rRNA processing	 where it cleaves the internal transcribed spacer 1 between 18S and 5.8S rRNAs.

Name: seven_methylguanosine
Definition: 7_methylguanosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: attL_site
Definition: A region that results from recombination between attP_site and attB_site	 composed of the 5' portion of attB_site and the 3' portion of attP_site.

Name: archaeal_intron
Definition: An intron characteristic of Archaeal tRNA and rRNA genes	 where intron transcript generates a bulge-helix-bulge motif that is recognised by a splicing endoribonuclease.

Name: engineered_tag
Definition: A tag that is engineered.

Name: unigene_cluster
Definition: A kind of transcribed_cluster defined by a set of transcribed sequences from the a unique gene.

Name: macronuclear_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the macronuclei of ciliates.

Name: amino_acid
Definition: A sequence feature that corresponds to a single amino acid residue in a polypeptide.

Name: GC_rich_promoter_region
Definition: A conserved GC-rich region located upstream of the start point of eukaryotic transcription units which may occur in multiple copies or in either orientation; consensus=GGGCGG.

Name: mobile_element_deletion
Definition: A deletion of a mobile element when comparing a reference sequence (has mobile element) to a individual sequence (does not have mobile element).

Name: intrinsically_unstructured_polypeptide_region
Definition: A region of polypeptide chain with high conformational flexibility.

Name: synthetic_oligo
Definition: An oligo composed of synthetic nucleotides.

Name: transcription_unit
Definition: DNA regions delimited by different nonspurious TSS-TTS pairs.

Name: five_carbamoylmethyl_two_prime_O_methyluridine
Definition: 5_carbamoylmethyl_2_prime_O_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: U3_three_prime_LTR_region
Definition: The U3 segment of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: R_GNA_oligo
Definition: An oligo composed of (R)-GNA residues.

Name: dh_repeat
Definition: A repeat region which is part of the regional centromere outer repeat region.

Name: unconfirmed_transcript
Definition: This is used for non-spliced EST clusters that have polyA features. This category has been specifically created for the ENCODE project to highlight regions that could indicate the presence of protein coding genes that require experimental validation	 either by 5' RACE or RT-PCR to extend the transcripts	 or by confirming expression of the putatively-encoded peptide with specific antibodies.

Name: pyrrolysine
Definition: A relatively rare amino acid encoded by the codon UAG in some contexts	 whereas UAG is a termination codon in other contexts.

Name: internal_transcribed_spacer_region
Definition: Non-coding regions of DNA sequence that separate genes coding for the 28S	 5.8S	 and 18S ribosomal RNAs.

Name: target_site_duplication
Definition: A sequence of the target DNA that is duplicated when a transposable element or phage inserts; usually found at each end the insertion.

Name: CDS_supported_by_domain_match_data
Definition: A CDS that is supported by domain similarity.

Name: transcribed_processed_pseudogene
Definition: A processed_pseudogene overlapped by locus-specific evidence of transcription.

Name: open_chromatin_region
Definition: A DNA sequence that in the normal state of the chromosome corresponds to an unfolded	 un-complexed stretch of double-stranded DNA.

Name: centromere_DNA_Element_III
Definition: A centromere DNA Element I (CDEI) is a conserved region	 part of the centromere	 consisting of a consensus region that consists of a 25-bp which enables binding by the centromere DNA binding factor 3 (CBF3) complex.

Name: Ngaro_YR_retrotransposon
Definition: Ngaro retrotransposons are members of the YR_retrotransposon (SO:0002286) superfamily with the following protein domains: RT	 RH	 YR. RT is a reverse transcriptase. RH is RNAse H. YR is Tyrosine recombinase. Inverted terminal repeats (ITRs) in Ngaro are arranged in A-pol-B-A-B order where A and B represent ITRs.

Name: polypeptide_conserved_motif
Definition: A conserved motif is a short (up to 20 amino acids) region of biological interest that is conserved in different proteins. They may or may not have functional or structural significance within the proteins in which they are found.

Name: right_handed_peptide_helix
Definition: A right handed helix is a region of peptide where the coiled conformation turns in a clockwise	 right handed screw.

Name: junction
Definition: A sequence_feature with an extent of zero.

Name: SP6_RNA_Polymerase_Promoter
Definition: A region (DNA) to which the SP6 RNA polymerase binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: vertebrate_immune_system_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene derived from a vertebrate immune system gene.

Name: telomeric_transcript
Definition: A non-coding transcript derived from the transcript of the telomere.

Name: five_prime_open_reading_frame
Definition: An open reading frame found within the 5' UTR that can be translated and stall the translation of the downstream open reading frame.

Name: non_adjacent_residues
Definition: Indicates that two consecutive residues in a fragment sequence are not consecutive in the full-length protein and that there are a number of unsequenced residues between them.

Name: shRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding an shRNA.

Name: cloned_genomic_insert
Definition: A clone insert made from genomic DNA.

Name: polypeptide_nest_right_left_motif
Definition: A motif of two consecutive residues with dihedral angles: Residue(i): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees. Residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees	 -40 degrees < psi < +90 degrees.

Name: point_centromere
Definition: A point centromere is a relatively small centromere (about 125 bp DNA) in discrete sequence	 found in some yeast including S. cerevisiae.

Name: DCE_SI
Definition: A sub element of the DCE core promoter element	 with consensus sequence CTTC.

Name: meiotic_recombination_region
Definition: A genomic region in which there is an exchange of genetic material as a result of the repair of meiosis-specific double strand breaks that occur during meiotic prophase.

Name: capped_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA that is capped.

Name: H4K8_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 8th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: gene_with_dicistronic_mRNA
Definition: A gene that encodes a polycistronic mRNA.

Name: circular
Definition: A quality of a nucleotide polymer that has no terminal nucleotide residues.

Name: wild_type
Definition: An attribute describing sequence with the genotype found in nature and/or standard laboratory stock.

Name: rescue_region
Definition: A region that rescues.

Name: dif_site
Definition: A site at which replicated bacterial circular chromosomes are decatenated by site specific resolvase.

Name: SL12_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL12 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL12 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: methionine
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codon ATG.

Name: chromosome_part
Definition: A region of a chromosome.

Name: DRE
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence CGWGGWNGMM	 bound by transcription factors related to RecA and found in promoters of genes expressed following several types of DNA damage or inhibition of DNA synthesis.

Name: rRNA_23S
Definition: A large polynucleotide in Bacteria and Archaea	 which functions as the large subunit of the ribosome.

Name: intramembrane_polypeptide_region
Definition: Polypeptide region present in the lipid bilayer.

Name: rRNA_5_8S
Definition: 5_8S ribosomal RNA (5.8S rRNA) is a component of the large subunit of the eukaryotic ribosome. It is transcribed by RNA polymerase I as part of the 45S precursor that also contains 18S and 28S rRNA. Functionally	 it is thought that 5.8S rRNA may be involved in ribosome translocation. It is also known to form covalent linkage to the p53 tumour suppressor protein.

Name: H2AZK7_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 7th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2AZ histone protein is acetylated.

Name: ct_gene
Definition: A gene from chloroplast sequence.

Name: knob
Definition: Cytologically observable heterochromatic regions of chromosomes away from centromeres that contain predominatly large tandem repeats and retrotransposons.

Name: assortment_derived_variation
Definition: A chromosome variation derived from an event during meiosis.

Name: promoter_flanking_region
Definition: A region immediately adjacent to a promoter which may or may not contain transcription factor binding sites.

Name: mitochondrial_targeting_signal
Definition: A polypeptide region that targets a polypeptide to the mitochondrion.

Name: transcription_end_site
Definition: The base where transcription ends.

Name: small_subunit_rRNA
Definition: Ribosomal RNA transcript that structures the small subunit of the ribosome.

Name: chromosomal_structural_element
Definition: Regions of the chromosome that are important for structural elements.

Name: polypeptide_tungsten_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with tungsten ions.

Name: C_to_G_transversion
Definition: A transversion of a cytidine to a guanine.

Name: TERRA
Definition: A non-coding RNA transcript	 derived from the transcription of the telomere. These  transcripts contain G rich telomeric RNA repeats and RNA tracts corresponding to adjacent subtelomeric sequences. They are 100-9000 bases long.

Name: monomeric_repeat
Definition: A repeat_region containing repeat_units of 1 bp that is repeated multiple times in tandem.

Name: terminal_repeat
Definition: A repeat at the ends of and within the sequence for which it has functional significance other than long terminal repeat.

Name: ARS_consensus_sequence
Definition: The ACS is an 11-bp sequence of the form 5'-WTTTAYRTTTW-3' which is at the core of every yeast ARS	 and is necessary but not sufficient for recognition and binding by the origin recognition complex (ORC). Functional ARSs require an ACS	 as well as other cis elements in the 5' (C domain) and 3' (B domain) flanking sequences of the ACS.

Name: gene_with_start_codon_CUG
Definition: A gene with a translational start codon of CUG.

Name: H4K_acylation_region
Definition: A region of the H4 histone whereby multiple lysines are acylated.

Name: N4_methylcytidine
Definition: N4-methylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: gene_group
Definition: A collection of related genes.

Name: phosphorylation_site
Definition: A post-translationally modified region in which residues of the protein are modified by phosphorylation.

Name: Shine_Dalgarno_sequence
Definition: A region in the 5' UTR that pairs with the 16S rRNA during formation of the preinitiation complex.

Name: siRNA
Definition: A small RNA molecule that is the product of a longer exogenous or endogenous dsRNA	 which is either a bimolecular duplex or very long hairpin	 processed (via the Dicer pathway) such that numerous siRNAs accumulate from both strands of the dsRNA. SRNAs trigger the cleavage of their target molecules.

Name: macronuclear_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in a macronucleus.

Name: single
Definition: When a nucleotide polymer has only one strand.

Name: DNA_loop_anchor
Definition: The ends of a DNA loop where the two strands of DNA are held in close physical proximity. During interphase the anchors of DNA loops are convergently oriented CTCF binding sites.

Name: L1_LINE_retrotransposon
Definition: Long interspersed element-1 (LINE-1) elements are found in the human genome	 which contains ORF1 (open reading frame1	 including CC	 coiled coil; RRM	 RNA recognition motif; CTD	 carboxyl-terminal domain) and ORF2 (including EN	 endonuclease; RT	 reverse transcriptase; C	 cysteine-rich domain). The L1-encoded proteins (ORF1p and ORF2p) can mobilize nonautonomous retrotransposons	 other noncoding RNAs	 and messenger RNAs.

Name: paternal_uniparental_disomy
Definition: Uniparental disomy is a sequence_alteration where a diploid individual receives two copies for all or part of a chromosome from the father and no copies of the same chromosome or region from the mother.

Name: inversion_derived_deficiency_plus_duplication
Definition: A chromosome deletion whereby a chromosome is generated by recombination between two inversions; there is a deficiency at one end of the inversion and a duplication at the other end of the inversion.

Name: ds_RNA_viral_sequence
Definition: A ds_RNA_viral_sequence is a viral_sequence that is the sequence of a virus that exists as double stranded RNA.

Name: SL5_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL5 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL5 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: RNApol_II_core_promoter
Definition: The minimal portion of the promoter required to properly initiate transcription in RNA polymerase II transcribed genes.

Name: unitary_pseudogenic_tRNA
Definition: The pseudogene has no parent. It is the original gene	 which is functional in some species but disrupted in some way (indels	 mutation	 recombination) in another species or strain.

Name: epoxyqueuosine
Definition: Epoxyqueuosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: translationally_frameshifted
Definition: Recoding by frameshifting a particular site.

Name: validated_cDNA_clone
Definition: A cDNA clone that has been validated.

Name: maternally_imprinted_gene
Definition: A gene that is maternally_imprinted.

Name: repeat_unit
Definition: The simplest repeated component of a repeat region. A single repeat.

Name: aspartyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has an aspartic acid anticodon	 and a 3' aspartic acid binding region.

Name: insertion_attribute
Definition: A quality of a chromosomal insertion	.

Name: membrane_peptide_loop
Definition: Polypeptide region localized within the lipid bilayer where both ends traverse the same membrane.

Name: SNP
Definition: SNPs are single base pair positions in genomic DNA at which different sequence alternatives exist in normal individuals in some population(s)	 wherein the least frequent variant has an abundance of 1% or greater.

Name: N_region
Definition: Extra nucleotides inserted between rearranged immunoglobulin segments.

Name: TNA
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases attached to a repeating unit made of threose rings connected to a phosphate backbone.

Name: five_prime_EST
Definition: An EST read from the 5' end of a transcript that usually codes for a protein. These regions tend to be conserved across species and do not change much within a gene family.

Name: mitotic_recombination_region
Definition: A genomic region where there is an exchange of genetic material with another genomic region	 occurring in somatic cells.

Name: regulatory_region
Definition: A region of sequence that is involved in the control of a biological process.

Name: positive_sense_ssRNA_viral_sequence
Definition: A positive_sense_RNA_viral_sequence is a ss_RNA_viral_sequence that is the sequence of a single stranded RNA virus that can be immediately translated by the host.

Name: epigenetically_modified
Definition: This attribute describes a gene where heritable changes other than those in the DNA sequence occur. These changes include: modification to the DNA (such as DNA methylation	 the covalent modification of cytosine)	 and post-translational modification of histones.

Name: pre_miRNA
Definition: The 60-70 nucleotide region remain after Drosha processing of the primary transcript	 that folds back upon itself to form a hairpin structure.

Name: five_formylcytidine
Definition: 5-formylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: homologous_region
Definition: A region that is homologous to another region.

Name: G_to_T_transversion
Definition: A transversion from guanine to thymine.

Name: trans_splice_donor_site
Definition: The 5' five prime splice site region of the donor RNA.

Name: complex_structural_alteration
Definition: A structural sequence alteration or rearrangement encompassing one or more genome fragments	 with 4 or more breakpoints.

Name: beta_bulge
Definition: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet in which the main chains of two consecutive residues are H-bonded to that of the third	 and in which the dihedral angles are as follows: Residue(i): -140 degrees < phi(l) -20 degrees 	 -90 degrees < psi(l) < 40 degrees. Residue (i+1): -180 degrees < phi < -25 degrees or +120 degrees < phi < +180 degrees	 +40 degrees < psi < +180 degrees or -180 degrees < psi < -120 degrees.

Name: elongated_out_of_frame_polypeptide_C_terminal
Definition: A sequence variant with in the CDS that causes out of frame elongation of the resulting polypeptide sequence at the C terminus.

Name: five_prime_clip
Definition: 5' most region of a precursor transcript that is clipped off during processing.

Name: simple_operon
Definition: An operon whose transcription is coordinated on a single transcription unit.

Name: U4_snRNA
Definition: U4 small nuclear RNA (U4 snRNA) is a component of the major U2-dependent spliceosome. It forms a duplex with U6	 and with each splicing round	 it is displaced from U6 (and the spliceosome) in an ATP-dependent manner	 allowing U6 to refold and create the active site for splicing catalysis. A recycling process involving protein Prp24 re-anneals U4 and U6.

Name: signature
Definition: A region of  sequence where developer information is encoded.

Name: rRNA_25S
Definition: A large polynucleotide which functions as part of the large subunit of the ribosome in some eukaryotes.

Name: terminator_of_type_2_RNApol_III_promoter
Definition: A terminator signal for RNA polymerase III transcription.

Name: homologous
Definition: Similarity due to common ancestry.

Name: mutational_hotspot
Definition: A region of genomic sequence known to undergo mutational events with greater frequency than expected by chance.

Name: hammerhead_ribozyme
Definition: A small catalytic RNA motif that catalyzes self-cleavage reaction. Its name comes from its secondary structure which resembles a carpenter's hammer. The hammerhead ribozyme is involved in the replication of some viroid and some satellite RNAs.

Name: read_pair
Definition: One of a pair of sequencing reads in which the two members of the pair are related by originating at either end of a clone insert.

Name: translated_nucleotide_match
Definition: A match against a translated sequence.

Name: polypeptide_binding_motif
Definition: A polypeptide binding motif is a short (up to 20 amino acids) polypeptide region of biological interest that contains one or more amino acids experimentally shown to bind to a ligand.

Name: T3_RNA_Polymerase_Promoter
Definition: A DNA sequence to which the T3 RNA polymerase binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: three_prime_UTR_intron
Definition: An intron located in the 3' UTR.

Name: modified_RNA_base_feature
Definition: A post_transcriptionally modified base.

Name: start_codon
Definition: First codon to be translated by a ribosome.

Name: U5_five_prime_LTR_region
Definition: The U5 segment of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: polypeptide_ligand_contact
Definition: Residues which interact with a ligand.

Name: four_bp_start_codon
Definition: A non-canonical start codon with 4 base pairs.

Name: mitochondrial_DNA
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a mitochondria.

Name: tmRNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a transfer-messenger RNA (tmRNA).

Name: five_methyl_2_thiouridine
Definition: 5_methyl_2_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: modified_adenosine
Definition: A modified adenine is an adenine base feature that has been altered.

Name: Alu_deletion
Definition: A deletion of an Alu mobile element with respect to a reference.

Name: repeat_fragment
Definition: A portion of a repeat	 interrupted by the insertion of another element.

Name: three_methyluridine
Definition: 3_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: contig_collection
Definition: A collection of contigs.

Name: selenocysteine
Definition: A relatively rare amino acid encoded by the codon UGA in some contexts	 whereas UGA is a termination codon in other contexts.

Name: miR_encoding_vaultRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A vaultRNA primary transcript that also encodes pre-miR sequence that is processed to form functionally active miRNA.

Name: five_hydroxymethylcytidine
Definition: 5-hydroxymethylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: branch_site
Definition: A pyrimidine rich sequence near the 3' end of an intron to which the 5'end becomes covalently bound during nuclear splicing. The resulting structure resembles a lariat.

Name: mitochondrial_supercontig
Definition: A scaffold composed of mitochondrial contigs.

Name: serine
Definition: A polar	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons TCN (TCT	 TCC	 TCA	 TCG)	 AGT and AGC.

Name: HSE
Definition: A promoter element that consists of at least three copies of the pentanucleotide NGAAN	 bound by the heat shock transcription factor HSF.

Name: minicircle
Definition: A minicircle is a replicon	 part of a kinetoplast	 that encodes for guide RNAs.

Name: translational_frameshift
Definition: The region of mRNA (not divisible by 3 bases) that is skipped or added during the process of translational frameshifting (GO:0006452)	 causing the reading frame to be different.

Name: cleaved_for_gpi_anchor_region
Definition: The C-terminal residues of a polypeptide which are exchanged for a GPI-anchor.

Name: five_prime_sticky_end_restriction_enzyme_cleavage_site
Definition: A restriction enzyme recognition site that	 when cleaved	 results in 5 prime overhangs.

Name: heptamer_of_recombination_feature_of_vertebrate_immune_system_gene
Definition: Seven nucleotide recombination site (e.g. CACAGTG)	 part of V-gene	 D-gene or J-gene recombination feature of an immunoglobulin or T-cell receptor gene.

Name: miR_encoding_Y_RNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A Y-RNA primary transcript that also encodes pre-miR sequence that is processed to form functionally active miRNA.

Name: N6_methyladenosine
Definition: N6_methyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: rRNA_25S_gene
Definition: A gene which codes for 25S_rRNA	 which functions as a component of the large subunit of the ribosome in some eukaryotes.

Name: RFLP_fragment
Definition: A DNA fragment used as a reagent to detect the polymorphic genomic loci by hybridizing against the genomic DNA digested with a given restriction enzyme.

Name: DMv3_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 usually located between -30 and +15 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is KNNCAKCNCTRNY. Tends to co-occur with DMv2 (SO:0001161). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or MTE (0001162).

Name: RNase_P_RNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes an RNase P RNA.

Name: trinucleotide_repeat_microsatellite_feature
Definition: A region of a repeating trinucleotide sequence (three bases).

Name: archaeosine
Definition: Archaeosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: expressed_sequence_assembly
Definition: A sequence assembly derived from expressed sequences.

Name: modified_L_tryptophan
Definition: A post translationally modified tryptophan amino acid feature.

Name: Hoogsteen_base_pair
Definition: A type of non-canonical base-pairing. This is less energetically favourable than watson crick base pairing. Hoogsteen GC base pairs only have two hydrogen bonds.

Name: H3K27_trimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 27th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is tri-methylated.

Name: Ace2_UAS
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence CCAGCC	 bound by the fungal transcription factor Ace2.

Name: fragmentary
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that is incomplete.

Name: gamma_turn
Definition: Gamma turns	 defined for 3 residues i	( i+1)	( i+2) if a hydrogen bond exists between residues i and i+2 and the phi and psi angles of residue i+1 fall within 40 degrees.

Name: non_canonical_five_prime_splice_site
Definition: A 5' splice site which does not have the sequence "GT".

Name: L_box
Definition: An orientation dependent  regulatory promoter element	 with consensus sequence of TTGCACAN4TTGCACA	 found in plants.

Name: TFRS_module
Definition: The possible discontinuous stretch of DNA that is the combination of one or several TFRSs whose bound TFs work jointly in the regulation of a promoter.

Name: three_three_amino_three_carboxypropyl_uridine
Definition: 3_3_amino_3_carboxypropyl_uridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: mobile_genetic_element
Definition: A nucleotide region with either intra-genome or intracellular mobility	 of varying length	 which often carry the information necessary for transfer and recombination with the host genome.

Name: haplotype_block
Definition: A region of the genome which is co-inherited as the result of the lack of historic recombination within it.

Name: nested_transposon
Definition: A transposon that is disrupted by the insertion of another element.

Name: transcribed_cluster
Definition: A region defined by a set of transcribed sequences from the same gene or expressed pseudogene.

Name: leucoplast_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome with origin in a leucoplast.

Name: chromosome_breakage_sequence
Definition: A sequence within the micronuclear DNA of ciliates at which chromosome breakage and telomere addition occurs during nuclear differentiation.

Name: silenced_by_histone_methylation
Definition: An attribute describing an epigenetic process where a gene is inactivated by histone methylation.

Name: SECIS_element
Definition: The incorporation of selenocysteine into a protein sequence is directed by an in-frame UGA codon (usually a stop codon) within the coding region of the mRNA. Selenoprotein mRNAs contain a conserved secondary structure in the 3' UTR that is required for the distinction of UGA stop from UGA selenocysteine. The selenocysteine insertion sequence (SECIS) is around 60 nt in length and adopts a hairpin structure which is sufficiently well-defined and conserved to act as a computational screen for selenoprotein genes.

Name: cryptic_splice_site
Definition: A splice site that is in part of the transcript not normally spliced. They occur via mutation or transcriptional error.

Name: BAC_end
Definition: A region of sequence from the end of a BAC clone that may provide a highly specific marker.

Name: forward_primer
Definition: A single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction.

Name: frameshift
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that contains a mutation involving the deletion or insertion of one or more bases	 where this number is not divisible by 3.

Name: mRNA_attribute
Definition: An attribute describing an mRNA feature.

Name: assembly
Definition: A region of the genome of known length that is composed by ordering and aligning two or more different regions.

Name: three_prime_RACE_clone
Definition: A three prime RACE (Rapid Amplification of cDNA Ends) clone is a cDNA clone copied from the 3' end of an mRNA (using a poly-dT primer to capture the polyA tail and a gene-specific or randomly primed 5' primer)	 and spliced into a vector for propagation in a suitable host.

Name: beta_turn_type_six
Definition: A motif of four consecutive peptide resides of type VIa or type VIb and where the i+2 residue is cis-proline.

Name: natural_variant_site
Definition: Describes the natural sequence variants due to polymorphisms	 disease-associated mutations	 RNA editing and variations between strains	 isolates or cultivars.

Name: tetranucleotide_repeat_microsatellite_feature
Definition: A region of a repeating tetranucleotide sequence (four bases).

Name: N2_methylguanosine
Definition: N2_methylguanosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: genome
Definition: A genome is the sum of genetic material within a cell or virion.

Name: H4R3_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 3nd residue (an arginine)	 from the start of the H4 protein is di-methylated.

Name: no_sequence_alteration
Definition: A position or feature within a sequence that is identical to the comparable position or feature of a specified reference sequence.

Name: V_nonamer
Definition: 9 nucleotide recombination site (e.g. ACAAAAACC)	 part of V-gene recombination feature of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: proviral_region
Definition: A viral sequence which has integrated into a host genome.

Name: TATA_box
Definition: A conserved AT-rich septamer found about 25-bp before the start point of many eukaryotic RNA polymerase II transcript units; may be involved in positioning the enzyme for correct initiation; consensus=TATA(A|T)A(A|T).

Name: X_region
Definition: One of two segments of homology found at all three mating loci (HML	 MAT and HMR).

Name: propeptide
Definition: Part of a peptide chain which is cleaved off during the formation of the mature protein.

Name: DIRS_YR_retrotransposon
Definition: Dictyostelium intermediate repeat sequence (DIRS) retrotransposons are members of the YR_retrotransposon (SO:0002286) superfamily with the following protein domains: RT	 RH	 YR	 and MT. RT is a reverse transcriptase. RH is RNAse H. YR is tyrosine recombinase. MT is DNA N-6-adenine-methyltransferase.

Name: self_cleaving_ribozyme
Definition: An RNA that catalyzes its own cleavage.

Name: piRNA
Definition: A small non coding RNA	 part of a silencing system that prevents the spreading of selfish genetic elements.

Name: five_carboxyhydroxymethyl_uridine
Definition: 5_carboxyhydroxymethyl_uridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: snRNA
Definition: A small nuclear RNA molecule involved in pre-mRNA splicing and processing.

Name: spot_42_RNA
Definition: A 109-nucleotide RNA of E. coli that seems to have a regulatory role on the galactose operon. Changes in Spot 42 levels are implicated in affecting DNA polymerase I levels.

Name: VJ_gene_segment
Definition: Rearranged genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene including L-part1	 V-intron and V-J-exon	 with the 5'UTR (SO:0000204) and 3'UTR (SO:0000205).

Name: transversion
Definition: Change of a pyrimidine nucleotide	 C or T	 into a purine nucleotide	 A or G	 or vice versa.

Name: R_three_prime_LTR_region
Definition: The R segment of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: autoregulated
Definition: The gene product is involved in its own transcriptional regulation.

Name: polyA_site_cluster
Definition: A region defined by a cluster of experimentally determined polyadenylation sites	 typically less than 25 bp in length and associated with a single polyadenylation signal.

Name: D_gene_segment
Definition: Germline genomic DNA including D-region with 5' UTR and 3' UTR	 also designated as D-segment.

Name: sequence_alteration
Definition: A sequence_alteration is a sequence_feature whose extent is the deviation from another sequence.

Name: proviral_location
Definition: The location of DNA that has come from a viral origin.

Name: retinoic_acid_responsive_element
Definition: A transcription factor binding site of variable direct repeats of the sequence PuGGTCA spaced by five nucleotides (DR5) found in the promoters of retinoic acid-responsive genes	 to which retinoic acid receptors bind.

Name: rescue_mini_gene
Definition: A mini_gene that rescues.

Name: translated_unprocessed_pseudogene
Definition: A non-processed pseudogene where there is evidence	 (mass spec data) suggesting that it is also translated.

Name: coding_conserved_region
Definition: Coding region of sequence similarity by descent from a common ancestor.
