Name: engineered_plasmid
Definition: A plasmid that is engineered.

Name: outron
Definition: A region of a primary transcript	 that is removed via trans splicing.

Name: PAC_end
Definition: A region of sequence from the end of a PAC clone that may provide a highly specific marker.

Name: compositionally_biased_region_of_peptide
Definition: Polypeptide region that is rich in a particular amino acid or homopolymeric and greater than three residues in length.

Name: linear
Definition: A quality of a nucleotide polymer that has a 3'-terminal residue and a 5'-terminal residue.

Name: peptide_helix
Definition: A helix is a secondary_structure conformation where the peptide backbone forms a coil.

Name: non_LTR_retrotransposon_polymeric_tract
Definition: A polymeric tract	 such as poly(dA)	 within a non_LTR_retrotransposon.

Name: feature_attribute
Definition: An attribute describing a located_sequence_feature.

Name: kinetoplast
Definition: A kinetoplast is an interlocked network of thousands of minicircles and tens of maxicircles	 located near the base of the flagellum of some protozoan species.

Name: insertion_artifact
Definition: An insertion that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: reading_frame
Definition: A nucleic acid sequence that when read as sequential triplets	 has the potential of encoding a sequential string of amino acids. It need not contain the start or stop codon.

Name: V_gene_segment
Definition: Germline genomic DNA including L-part1	 V-intron and V-exon	 with the 5' UTR and 3' UTR.

Name: anti_ARRET
Definition: A non-coding RNA transcript	 derived from the transcription of the telomere. These  transcripts are antisense of ARRET transcripts.

Name: intein_encoding_region
Definition: The nucleotide sequence which encodes the intein portion of the precursor gene.

Name: engineered_transposable_element
Definition: TE that has been modified by manipulations in vitro.

Name: rRNA_primary_transcript_region
Definition: A region of an rRNA primary transcript.

Name: leucoplast_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a leucoplast	 a colorless plastid generally containing starch or oil.

Name: attC_site
Definition: An attC site is a sequence required for the integration of a DNA of an integron.

Name: regulatory_promoter_element
Definition: A promoter element that is not part of the core promoter	 but provides the promoter with a specific regulatory region.

Name: miRNA_primary_transcript_region
Definition: A part of an miRNA primary_transcript.

Name: coding_region_of_exon
Definition: The region of an exon that encodes for protein sequence.

Name: intermediate_element
Definition: A core promoter region of RNA polymerase III type 1 promoters.

Name: post_translationally_regulated_gene
Definition: A gene that is post translationally regulated.

Name: NSD_transcript
Definition: A transcript that contains a CDS but has no stop codon before the polyA site is reached.

Name: four_demethylwyosine
Definition: 4_demethylwyosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: sequence_collection
Definition: A collection of discontinuous sequences.

Name: c_terminal_region
Definition: The more polar	 carboxy-terminal region of the signal peptide (approx 3-7 aa).

Name: Robertsonian_fusion
Definition: A non reciprocal translocation whereby the participating chromosomes break at their centromeres and the long arms fuse to form a single chromosome with a single centromere.

Name: CAAX_box
Definition: A C-terminus protein motif (CAAX) serving as a post-translational prenylation site modified by the attachment of either a farnesyl or a geranyl-geranyl group to a cysteine residue. Farnesyltransferase recognizes CaaX boxes where X = M	 S	 Q	 A	 or C	 whereas Geranylgeranyltransferase I recognizes CaaX boxes with X = L or E.

Name: SINE_element
Definition: A repetitive element	 a few hundred base pairs long	 that is dispersed throughout the genome. A common human SINE is the Alu element.

Name: orphan
Definition: A gene whose predicted amino acid sequence is unsupported by any experimental evidence or by any match with any other known sequence.

Name: GcvB_RNA
Definition: A small untranslated RNA involved in expression of the dipeptide and oligopeptide transport systems in Escherichia coli.

Name: non_processed_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene that arose from a means other than retrotransposition. A pseudogene created via genomic duplication of a functional protein-coding parent gene followed by accumulation of deleterious mutations.

Name: asx_turn_right_handed_type_one
Definition: Right handed type I (dihedral angles):- Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi (1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi +120 degrees < +40 degrees. Residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees.

Name: oriV
Definition: An origin of vegetative replication in plasmids and phages.

Name: nucleotide_match
Definition: A match against a nucleotide sequence.

Name: U11_snRNA
Definition: U11 snRNA plays a role in splicing of the minor U12-dependent class of eukaryotic nuclear introns	 similar to U1 snRNA in the major class spliceosome it base pairs to the conserved 5' splice site sequence.

Name: 5_carboxylcytosine
Definition: A modified DNA cytosine base feature	 modified by a carboxy group at the 5 carbon.

Name: Retrovirus_LTR_retrotransposon
Definition: LTR retrotransposons in the retrovirus superfamily are similar to LTR retrotransposons in the Gypsy and Bel-Pao superfamilies. Mainly described in vertebrate animals	 this superfamily contain elements coding for specific proteins in this order: GAG	 AP	 RT	 RH	 INT	 and ENV. GAG is a structural protein for virus-like particles. AP is aspartic proteinase. INT is a DDE integrase. RT is a reverse transcriptase. RH is RNAse H. ENV is envelop protein.

Name: modified_guanosine
Definition: A guanosine base that has been modified.

Name: five_aminomethyl_two_thiouridine
Definition: 5_aminomethyl_2_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: rearranged_at_DNA_level
Definition: An attribute to describe the sequence of a feature	 where the DNA is rearranged.

Name: origin_of_replication
Definition: A region of nucleic acid from which replication initiates; includes sequences that are recognized by replication proteins	 the site from which the first separation of complementary strands occurs	 and specific replication start sites.

Name: polypeptide_nest_left_right_motif
Definition: A motif of two consecutive residues with dihedral angles: Residue(i): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees	 -40 degrees < psi < +90 degrees. Residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees.

Name: interband
Definition: A light region between two darkly staining bands in a polytene chromosome.

Name: 5_methylcytosine
Definition: A cytosine methylated at the 5 carbon.

Name: glutamic_acid_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding glutaminyl tRNA (SO:0000260).

Name: five_prime_UTR
Definition: A region at the 5' end of a mature transcript (preceding the initiation codon) that is not translated into a protein.

Name: intronic_splicing_silencer
Definition: An intronic  splicing regulatory element that functions to recruit trans acting splicing factors suppress the transcription of the gene or genes they control.

Name: five_prime_D_spacer
Definition: 12 or 23 nucleotide spacer between the 5' D-heptamer (SO:0000496) and 5' D-nonamer (SO:0000497) of a 5' D-recombination signal sequence (SO:0000556) of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: peroxywybutosine
Definition: Peroxywybutosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: Alu_insertion
Definition: An insertion of sequence from the Alu family of mobile elements.

Name: clip
Definition: Part of the primary transcript that is clipped off during processing.

Name: RNase_MRP_RNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes a RNase_MRP_RNA.

Name: five_prime_recoding_site
Definition: The recoding stimulatory signal located upstream of the recoding site.

Name: H3K79_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 79th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is di-methylated.

Name: five_isopentenylaminomethyl_two_thiouridine
Definition: 5_isopentenylaminomethyl_2_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: core_eukaryotic_promoter_element
Definition: An element that only exists within the promoter region of a eukaryotic gene.

Name: PIF_Harbinger_TIR_transposon
Definition: Terminal inverted repeat transposons in the PIF/Harbinger/tourist superfamily create 3-bp target site duplication that are mainly 'TAA' or 'TTA'. The autonomous PIF-Harbinger elements are relatively small in size	 usually a few kb in length. Non-autonomous elements in this superfamily usually shorter than 600 bp are referrred to as Tourist elements. The terminal sequences for PIF/Harbinger/Tourist elements are 'GGG/CCCb&GGC/GCC' or 'GA/GGCAb&TGCC/TC'.

Name: blunt_end_restriction_enzyme_cleavage_junction
Definition: A restriction enzyme cleavage site where both strands are cut at the same position.

Name: H3K79_methylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 79th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is methylated.

Name: SRP_RNA_gene
Definition: A noncoding RNA that binds to the ribosome to halt protein synthesis when the signal peptide is present.

Name: propeptide_region_of_CDS
Definition: A CDS region corresponding to a propeptide of a polypeptide.

Name: homol_D_box
Definition: A core promoter element that has the consensus sequence CAGTCACA (or its inverted form TGTGACTG)	 and plays the role of a TATA box in promoters that do not contain a canonical TATA sequence.

Name: two_prime_O_methylpseudouridine
Definition: 2prime_O_methylpseudouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: beta_turn_type_six_b
Definition: A motif of four consecutive peptide residues	 of which the i+2 residue is proline	 and that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth and is characterized by the dihedral angles: Residue(i+1): phi ~ -120 degrees	 psi ~ 120 degrees. Residue(i+2): phi ~ -60 degrees	 psi ~ 0 degrees.

Name: point_mutation
Definition: A single nucleotide change which has occurred at the same position of a corresponding nucleotide in a reference sequence.

Name: isoleucine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding isoleucyl tRNA (SO:0000263).

Name: selenocysteine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding seryl tRNA (SO:000269).

Name: variant_collection
Definition: A collection of one or more sequences of an individual.

Name: serine_threonine_motif
Definition: A motif of five consecutive residues and two hydrogen bonds in which: residue(i) is Serine (S) or Threonine (T)	 the side-chain O of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+2) or (i+3) 	 the main-chain CO group of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+3) or (i+4).

Name: STS_map
Definition: An STS map is a physical map organized by the unique STS landmarks.

Name: RNA_6S
Definition: A small (184-nt in E. coli) RNA that forms a hairpin type structure. 6S RNA associates with RNA polymerase in a highly specific manner. 6S RNA represses expression from a sigma70-dependent promoter during stationary phase.

Name: paired_end_fragment
Definition: An assembly region that has been sequenced from both ends resulting in a read_pair (mate_pair).

Name: H3K9_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 9th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein may be dimethylated.

Name: interchromosomal_transposition
Definition: A chromosome structure variation whereby a transposition occurred between chromosomes.

Name: ss_RNA_viral_sequence
Definition: A ss_RNA_viral_sequence is a viral_sequence that is the sequence of a virus that exists as single stranded RNA.

Name: VDJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one VDJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: DMv5_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 usually located between -50 and -10 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is KTYRGTATWTTT. Tends to co-occur with DMv4 (SO:0001157) . Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or MTE (SO:0001162).

Name: laevosynaptic_chromosome
Definition: LS is an autosynaptic chromosome carrying the two left (L = levo) telomeres.

Name: beta_turn_left_handed_type_two
Definition: Left handed type II: A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. It is characterized by the dihedral angles: Residue(i+1): -140 degrees > phi > -20 degrees	 +80 degrees > psi > +180 degrees. Residue(i+2): +20 degrees > phi > +140 degrees	 -40 degrees > psi > +90 degrees.

Name: smFISH_probe
Definition: A smFISH is a probe that binds RNA in a single molecule in situ hybridization experiment.

Name: flanking_region
Definition: The sequences extending on either side of a specific region.

Name: bacterial_RNApol_promoter_sigma_70_element
Definition: A DNA sequence to which bacterial RNA polymerase sigma 70 binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: AU_rich_element
Definition: A cis-acting element found in the 3' UTR of some mRNA which is rich in AUUUA pentamers. Messenger RNAs bearing multiple AU-rich elements are often unstable.

Name: nucleotide_cleavage_site
Definition: A point in nucleic acid where a cleavage event occurs.

Name: CDS_five_prime_extension
Definition: A sequence variant extending the CDS at the 5' end	 that causes elongation of the resulting polypeptide sequence at the N terminus.

Name: modified_L_tyrosine
Definition: A post translationally modified tyrosine amino acid feature.

Name: long_terminal_repeat
Definition: A sequence directly repeated at both ends of a defined sequence	 of the sort typically found in retroviruses.

Name: two_prime_O_methyladenosine
Definition: 2prime_O_methyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: miRNA_target_site
Definition: A miRNA target site is a binding site where the molecule is a micro RNA.

Name: circular_plasmid
Definition: A self replicating circular nucleic acid molecule that is distinct from a chromosome in the organism.

Name: repeat_instability_region
Definition: A repeat region that is prone to expansions and/or contractions.

Name: tRNA_region
Definition: A region of a tRNA.

Name: positively_autoregulated_gene
Definition: A gene that is positively autoregulated.

Name: Y_region
Definition: A segment of non-homology between a and alpha mating alleles	 found at all three mating loci (HML	 MAT	 and HMR)	 has two forms (Ya and Yalpha).

Name: DNaseI_hypersensitive_site
Definition: DNA region representing open chromatin structure that is hypersensitive to digestion by DNase I.

Name: three_methylpseudouridine
Definition: 3_methylpseudouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: polymorphic_pseudogene_with_retained_intron
Definition: A polymorphic  pseudogene in the reference genome	 containing a retained intron	  known to be intact in the genomes of other individuals of the same species. The annotation process has confirmed that the pseudogenisation event is not a genomic sequencing error.

Name: epitope
Definition: A binding site that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with antibodies	 B cells or T cells.

Name: peptide_collection
Definition: A collection of peptide sequences.

Name: CDS_predicted
Definition: A CDS that is predicted.

Name: defective_conjugative_transposon
Definition: An island that contains genes for integration/excision and the gene and site for the initiation of intercellular transfer by conjugation. It can be complemented for transfer by a conjugative transposon.

Name: natural
Definition: An attribute describing a feature that occurs in nature.

Name: NMD_polymorphic_pseudogene_transcript
Definition: A polymorphic pseudogene transcript that contains a CDS but has one or more splice junctions >50bp downstream of stop codon. Premature stop codon is not introduced	 directly or indirectly	 as a result of the variation i.e. must be present in both protein_coding and pseudogenic alleles.

Name: three_prime_coding_exon_noncoding_region
Definition: The sequence of the 3' exon that is not coding.

Name: tmRNA
Definition: A tmRNA liberates a mRNA from a stalled ribosome. To accomplish this part of the tmRNA is used as a reading frame that ends in a translation stop signal. The broken mRNA is replaced in the ribosome by the tmRNA and translation of the tmRNA leads to addition of a proteolysis tag to the incomplete protein enabling recognition by a protease. Recently a number of permuted tmRNAs genes have been found encoded in two parts. TmRNAs have been identified in eubacteria and some chloroplasts but are absent from archeal and Eukaryote nuclear genomes.

Name: DCE
Definition: A discontinuous core element of RNA polymerase II transcribed genes	 situated downstream of the TSS. It is composed of three sub elements: SI	 SII and SIII.

Name: BREd_motif
Definition: A core RNA polymerase II promoter element with consensus (G/A)T(T/G/A)(T/A)(G/T)(T/G)(T/G).

Name: bipartite_inversion
Definition: A chromosomal inversion caused by three breaks in the same chromosome; both central segments are inverted in place (i.e.	 they are not transposed).

Name: plus_1_frameshift
Definition: A frameshift caused by inserting one base.

Name: wybutosine
Definition: Wybutosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: double_stranded_RNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 double-stranded RNA molecule.

Name: variant_genome
Definition: A collection of sequences (often chromosomes) of an individual.

Name: pre_edited_region
Definition: The region of a transcript that will be edited.

Name: chromatin_regulatory_region
Definition: A region of a chromosome where regulatory events occur	 including epigenetic modifications. These epigenetic modifications can include nucleosome modifications and post-replicational DNA modifications.

Name: st_turn_right_handed_type_two
Definition: The peptide twists in an clockwise	 right handed manner. The dihedral angles for this turn are: Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi(1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 +80 degrees psi +120 degrees < +180 degrees	 residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees	 -40 < psi < +90 degrees.

Name: centromere_DNA_Element_I
Definition: A centromere DNA Element I (CDEI) is a conserved region	 part of the centromere	 consisting of a consensus region composed of 8-11bp which enables binding by the centromere binding factor 1(Cbf1p).

Name: late_origin_of_replication
Definition: An origin of replication that initiates late in S phase.

Name: HERV_deletion
Definition: A deletion of the HERV mobile element with respect to a reference.

Name: two_prime_O_methyluridine
Definition: 2prime_O_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: signal_peptide_region_of_CDS
Definition: A CDS region corresponding to a signal peptide of a polypeptide.

Name: R_GNA
Definition: An attribute describing a GNA sequence in the (R)-GNA enantiomer.

Name: CDS_supported_by_EST_or_cDNA_data
Definition: A CDS that is supported by similarity to EST or cDNA data.

Name: invalidated_by_genomic_contamination
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that is invalidated due to genomic contamination.

Name: piggyBac_TIR_transposon
Definition: Primarily found in animals	 the terminal inverted repeat (TIR) transposon superfamily piggyBac elements favour insertion adjacent to TTAA.

Name: miR_encoding_shRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A shRNA primary transcript that also encodes pre-miR sequence that is processed to form functionally active miRNA.

Name: OxyS_RNA
Definition: A small untranslated RNA which is induced in response to oxidative stress in Escherichia coli. Acts as a global regulator to activate or repress the expression of as many as 40 genes	 including the fhlA-encoded transcriptional activator and the rpoS-encoded sigma(s) subunit of RNA polymerase. OxyS is bound by the Hfq protein	 that increases the OxyS RNA interaction with its target messages.

Name: signal_peptide
Definition: The signal_peptide is a short region of the peptide located at the N-terminus that directs the protein to be secreted or part of membrane components.

Name: tyrosine
Definition: A polar	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons TAT and TAC.

Name: intronic_regulatory_region
Definition: A regulatory region that is part of an intron.

Name: primer_match
Definition: A nucleotide match to a primer sequence.

Name: gRNA_gene
Definition: A noncoding RNA that guides the insertion or deletion of uridine residues in mitochondrial mRNAs. This may also refer to synthetic RNAs used to guide DNA editing using the CRIPSR/Cas9 system.

Name: polypeptide_nickel_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with nickel ions.

Name: feature_variant
Definition: A sequence variant that falls entirely or partially within a genomic feature.

Name: gene_with_stop_codon_redefined_as_pyrrolysine
Definition: A gene encoding an mRNA that has the stop codon redefined as pyrrolysine.

Name: gene_with_dicistronic_primary_transcript
Definition: A gene that encodes a dicistronic primary transcript.

Name: five_methyldihydrouridine
Definition: 5_methyldihydrouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: stop_codon_redefined_as_pyrrolysine
Definition: A stop codon redefined to be the new amino acid	 pyrrolysine.

Name: one_two_prime_O_dimethyladenosine
Definition: 1	2'-O-dimethyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: unassigned_supercontig
Definition: A supercontig that is not been assigned to any ultracontig during a genome assembly project.

Name: modified_L_proline
Definition: A post translationally modified proline amino acid feature.

Name: pseudogene
Definition: A sequence that closely resembles a known functional gene	 at another locus within a genome	 that is non-functional as a consequence of (usually several) mutations that prevent either its transcription or translation (or both). In general	 pseudogenes result from either reverse transcription of a transcript of their "normal" paralog (SO:0000043) (in which case the pseudogene typically lacks introns and includes a poly(A) tail) or from recombination (SO:0000044) (in which case the pseudogene is typically a tandem duplication of its "normal" paralog).

Name: hAT_TIR_transposon
Definition: The hAT terminal inverted repeat transposon superfamily elements were first found in maize (the Ac/Ds elements). Members of the hAT superfamily have TSDs of 8 bp	 relatively short TIRs of 5b27 bp and overall lengths of less than 4 kb.

Name: chromosomally_aberrant_genome
Definition: When a genome contains an abnormal amount of chromosomes.

Name: antisense_primary_transcript
Definition: The reverse complement of the primary transcript.

Name: promoter_targeting_sequence
Definition: A transcriptional_cis_regulatory_region that restricts the activity of a CRM to a single promoter and which functions only when both itself and an insulator are located between the CRM and the promoter.

Name: H3K27_methylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 27th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is methylated.

Name: interchromosomal_translocation
Definition: A translocation where the regions involved are from different chromosomes.

Name: H2BK15_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 15th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2B histone protein is acetylated.

Name: attI_site
Definition: A region within an integron	 adjacent to an integrase	 at which site specific recombination involving an attC_site takes place.

Name: uridine_five_oxyacetic_acid_methyl_ester
Definition: Uridine_5_oxyacetic_acid_methyl_ester is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: clone_insert_start
Definition: The start of the clone insert.

Name: non_protein_coding
Definition: A gene which can be transcribed	 but will not be translated into a protein.

Name: SL11_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL11 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL11 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: cysteine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding cysteinyl tRNA (SO:0000258).

Name: polypeptide_sequencing_information
Definition: Incompatibility in the sequence due to some experimental problem.

Name: CAGE_tag
Definition: A CAGE tag is a sequence tag hat corresponds to 5' ends of mRNA at cap sites	 produced by cap analysis gene expression and used to identify transcriptional start sites.

Name: B_box
Definition: A variably distant linear promoter region recognized by TFIIIC	 with consensus sequence AGGTTCCAnnCC.

Name: single_strand_restriction_enzyme_cleavage_site
Definition: A restriction enzyme cleavage site whereby only one strand is cut.

Name: snoRNA
Definition: A snoRNA (small nucleolar RNA) is any one of a class of small RNAs that are associated with the eukaryotic nucleus as components of small nucleolar ribonucleoproteins. They participate in the processing or modifications of many RNAs	 mostly ribosomal RNAs (rRNAs) though snoRNAs are also known to target other classes of RNA	 including spliceosomal RNAs	 tRNAs	 and mRNAs via a stretch of sequence that is complementary to a sequence in the targeted RNA.

Name: dicistronic_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is dicistronic.

Name: sequence_motif
Definition: A sequence motif is a nucleotide or amino-acid sequence pattern that may have biological significance.

Name: antisense_lncRNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes an antisense long	 non-coding RNA.

Name: DMv1_motif
Definition: A promoter motif with consensus sequence CARCCCT.

Name: T_to_C_transition
Definition: A transition of a thymine to a cytidine.

Name: gene_with_non_canonical_start_codon
Definition: A gene with a start codon other than AUG.

Name: experimental_result_region
Definition: A region of sequence implicated in an experimental result.

Name: base_call_error_correction
Definition: A region of sequence where the final nucleotide assignment is different from that given by the base caller due to an improvement that replaces a mistake.

Name: extramembrane_polypeptide_region
Definition: Polypeptide region that is localized outside of a lipid bilayer.

Name: transmembrane_helix
Definition: A region that traverses the lipid bilayer and adopts a helical secondary structure.

Name: DSR_motif
Definition: The determinant of selective removal (DSR) motif consists of repeats of U(U/C)AAAC. The motif targets meiotic transcripts for removal during mitosis via the exosome.

Name: engineered_insert
Definition: A clone insert that is engineered.

Name: Z1_region
Definition: A mating type region motif	 one of two segments of homology found at all three mating loci (HML	 MAT	 and HMR).

Name: purine_to_pyrimidine_transversion
Definition: Change of a purine nucleotide	 A or G 	 into a pyrimidine nucleotide C or T.

Name: floxed
Definition: An attribute describing sequence that is flanked by Lox-P sites.

Name: SUMO_interaction_motif
Definition: A polypeptide region that mediates binding to SUMO. The motif contains a hydrophobic core sequence consisting of three or four Ile	 Leu	 or Val residues plus one acidic or polar residue at position 2 or 3.

Name: attenuator
Definition: A sequence segment located within the five prime end of an mRNA that causes premature termination of translation.

Name: genotype
Definition: A genotype is a variant genome	 complete or incomplete.

Name: scRNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a small cytoplasmic RNA (scRNA).

Name: canonical_five_prime_splice_site
Definition: The canonical 5' splice site has the sequence "GT".

Name: extended_cis_splice_site
Definition: Intronic positions associated with cis-splicing. Contains the first and second positions immediately before the exon and the first	 second and fifth positions immediately after.

Name: A_box
Definition: A variably distant linear promoter region recognized by TFIIIC	 with consensus sequence TGGCnnAGTGG.

Name: rRNA_28S
Definition: A component of the large ribosomal subunit.

Name: nucleotide_to_protein_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the nucleotide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues.

Name: fusion_gene
Definition: A gene that is a fusion.

Name: methylation_guide_snoRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a methylation guide small nucleolar RNA.

Name: sterol_regulatory_element
Definition: A 10-bp promoter element bound by sterol regulatory element binding proteins (SREBPs)	 found in promoters of genes involved in sterol metabolism. Many variants of the sequence ATCACCCCAC function as SREs.

Name: antisense_lncRNA
Definition: Non-coding RNA transcribed from the opposite DNA strand compared with other transcripts and overlap in part with sense RNA.

Name: symbiosis_island
Definition: A transmissible element containing genes involved in symbiosis	 analogous to the pathogenicity islands of gram negative bacteria.

Name: histone_4_acetylation_site
Definition: A histone 4 modification where the modification is the acetylation of the residue.

Name: FRE
Definition: A FRE is an enhancer element necessary and sufficient to confer filamentation associated expression in S. cerevisiae.

Name: centromeric_repeat
Definition: A repeat region found within the modular centromere.

Name: cDNA_clone
Definition: Complementary DNA; A piece of DNA copied from an mRNA and spliced into a vector for propagation in a suitable host.

Name: X_element_combinatorial_repeat
Definition: An X element combinatorial repeat is a repeat region located between the X element and the telomere or adjacent Y' element.

Name: TR_V_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogenic variable region which closely resembles a known functional T receptor variable gene but in which the coding region has stop codons	 frameshift mutations or a mutation that effects the initiation codon that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the variable region of  an immunoglobulin chain.

Name: post_translationally_regulated
Definition: An attribute describing a gene that is regulated after it has been translated.

Name: gene_silenced_by_histone_deacetylation
Definition: A gene that is silenced by histone deacetylation.

Name: ribothymidine
Definition: A modified RNA base in which thymine is bound to the ribose ring.

Name: maxicircle_gene
Definition: A mitochondrial gene located in a maxicircle.

Name: linear_plasmid
Definition: A self replicating linear nucleic acid molecule that is distinct from a chromosome in the organism. They are capped by terminal proteins covalently bound to the 5' ends of the DNA.

Name: pyrosequenced_read
Definition: A read produced by pyrosequencing technology.

Name: V_DJ_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene and one DJ-gene.

Name: cis_regulatory_module
Definition: A regulatory region where transcription factor binding sites are clustered to regulate various aspects of transcription activities. (CRMs can be located a few kb to hundreds of kb upstream of the core promoter	 in the coding sequence	 within introns	 or in the untranslated regions (UTR) sequences	 and even on a different chromosome). A single gene can be regulated by multiple CRMs to give precise control of its spatial and temporal expression. CRMs function as nodes in large	 intertwined regulatory network. CRM DNA accessibility is subject to regulation by dbTFs and transcription co-TFs.

Name: autopolyploid
Definition: A polyploid where the multiple chromosome set was derived from the same organism.

Name: transmembrane_polypeptide_region
Definition: Polypeptide region traversing the lipid bilayer.

Name: mRNA_with_minus_1_frameshift
Definition: An mRNA with a minus 1 frameshift.

Name: ribosome_entry_site
Definition: Region in mRNA where ribosome assembles.

Name: RNA_stability_element
Definition: A motif that affects the stability of RNA.

Name: pseudogenic_rRNA
Definition: A non functional descendant of an rRNA.

Name: sense_intronic_ncRNA
Definition: A long non-coding transcript found within an intron of a coding or non-coding gene	 with no overlap of exonic sequence.

Name: DNA_motif
Definition: A motif that is active in the DNA form of the sequence.

Name: clone_insert_end
Definition: The end of the clone insert.

Name: U12_intron
Definition: A type of spliceosomal intron spliced by the U12 spliceosome	 that includes U11	 U12	 U4atac/U6atac and U5 snRNAs.

Name: assortment_derived_duplication
Definition: A multi-chromosome duplication aberration generated by reassortment of other aberration components.

Name: transcript_region
Definition: A region of a transcript.

Name: three_prime_coding_exon_coding_region
Definition: The sequence of the three_prime_coding_exon that codes for protein.

Name: H3K23_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 23rd residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 protein is di-methylated.

Name: pseudogenic_exon
Definition: A non functional descendant of an exon	 part of a pseudogene.

Name: circular_ncRNA
Definition: A non-coding RNA that is generated by backsplicing of exons or introns	 resulting in a covalently closed loop without a 5b cap or 3b polyA tail.

Name: asymmetric_RNA_internal_loop
Definition: An internal RNA loop where one of the strands includes more bases than the corresponding region on the other strand.

Name: maxicircle
Definition: A maxicircle is a replicon	 part of a kinetoplast	 that contains open reading frames and replicates via a rolling circle method.

Name: mature_protein_region_of_CDS
Definition: A CDS region corresponding to a mature protein region of a polypeptide.

Name: engineered_region
Definition: A region that is engineered.

Name: gene_variant
Definition: A sequence variant where the structure of the gene is changed.

Name: trans_spliced_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is trans-spliced.

Name: spliceosomal_intron_region
Definition: A region within an intron.

Name: polypeptide_cobalt_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with cobalt ions.

Name: Watson_strand
Definition: An absolute reference to the strand. When a chromosome has p and q arms	 the Watson strand is the strand whose 5'-end is on the short arm of the chromosome. Of note	 the term 'plus strand' is typically based on a reference sequence where it's preferred for the plus strand to be the Watson strand	 but might not be and 'plus strand' is therefore not an exact synonym.

Name: attR_site
Definition: A region that results from recombination between attP_site and attB_site	 composed of the 5' portion of attP_site and the 3' portion of attB_site.

Name: cryptogene
Definition: A maxicircle gene so extensively edited that it cannot be matched to its edited mRNA sequence.

Name: SAGE_tag
Definition: A short diagnostic sequence tag	 serial analysis of gene expression (SAGE)	 that allows the quantitative and simultaneous analysis of a large number of transcripts.

Name: transcribed_unitary_pseudogene
Definition: A species specific unprocessed pseudogene without a parent gene	 as it has an active orthologue in another species.

Name: viral_sequence
Definition: The region of nucleotide sequence of a virus	 a submicroscopic particle that replicates by infecting a host cell.

Name: consensus_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA sequence produced from an aligment algorithm that uses multiple sequences as input.

Name: sequencing_primer
Definition: A single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction.

Name: match_part
Definition: A part of a match	 for example an hsp from blast is a match_part.

Name: tiling_path_fragment
Definition: A piece of sequence that makes up a tiling_path (SO:0000472).

Name: unitary_pseudogenic_rRNA
Definition: The pseudogene has no parent. It is the original gene	 which is functional in some species but disrupted in some way (indels	 mutation	 recombination) in another species or strain.

Name: anticodon
Definition: A sequence of three nucleotide bases in tRNA which recognizes a codon in mRNA.

Name: oriC
Definition: An origin of bacterial chromosome replication.

Name: queuosine
Definition: Queuosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: SNV_artifact
Definition: An SNV that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: morpholino_oligo
Definition: Morpholino oligos are synthesized from four different Morpholino subunits	 each of which contains one of the four genetic bases (A	 C	 G	 T) linked to a 6-membered morpholine ring. Eighteen to 25 subunits of these four subunit types are joined in a specific order by non-ionic phosphorodiamidate intersubunit linkages to give a Morpholino.

Name: CRE
Definition: MERGED DEFINITION:nTARGET DEFINITION: A promoter element with consensus sequence TGACGTCA; bound by the ATF/CREB family of transcription factors.n--------------------nSOURCE DEFINITION: A promoter element that contains a core sequence TGACGT	 bound by a protein complex that regulates transcription of genes encoding PKA pathway components.

Name: modified_L_histidine
Definition: A post translationally modified histidine amino acid feature.

Name: DsrA_RNA
Definition: DsrA RNA regulates both transcription	 by overcoming transcriptional silencing by the nucleoid-associated H-NS protein	 and translation	 by promoting efficient translation of the stress sigma factor	 RpoS. These two activities of DsrA can be separated by mutation: the first of three stem-loops of the 85 nucleotide RNA is necessary for RpoS translation but not for anti-H-NS action	 while the second stem-loop is essential for antisilencing and less critical for RpoS translation. The third stem-loop	 which behaves as a transcription terminator	 can be substituted by the trp transcription terminator without loss of either DsrA function. The sequence of the first stem-loop of DsrA is complementary with the upstream leader portion of RpoS messenger RNA	 suggesting that pairing of DsrA with the RpoS message might be important for translational regulation.

Name: CDS_independently_known
Definition: A CDS with the evidence status of being independently known.

Name: vault_RNA

The complex consists of a major vault protein (MVP)	 two minor vault proteins (VPARP and TEP1)	 and several small untranslated RNA molecules. It has been suggested that the vault complex is involved in drug resistance.

Name: leucine
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codons CTN (CTT	 CTC	 CTA and CTG)	 TTA and TTG.

Name: pseudouridylation_guide_snoRNA

Name: transcriptionally_repressed

Name: translocation_breakpoint

Name: candidate_gene

Name: n_terminal_region

Name: ambisense_ssRNA_viral_sequence

Name: LTR_component
Definition: The long terminal repeat found at the ends of the sequence to be inserted into the host genome.

Name: SRP_RNA
Definition: The signal recognition particle (SRP) is a universally conserved ribonucleoprotein. It is involved in the co-translational targeting of proteins to membranes. The eukaryotic SRP consists of a 300-nucleotide 7S RNA and six proteins: SRPs 72	 68	 54	 19	 14	 and 9. Archaeal SRP consists of a 7S RNA and homologues of the eukaryotic SRP19 and SRP54 proteins. In most eubacteria	 the SRP consists of a 4.5S RNA and the Ffh protein (a homologue of the eukaryotic SRP54 protein). Eukaryotic and archaeal 7S RNAs have very similar secondary structures	 with eight helical elements. These fold into the Alu and S domains	 separated by a long linker region. Eubacterial SRP is generally a simpler structure	 with the M domain of Ffh bound to a region of the 4.5S RNA that corresponds to helix 8 of the eukaryotic and archaeal SRP S domain. Some Gram-positive bacteria (e.g. Bacillus subtilis)	 however	 have a larger SRP RNA that also has an Alu domain. The Alu domain is thought to mediate the peptide chain elongation retardation function of the SRP. The universally conserved helix which interacts with the SRP54/Ffh M domain mediates signal sequence recognition. In eukaryotes and archaea	 the SRP19-helix 6 complex is thought to be involved in SRP assembly and stabilizes helix 8 for SRP54 binding.

Name: intron_domain
Definition: An intronic region that has an attribute.

Name: partially_characterized_chromosomal_mutation

Name: short_tandem_repeat_variation

Name: monocistronic_mRNA

Name: cryptic_prophage

Name: modified_L_alanine

Name: sequence_secondary_structure

Name: tRNA_gene

Name: transgenic_insertion

Name: single_stranded_DNA_chromosome

Name: schellmann_loop

Name: nuclear_sequence

Name: group_1_intron_homing_endonuclease_target_region

Name: assembly_component

Name: elongated_in_frame_polypeptide_C_terminal

Name: glycine

Name: databank_entry

Name: protein_coding

Name: methionine_tRNA_primary_transcript

Definition: A binding site that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with DNA.

Definition: A DNA sequence in eukaryotic DNA to which RNA polymerase III binds	 to begin transcription.

Definition: A set of units of gene expression directly regulated by a common set of one or more common regulatory gene products.
