Definition: DNA segment that ranges from about -250 to -40 relative to +1 of RNA transcription start site	 where sequence specific DNA-binding transcription factors binds	 such as Sp1	 CTF (CCAAT-binding transcription factor)	 and CBF (CCAAT-box binding factor).

Name: transit_peptide
Definition: The transit_peptide is a short region at the N-terminus of the peptide that directs the protein to an organelle (chloroplast	 mitochondrion	 microbody or cyanelle).

Name: sequence_uncertainty
Definition: Describes the positions in a sequence where the authors are unsure about the sequence assignment.

Name: invalidated_cDNA_clone
Definition: A cDNA clone that is invalid.

Name: alanyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has an alanine anticodon	 and a 3' alanine binding region.

Name: intrachromosomal_mutation
Definition: A chromosomal structure variation within a single chromosome.

Name: core_promoter_element
Definition: An element that always exists within the promoter region of a gene. When multiple transcripts exist for a gene	 the separate transcripts may have separate core_promoter_elements.

Name: U3_five_prime_LTR_region
Definition: The U3 segment of the three-prime long terminal repeat.

Name: topology_attribute
Definition: The attribute of whether a nucleotide polymer is linear or circular.

Name: gene_with_trans_spliced_transcript
Definition: A gene with a transcript that is trans-spliced.

Name: dispersed_repeat
Definition: A repeat that is located at dispersed sites in the genome.

Name: U14_snoRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: The primary transcript of an evolutionarily conserved eukaryotic low molecular weight RNA capable of intermolecular hybridization with both homologous and heterologous 18S rRNA.

Name: three_prime_EST
Definition: An EST read from the 3' end of a transcript. They are more likely to fall within non-coding	 or untranslated regions(UTRs).

Name: linear_double_stranded_DNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 double-stranded	 linear DNA molecule.

Name: T7_RNA_Polymerase_Promoter
Definition: A region (DNA) to which the T7 RNA polymerase binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: Jockey_LINE_retrotransposon
Definition: Jockey retrotransposons are LINE elements (SO:0000194) found only in arthropods. The full-length element is ~b
Children: kb and contains two open reading frames (SO:0000236)	 ORF1 (568 aa) and ORF2 (916 aa)	 the second of which encodes an apurinic endonuclease (APE) and a reverse transcriptase (RT).

Name: paternally_imprinted_gene
Definition: A gene that is paternally imprinted.

Name: sugar_edge_base_pair
Definition: A type of non-canonical base-pairing.

Name: cassette_pseudogene
Definition: A cassette pseudogene is a kind of gene in an inactive form which may recombine at a telomeric locus to form a functional copy.

Name: five_prime_D_recombination_signal_sequence
Definition: Recombination signal of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene	 including the 5' D-nonamer (SO:0000497)	 5' D-spacer (SO:0000498)	 and 5' D-heptamer (SO:0000396) in 5' of the D-region of a D-gene	 or in 5' of the D-region of DJ-gene.

Name: SL1_acceptor_site
Definition: A trans_splicing_acceptor_site which appends the 22nt SL1 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of most mRNAs.

Name: inverted_intrachromosomal_transposition
Definition: An intrachromosomal transposition whereby the segment between the first two breaks listed is removed and inserted at the third break; the insertion is in cytologically inverted orientation with respect to its flanking segments.

Name: solo_LTR
Definition: A recombination product between the 2 LTR of the same element.

Name: N4_acetylcytidine
Definition: N4-acetylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: U4atac_snRNA
Definition: An snRNA required for the splicing of the minor U12-dependent class of eukaryotic nuclear introns. It forms a base paired complex with U6atac_snRNA (SO:0000397).

Name: SL2_acceptor_site
Definition: A trans_splicing_acceptor_site which appends the 22nt SL2 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of mRNAs. SL2 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: aneuploid_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome structural variation whereby either a chromosome exists in addition to the normal chromosome complement or is lacking.

Name: asx_motif
Definition: A motif of five consecutive residues and two H-bonds in which: Residue(i) is Aspartate or Asparagine (Asx)	 side-chain O of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+2) or (i+3)	 main-chain CO of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+3) or (i+4).

Name: non_LTR_retrotransposon
Definition: A retrotransposon without long terminal repeat sequences.

Name: Y_RNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding a  Y-RNA.

Name: transcript
Definition: An RNA synthesized on a DNA or RNA template by an RNA polymerase.

Name: riboswitch
Definition: A riboswitch is a part of an mRNA that can act as a direct sensor of small molecules to control their own expression. A riboswitch is a cis element in the 5' end of an mRNA	 that acts as a direct sensor of metabolites.

Name: UTR_region
Definition: A region of UTR.

Name: specific_recombination_site
Definition: A location where recombination or occurs during mitosis or meiosis.

Name: gene_silenced_by_DNA_methylation
Definition: A gene that is silenced by DNA methylation.

Name: endosomal_localization_signal
Definition: A polypeptide region that targets a polypeptide to the endosome.

Name: bacterial_RNApol_promoter_sigma_ecf_element
Definition: A bacterial promoter with sigma ecf factor binding dependency. This is a type of bacterial promoters that requires a sigma ECF factor to bind to identified -10 and -35 sequence regions in order to mediate binding of the RNA polymerase to the promoter region as part of transcription initiation.

Name: polypeptide_catalytic_motif
Definition: A polypeptide catalytic motif is a short (up to 20 amino acids) polypeptide region that contains one or more active site residues.

Name: modified_amino_acid_feature
Definition: A post translationally modified amino acid feature.

Name: base
Definition: A base is a sequence feature that corresponds to a single unit of a nucleotide polymer.

Name: TR_D_Gene
Definition: A gene that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the diversity region of the variable domain of aT-cell receptor gene.

Name: processed_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene created via retrotranposition of the mRNA of a functional protein-coding parent gene followed by accumulation of deleterious mutations lacking introns and promoters	 often including a polyA tail.

Name: CDS_region
Definition: A region of a CDS.

Name: natural_plasmid
Definition: A plasmid that occurs naturally.

Name: miRNA_stem
Definition: The stem of the hairpin loop formed by folding of the pre-miRNA.

Name: helitron
Definition: A rolling circle transposon. Autonomous helitrons encode a 5'-to-3' DNA helicase and nuclease/ligase similar to those encoded by known rolling-circle replicons.

Name: bacterial_terminator
Definition: A terminator signal for bacterial transcription.

Name: CsrB_RsmB_RNA
Definition: An enterobacterial RNA that binds the CsrA protein. The CsrB RNAs contain a conserved motif CAGGXXG that is found in up to 18 copies and has been suggested to bind CsrA. The Csr regulatory system has a strong negative regulatory effect on glycogen biosynthesis	 glyconeogenesis and glycogen catabolism and a positive regulatory effect on glycolysis. In other bacteria such as Erwinia caratovara the RsmA protein has been shown to regulate the production of virulence determinants	 such extracellular enzymes. RsmA binds to RsmB regulatory RNA which is also a member of this family.

Name: biomaterial_region
Definition: A region which is intended for use in an experiment.

Name: restriction_enzyme_five_prime_single_strand_overhang
Definition: A terminal region of DNA sequence where the end of the region is not blunt ended and the exposed single strand terminates at the 5' end.

Name: leucoplast_gene
Definition: A plastid gene from leucoplast sequence.

Name: recoding_stimulatory_region
Definition: A site in an mRNA sequence that stimulates the recoding of a region in the same mRNA.

Name: SL4_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL4 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL4 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: pyrimidine_to_purine_transversion
Definition: Change of a pyrimidine nucleotide	 C or T	 into a purine nucleotide	 A or G.

Name: RNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 RNA molecule.

Name: four_thiouridine
Definition: 4_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: site_specific_recombination_target_region
Definition: A region specifically recognised by a recombinase where recombination can occur during mitosis or meiosis.

Name: C_box
Definition: An RNA polymerase III type 1 promoter with consensus sequence CAnnCCn.

Name: region
Definition: A sequence_feature with an extent greater than zero. A nucleotide region is composed of bases and a polypeptide region is composed of amino acids.

Name: U5_LTR_region
Definition: The U5 segment of the long terminal repeats.

Name: non_AUG_initiated_uORF
Definition: A uORF beginning with a codon other than AUG.

Name: catalytic_residue
Definition: Amino acid involved in the activity of an enzyme.

Name: SL10_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL10 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL10 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: modified_cytosine
Definition: A modified cytosine DNA base feature.

Name: lincRNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes a long	 intervening non-coding RNA.

Name: serine_threonine_staple_motif
Definition: A motif of four or five consecutive residues and one H-bond in which: residue(i) is Serine (S) or Threonine (T)	 the side-chain OH of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain CO of residue(i3) or (i4)	 Phi angles of residues(i1)	 (i2) and (i3) are negative.

Name: three_prime_UTR
Definition: A region at the 3' end of a mature transcript (following the stop codon) that is not translated into a protein.

Name: tryptophan
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codon TGG.

Name: H3K4_trimethylation
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 4th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 protein is tri-methylated.

Name: TCT_motif
Definition: A cis-regulatory element	 conserved sequence YYC+1TTTYY	 and spans -2 to +6 relative to +1 TSS. It is present in most ribosomal protein genes in Drosophila and mammals but not in the yeast Saccharomyces cerevisiae. Resembles the initiator (TCAKTY in Drosophila) but functionally distinct from initiator.

Name: overlapping_feature_set
Definition: A continuous region of sequence composed of the overlapping of multiple sequence_features	 which ultimately provides evidence for another sequence_feature.

Name: mRNA
Definition: Messenger RNA is the intermediate molecule between DNA and protein. It includes UTR and coding sequences. It does not contain introns.

Name: Bruno_response_element
Definition: A cis-acting element found in the 3' UTR of some mRNA which is bound by the Drosophila Bruno protein and its homologs.

Name: autocatalytically_spliced_intron
Definition: A self spliced intron.

Name: epigenetically_modified_region
Definition: A biological DNA region implicated in epigenomic changes caused by mechanisms other than changes in the underlying DNA sequence. This includes	 nucleosomal histone post-translational modifications	 nucleosome depletion to render DNA accessible and post-replicational base modifications such as cytosine modification.

Name: minus_1_frameshift
Definition: A frameshift caused by deleting one base.

Name: polyA_sequence
Definition: Sequence of about 100 nucleotides of A added to the 3' end of most eukaryotic mRNAs.

Name: H3K9_methylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 9th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is methylated.

Name: methylwyosine
Definition: Methylwyosine is a modified guanosine base feature.

Name: polymorphic_sequence_variant
Definition: A sequence variant that is segregating in one or more natural populations of a species.

Name: nuclease_sensitive_site
Definition: A region of nucleotide sequence targeted by a nuclease enzyme.

Name: external_transcribed_spacer_region
Definition: Non-coding regions of DNA that precede the sequence that codes for the ribosomal RNA.

Name: intron_base_5
Definition: Fifth intronic position after the intron exon boundary	 close to the 5' edge of the intron.

Name: anticodon_loop
Definition: A sequence of seven nucleotide bases in tRNA which contains the anticodon. It has the sequence 5'-pyrimidine-purine-anticodon-modified purine-any base-3.

Name: chromosome_structure_variation
Definition: An alteration of the genome that leads to a change in the structure or number of one or more chromosomes.

Name: DNA_transposon
Definition: A transposon where the mechanism of transposition is via a DNA intermediate.

Name: three_methylcytidine
Definition: 3-methylcytidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: repeat_region
Definition: A region of sequence containing one or more repeat units.

Name: high_identity_region
Definition: An experimental feature with high sequence identity to another sequence.

Name: DNAzyme
Definition: A DNA sequence with catalytic activity.

Name: two_thiouridine
Definition: 2_thiouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: alteration_attribute
Definition: An attribute of alteration of one or more chromosomes.

Name: H_ACA_box_snoRNA
Definition: Members of the box H/ACA family contain an ACA triplet	 exactly 3 nt upstream from the 3' end and an H-box in a hinge region that links two structurally similar functional domains of the molecule. Both boxes are important for snoRNA biosynthesis and function. A few box H/ACA snoRNAs are involved in rRNA processing; most others are known or predicted to participate in selection of uridine nucleosides in rRNA to be converted to pseudouridines. Site selection is mediated by direct base pairing of the snoRNA with rRNA through one or both targeting domains.

Name: phage_sequence
Definition: The nucleotide sequence of a virus that infects bacteria.

Name: ds_DNA_viral_sequence
Definition: A ds_DNA_viral_sequence is a viral_sequence that is the sequence of a virus that exists as double stranded DNA.

Name: clone_end
Definition: A read from an end of the clone sequence.

Name: moR
Definition: A non-coding transcript encoded by sequences adjacent to the ends of the 5' and 3' miR-encoding sequences that abut the loop in precursor miRNA.

Name: five_prime_coding_exon_noncoding_region
Definition: The sequence of the 5' exon preceding the start codon.

Name: biochemical_region_of_peptide
Definition: A region of a peptide that is involved in a biochemical function.

Name: integron
Definition: A region encoding an integrase which acts at a site adjacent to it (attI_site) to insert DNA which must include but is not limited to an attC_site.

Name: sequence_alteration_artifact
Definition: A sequence_alteration where the source of the alteration is due to an artifact in the base-calling or assembly process.

Name: regional_centromere_central_core
Definition: A conserved region within the central region of a modular centromere	 where the kinetochore is formed.

Name: catmat_right_handed_three
Definition: A motif of 3 consecutive residues with dihedral angles as follows: res i: phi -90 bounds -120 to -60	 res i: psi -10 bounds -50 to 30	 res i+1: phi -75 bounds -100 to -50	 res i+1: psi 140 bounds 110 to 170. An extra restriction of the length of the O to O distance would be useful	 that it be less than 5 Angstrom. More precisely these two oxygens are the main chain carbonyl oxygen atoms of residues i-1 and i+1.

Name: response_element
Definition: A regulatory element that acts in response to a stimulus	 usually via transcription factor binding.

Name: five_taurinomethyluridine
Definition: 5_taurinomethyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: IG_D_gene
Definition: A gene that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the diversity region of the variable domain of an immunoglobuin (IG) gene.

Name: replication_start_site
Definition: A nucleotide site from which replication initiates.

Name: LNA
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases attached to a repeating unit made of 'locked' deoxyribose rings connected to a phosphate backbone. The deoxyribose unit's conformation is 'locked' by a 2'-C	4'-C-oxymethylene link.

Name: U14_snoRNA
Definition: U14 small nucleolar RNA (U14 snoRNA) is required for early cleavages of eukaryotic precursor rRNAs. In yeasts	 this molecule possess a stem-loop region (known as the Y-domain) which is essential for function. A similar structure	 but with a different consensus sequence	 is found in plants	 but is absent in vertebrates.

Name: bound_by_protein
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that is bound by a protein.

Name: micronuclear_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the micronuclei of a cell.

Name: PCB
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence GNAACR	 bound by the transcription factor complex PBF (PCB-binding factor) and found in promoters of genes expressed during the M/G1 transition of the cell cycle.

Name: H2AK9_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 9th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2A histone protein is acetylated.

Name: organelle_sequence
Definition: A sequence of DNA that originates from a an organelle.

Name: ISRE
Definition: An ISRE is a transcriptional cis regulatory region	 containing the consensus region: YAGTTTC(A/T)YTTTYCC	 responsible for increased transcription via interferon binding.

Name: shadow_enhancer
Definition: An enhancer that drives the pattern of transcription and binds to the same TF as the primary enhancer	 but is located in the intron of or on the far side of a neighboring gene.

Name: T_cell_receptor_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene derived from a T-cell receptor gene.

Name: nc_conserved_region
Definition: Non-coding region of sequence similarity by descent from a common ancestor.

Name: exon_junction
Definition: The boundary between two exons in a processed transcript.

Name: distal_promoter_element
Definition: A regulatory promoter element that is distal from the TSS.

Name: transposable_element_CDS
Definition: A CDS that is part of a transposable element.

Name: monocistronic_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is monocistronic.

Name: translocation
Definition: A region of nucleotide sequence that has translocated to a new position. The observed adjacency of two previously separated regions.

Name: enhancer
Definition: A cis-acting sequence that increases the utilization of (some) eukaryotic promoters	 and can function in either orientation and in any location (upstream or downstream) relative to the promoter.

Name: mature_transcript
Definition: A transcript which has undergone the necessary modifications	 if any	 for its function. In eukaryotes this includes	 for example	 processing of introns	 cleavage	 base modification	 and modifications to the 5' and/or the 3' ends	 other than addition of bases. In bacteria functional mRNAs are usually not modified.

Name: minus_10_signal
Definition: A conserved region about 10-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units which may be involved in binding RNA polymerase; consensus=TAtAaT. This region is associated with sigma factor 70.

Name: leucyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a leucine anticodon	 and a 3' leucine binding region.

Name: NDM3_motif
Definition: A non directional promoter motif with consensus sequence GAAAGCT.

Name: linear_double_stranded_RNA_chromosome
Definition: Structural unit composed of a self-replicating	 double-stranded	 linear RNA molecule.

Name: schellmann_loop_seven
Definition: Wild type: A motif of seven consecutive residues that contains two H-bonds in which: the main-chain CO of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+6)	 the main-chain CO of residue(i+1) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+5).

Name: mRNA_with_frameshift
Definition: An mRNA with a frameshift.

Name: inversion_derived_duplication_plus_aneuploid
Definition: A chromosome generated by recombination between two inversions; has a duplication at one end and presumed to have a deficiency or duplication at the other end of the inversion.

Name: exon_region
Definition: A region of an exon.

Name: unitary_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogene	 deactivated from original state by mutation	 fixed in a population	where the ortholog in a reference species such as mouse remains functional.

Name: K_turn_RNA_motif
Definition: The kink turn (K-turn) is an RNA structural motif that creates a sharp (~120 degree) bend between two continuous helices.

Name: V_D_DJ_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one D-gene	 one DJ-gene and one C-gene.

Name: inversion_derived_aneuploid_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome may be generated by recombination between two inversions; presumed to have a deficiency or duplication at each end of the inversion.

Name: unedited_region
Definition: The region of an edited transcript that will not be edited.

Name: galactosyl_queuosine
Definition: Galactosyl_queuosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: translated_processed_pseudogene
Definition: A processed pseudogene where there is evidence	 (mass spec data) suggesting that it is also translated.

Name: primer_binding_site
Definition: Non-covalent primer binding site for initiation of replication	 transcription	 or reverse transcription.

Name: U12_snRNA
Definition: The U12 small nuclear (snRNA)	 together with U4atac/U6atac	 U5	 and U11 snRNAs and associated proteins	 forms a spliceosome that cleaves a divergent class of low-abundance pre-mRNA introns.

Name: polypeptide_motif
Definition: A sequence motif is a short (up to 20 amino acids) region of biological interest. Such motifs	 although they are too short to constitute functional domains	 share sequence similarities and are conserved in different proteins. They display a common function (protein-binding	 subcellular location etc.).

Name: ARS
Definition: A sequence that can autonomously replicate	 as a plasmid	 when transformed into a bacterial host.

Name: J_gene_segment
Definition: Germline genomic DNA of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene including J-region with 5' UTR (SO:0000204) and 3' UTR (SO:0000205)	 also designated as J-segment.

Name: selenocysteinyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a selenocysteine anticodon	 and a 3' selenocysteine binding region.

Name: eukaryotic_promoter
Definition: A regulatory_region including the Transcription Start Site (TSS) of a gene and serving as a platform for Pre-Initiation Complex (PIC) assembly	 enabling transcription of a gene under certain conditions.

Name: core_viral_promoter_element
Definition: An element that always exists within the promoter region of a viral gene.

Name: loxP_site
Definition: Cre-Recombination target sequence.

Name: unprocessed_pseudogenic_rRNA
Definition: The pseudogene has arisen from a copy of the parent gene by duplication followed by accumulation of random mutation. The changes	 compared to their functional homolog	 include insertions	 deletions	 premature stop codons	 frameshifts and a higher proportion of non-synonymous versus synonymous substitutions.

Name: two_methylthio_N6_threonyl_carbamoyladenosine
Definition: 2_methylthio_N6_threonyl_carbamoyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: intrachromosomal
Definition: A change in chromosomes that occurs between two separate chromosomes.

Name: V_heptamer
Definition: 7 nucleotide recombination site (e.g. CACAGTG)	 part of V-gene recombination feature of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: cloned_region
Definition: The region of sequence that has been inserted and is being propagated by the clone.

Name: nuclear_rim_localization_signal
Definition: A polypeptide region that targets a polypeptide to the nuclear rim.

Name: parallel_beta_strand
Definition: A peptide region which hydrogen bonded to another region of peptide running in the oposite direction (both running N-terminal to C-terminal). This orientation is slightly less stable because it introduces nonplanarity in the inter-strand hydrogen bonding pattern. Hydrogen bonding occurs between every other C=O from one strand to every other N-H on the adjacent strand. In this case	 if two atoms C-alpha (i)and C-alpha (j) are adjacent in two hydrogen-bonded beta strands	 then they do not hydrogen bond to each other; rather	 one residue forms hydrogen bonds to the residues that flank the other (but not vice versa). For example	 residue i may form hydrogen bonds to residues j - 1 and j + 1; this is known as a wide pair of hydrogen bonds. By contrast	 residue j may hydrogen-bond to different residues altogether	 or to none at all. The dihedral angles (phi	 psi) are about (-120 degrees	 115 degrees) in parallel sheets.

Name: polycistronic
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that contains the code for more than one gene product.

Name: deletion
Definition: The point at which one or more contiguous nucleotides were excised.

Name: protein_match
Definition: A match against a protein sequence.

Name: RH_map
Definition: A radiation hybrid map is a physical map.

Name: gene_with_stop_codon_redefined_as_selenocysteine
Definition: A gene encoding an mRNA that has the stop codon redefined as selenocysteine.

Name: serine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding seryl tRNA (SO:000269).

Name: polycistronic_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding for more than one gene product.

Name: D_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including at least one D-gene and one J-gene.

Name: uORF
Definition: A short open reading frame that is found in the 5' untranslated region of an mRNA and plays a role in translational regulation.

Name: coding_end
Definition: The last base to be translated into protein. It does not include the stop codon.

Name: RRE_RNA
Definition: The Rev response element (RRE) is encoded within the HIV-env gene. Rev is an essential regulatory protein of HIV that binds an internal loop of the RRE leading	 encouraging further Rev-RRE binding. This RNP complex is critical for mRNA export and hence for expression of the HIV structural proteins.

Name: A_box_type_2
Definition: An A box within an RNA polymerase III type 2 promoter.

Name: simple_sequence_length_variation
Definition: SSLP are a kind of sequence alteration where the number of repeated sequences in intergenic regions may differ.

Name: silenced_by_DNA_methylation
Definition: An attribute describing an epigenetic process where a gene is inactivated by DNA methylation	 resulting in repression of transcription.

Name: transgenic_transposable_element
Definition: TE that has been modified in vitro	 including insertion of DNA derived from a source other than the originating TE.

Name: tandem_duplication
Definition: A duplication consisting of 2 identical adjacent regions.

Name: complex_substitution
Definition: When no simple or well defined DNA mutation event describes the observed DNA change	 the keyword "complex" should be used. Usually there are multiple equally plausible explanations for the change.

Name: H2AK5_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 5th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2A histone protein is acetylated.

Name: modified_uridine
Definition: A uridine base that has been modified.

Name: minus_1_translational_frameshift
Definition: The region of mRNA 1 base long that is included as part of two separate codons during the process of translational frameshifting (GO:0006452)	 causing the reading frame to be different.

Name: autosynaptic_chromosome
Definition: An autosynaptic chromosome is the aneuploid product of recombination between a pericentric inversion and a cytologically wild-type chromosome.

Name: peptide_coil
Definition: Irregular	 unstructured regions of a protein's backbone	 as distinct from the regular region (namely alpha helix and beta strand - characterised by specific patterns of main-chain hydrogen bonds).

Name: five_isopentenylaminomethyl_two_prime_O_methyluridine
Definition: 5_isopentenylaminomethyl_2prime_O_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: genomically_imprinted
Definition: Imprinted genes are epigenetically modified genes that are expressed monoallelically according to their parent of origin.

Name: retrotransposed
Definition: An attribute of a feature that occurred as the product of a reverse transcriptase mediated event.

Name: H3K9_monomethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 9th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is mono-methylated.

Name: chromosomal_deletion
Definition: An incomplete chromosome.

Name: non_canonical_three_prime_splice_site
Definition: A 3' splice site that does not have the sequence "AG".

Name: pseudoknot
Definition: A tertiary structure in RNA where nucleotides in a loop form base pairs with a region of RNA downstream of the loop.

Name: mature_protein_region
Definition: The polypeptide sequence that remains when the cleaved peptide regions have been cleaved from the immature peptide.

Name: simple_regulon
Definition: A regulon defined by considering one regulatory gene product.

Name: chromosome_breakpoint
Definition: A chromosomal region that may sustain a double-strand break	 resulting in a recombination event.

Name: spliced_leader_RNA
Definition: Snall nuclear RNAs that are incorporated into the pre-mRNAs to replace the 5' end in some eukaryotes.

Name: sense_overlap_ncRNA_gene
Definition: A gene that encodes a sense overlap long non-coding RNA.

Name: five_prime_restriction_enzyme_junction
Definition: The restriction enzyme cleavage junction on the 5' strand of the nucleotide sequence.

Name: S_GNA_oligo
Definition: An oligo composed of (S)-GNA residues.

Name: constitutive_promoter
Definition: A promoter that allows for continual transcription of gene.

Name: seven_aminomethyl_seven_deazaguanosine
Definition: 7_aminomethyl_7_deazaguanosine is a modified 7-deazoguanosine.

Name: status
Definition: An attribute describing the status of a feature	 based on the available evidence.

Name: terminal_inverted_repeat
Definition: An inverted repeat (SO:0000294) occurring at the termini of a DNA transposon.

Name: group_III_intron
Definition: Group III introns are introns found in the mRNA of the plastids of euglenoid protists. They are spliced by a two step transesterification with bulged adenosine as initiating nucleophile.

Name: transcriptionally_induced
Definition: An inducer molecule is required for transcription to occur.

Name: tmRNA_region
Definition: A region of a tmRNA.

Name: attP_site
Definition: An integration/excision site of a phage chromosome at which a recombinase acts to insert the phage DNA at a cognate integration/excision site on a bacterial chromosome.

Name: polypeptide
Definition: A sequence of amino acids linked by peptide bonds which may lack appreciable tertiary structure and may not be liable to irreversible denaturation.

Name: H4K91_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 91st residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: operator
Definition: A regulatory element of an operon to which activators or repressors bind thereby effecting translation of genes in that operon.

Name: nucleotide_motif
Definition: A region of nucleotide sequence corresponding to a known motif.

Name: no_output
Definition: An experimental region wherean analysis has been run and not produced any annotation.

Name: V_D_DJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one D-gene	 one DJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: complex_operon
Definition: An operon whose transcription is coordinated on several mutually overlapping transcription units transcribed in the same direction and sharing at least one gene.

Name: CCA_tail
Definition: Base sequence at the 3' end of a tRNA. The 3'-hydroxyl group on the terminal adenosine is the attachment point for the amino acid.

Name: RNA_aptamer
Definition: RNA molecules that have been selected from random pools based on their ability to bind other molecules.

Name: threonine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding threonyl tRNA (SO:000270).

Name: H4K12_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 12th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: regional_centromere_outer_repeat_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is transcribed from the outer repeat region of a regional centromere.

Name: D_DJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one D-gene	 one DJ-gene	 and one J-gene.

Name: gap
Definition: A gap in the sequence of known length. The unknown bases are filled in with N's.

Name: splice_junction
Definition: The boundary between an intron and an exon.

Name: telomerase_RNA
Definition: The RNA component of telomerase	 a reverse transcriptase that synthesizes telomeric DNA.

Name: insertion_breakpoint
Definition: The point within a chromosome where a insertion begins or ends.

Name: inverted_repeat
Definition: The sequence is complementarily repeated on the opposite strand. It is a palindrome	 and it may	 or may not be hyphenated. Examples: GCTGATCAGC	 or GCTGA-----TCAGC.

Name: V_DJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one DJ-gene and one J-gene.

Name: circular_mRNA
Definition: An mRNA that is generated by backsplicing of exons or introns	 resulting in a covalently closed loop without a 5b cap or 3b polyA tail.

Name: validated
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that has been proven.

Name: pseudogenic_tRNA
Definition: A non functional descendent of a tRNA.

Name: CTCF_binding_site
Definition: A transcription factor binding site with consensus sequence CCGCGNGGNGGCAG	 bound by CCCTF-binding factor.

Name: five_methylaminomethyl_two_selenouridine
Definition: 5_methylaminomethyl_2_selenouridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: transposable_element_gene
Definition: A gene encoded within a transposable element. For example gag	 int	 env and pol are the transposable element genes of the TY element in yeast.

Name: intrachromosomal_duplication
Definition: A duplication that occurred within a chromosome.

Name: five_prime_LTR
Definition: The long terminal repeat found at the five-prime end of the sequence to be inserted into the host genome.

Name: targeting_vector
Definition: An engineered vector that is able to take part in homologous recombination in a host with the intent of introducing site specific genomic modifications.

Name: enhancer_blocking_element
Definition: A transcriptional cis regulatory region that when located between an enhancer and a gene's promoter prevents the enhancer from modulating the expression of the gene. Sometimes referred to as an insulator but may not include the barrier function of an insulator.

Name: silenced_by_RNA_interference
Definition: An attribute describing an epigenetic process where a gene is inactivated by RNA interference.

Name: D_DJ_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one D-gene	 one DJ-gene and one C-gene.

Name: restriction_enzyme_single_strand_overhang
Definition: A terminal region of DNA sequence where the end of the region is not blunt ended.

Name: H4K4_trimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 4th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H4 protein is tri-methylated.

Name: KEN_box
Definition: A conserved polypeptide motif that can be recognized by FZR/Cdh1-activated anaphase-promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C) and targets a protein for ubiquitination and subsequent degradation by the APC/C. The consensus sequence is KENXXXN.

Name: engineered_foreign_region
Definition: A region that is engineered and foreign.

Name: apicoplast_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of an apicoplast	 a non-photosynthetic plastid.

Name: zinc_finger_binding_site
Definition: A binding site to which a polypeptide will bind with a zinc finger motif	 which is characterized by requiring one or more Zinc 2+ ions for stabilized folding.

Name: two_prime_O_methylinosine
Definition: 2'-O-methylinosine is a modified inosine.

Name: assortment_derived_deficiency_plus_duplication
Definition: A multi-chromosome aberration generated by reassortment of other aberration components; presumed to have a deficiency and a duplication.

Name: modified_L_methionine
Definition: A post translationally modified methionine amino acid feature.

Name: orphan_CDS
Definition: A CDS whose predicted amino acid sequence is unsupported by any experimental evidence or by any match with any other known sequence.

Name: seven_methylguanine
Definition: A modified RNA base in which guanine is methylated at the 7- position.

Name: cryptic
Definition: A feature_attribute describing a feature that is not manifest under normal conditions.

Name: transcribed_unprocessed_pseudogene
Definition: A unprocessed pseudogene supported by locus-specific evidence of transcription.

Name: polypeptide_copper_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with copper ions.

Name: five_prime_RST
Definition: A tag produced from a single sequencing read from a 5'-RACE product; typically a few hundred base pairs long.

Name: gene_with_stop_codon_read_through
Definition: A gene that encodes a transcript with stop codon readthrough.

Name: lincRNA
Definition: Long	 intervening non-coding RNA. A transcript that does not overlap within the start or end genomic coordinates of a coding gene or pseudogene on either strand.

Name: introgressed_chromosome_region
Definition: A region of a chromosome that has been introduced by backcrossing with a separate species.

Name: intrachromosomal_translocation
Definition: A translocation where the regions involved are from the same chromosome.

Name: TRIM
Definition: TRIM elements have terminal direct repeat sequences of 100-250 bp in length that flank an internal domain of 100b300 bp. TRIMs lack coding domains and thus do not encode proteins.

Name: isoleucine
Definition: A non-polar	 hydorophobic amino acid encoded by the codons ATH (ATT	 ATC and ATA).

Name: DNA_loop
Definition: A region of DNA between two loop anchor positions that are held in close physical proximity.

Name: plasmid_gene
Definition: A gene from plasmid sequence.

Name: miRtron
Definition: A de-branched intron which mimics the structure of pre-miRNA and enters the miRNA processing pathway without Drosha mediated cleavage.

Name: STREP_motif
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence CCCCTC	 bound by the PKA-responsive zinc finger transcription factor Rst2.

Name: genomic_DNA
Definition: DNA located in the genome and able to be transmitted to the offspring.

Name: duplication_attribute
Definition: An attribute of a duplication	 which is an insertion which derives from	 or is identical in sequence to	 nucleotides present at a known location in the genome.

Name: enhancerRNA
Definition: A short ncRNA that is transcribed from an enhancer. May have a regulatory function.

Name: pseudogenic_region
Definition: A non-functional descendant of a functional entity.

Name: capped
Definition: An attribute describing when a sequence	 usually an mRNA is capped by the addition of a modified guanine nucleotide at the 5' end.

Name: minicircle_gene
Definition: A gene found within a minicircle.

Name: glutamyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a glutamic acid anticodon	 and a 3' glutamic acid binding region.

Name: MicF_RNA
Definition: A non-translated 93 nt antisense RNA that binds its target ompF mRNA and regulates ompF expression by inhibiting translation and inducing degradation of the message.

Name: H3R2_dimethylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 2nd residue (an arginine)	 from the start of the H3 protein is di-methylated.

Name: plus_2_framshift
Definition: A frameshift caused by inserting two bases.

Name: AP_1_binding_site
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence TGACTCA	 bound by AP-1 and related transcription factors.

Name: cysteine
Definition: A polar amino acid encoded by the codons TGT and TGC.

Name: A_to_C_transversion
Definition: A transversion from adenine to cytidine.

Name: homol_E_box
Definition: A core promoter element that has the consensus sequence ACCCTACCCT (or its inverted form AGGGTAGGGT)	 and is found near the homol D box in some promoters that use a homol D box instead of a canonical TATA sequence.

Name: assembly_error_correction
Definition: A region of sequence where the final nucleotide assignment differs from the original assembly due to an improvement that replaces a mistake.

Name: arginine
Definition: A positively charged	 hydorophilic amino acid encoded by the codons CGN (CGT	 CGC	 CGA and CGG)	 AGA and AGG.

Name: oriT
Definition: A region of a DNA molecule where transfer is initiated during the process of conjugation or mobilization.

Name: invalidated_by_genomic_polyA_primed_cDNA
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that is invalidated due to polyA priming.

Name: polycistronic_transcript
Definition: A transcript that is polycistronic.

Name: primary_transcript
Definition: A transcript that in its initial state requires modification to be functional.

Name: transcript_with_translational_frameshift
Definition: A transcript with a translational frameshift.

Name: AFLP_fragment
Definition: A PCR product obtained by applying the AFLP technique	 based on a restriction enzyme digestion of genomic DNA and an amplification of the resulting fragments.

Name: amplification_origin
Definition: An origin_of_replication that is used for the amplification of a chromosomal nucleic acid sequence.

Name: D_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in germline configuration including more than one D-gene.

Name: direction_attribute
Definition: The attribute of whether the sequence is the same direction as a feature (forward) or the opposite direction as a feature (reverse).

Name: miR_encoding_lncRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A lncRNA primary transcript that also encodes pre-miR sequence that is processed to form functionally active miRNA.

Name: ARIA
Definition: A non-coding RNA transcript	 derived from the transcription of the telomere. These  transcripts consist of C rich repeats.

Name: polypeptide_molybdenum_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with molybdenum ions.

Name: vacuolar_sorting_signal
Definition: A polypeptide region that targets a polypeptide to the vacuole.

Name: exonic_splice_enhancer
Definition: Exonic splicing enhancers (ESEs) facilitate exon definition by assisting in the recruitment of splicing factors to the adjacent intron.

Name: Sap1_recognition_motif
Definition: A DNA motif to which the S. pombe Sap1 protein binds. The consensus sequence is 5'-TARGCAGNTNYAACGMG-3'; it is found at the mating type locus	 where it is important for mating type switching	 and at replication fork barriers in rDNA repeats.

Name: modified_L_cysteine
Definition: A post translationally modified cysteine amino acid feature.

Name: YR_retrotransposon
Definition: Tyrosine Kinase (YR) retrotransposons are a subclass of non-LTR retrotransposons. These YR-encoding elements consist of central gag	 pol and tyrosine recombinase (YR) open reading frames (ORFs) flanked with terminal repeat. The pol ORF includes a reverse transcriptase (RT)	 a RNase H (RH) and	 in case of DIRS	 a domain similar to bacterial and phage DNA N-6-adenine-methyltransferase (MT). Compared to the retroviral pol (LTR retrotransposons	 non-LTR retrotransposons and Penelope elements)	 both aspartic protease and DDE integrase are absent from YR retrotransposons. YR retrotransposons have inverted terminal repeats (ITRs).

Name: apicoplast_gene
Definition: A gene from apicoplast sequence.

Name: RNA_polymerase_III_TATA_box
Definition: A TATA box core promoter of a gene transcribed by RNA polymerase III.

Name: syntenic
Definition: Attribute describing sequence regions occurring in same order on chromosome of different species.

Name: ligand_binding_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with a small molecule such as a drug	 or hormone.

Name: Mat2P
Definition: A gene cassette array containing H+ mating type specific information.

Name: sense_overlap_ncRNA
Definition: A long non-coding transcript that contains a protein coding gene within its intronic sequence on the same strand	 with no overlap of exonic sequence.

Name: replication_regulatory_region
Definition: A regulatory region that is involved in the control of the process of nucleotide replication.

Name: 8_oxoadenine
Definition: A modified DNA adenine base	at the 8 carbon	 often the product of DNA damage.

Name: subtelomere
Definition: A heterochromatic region of the chromosome	  adjacent to the telomere (on the centromeric side) that contains repetitive DNA and sometimes genes and it is transcribed.

Name: Tc1_Mariner_TIR_transposon
Definition: Elements of the Tc1-Mariner terminal inverted repeat transposon superfamily (also called mariner transposons) are named after the Transponon of C. elegans number 1 transposasse. Their activity creates a 2-bp (TA) target-site duplication (TSD). Stowaway is the non-autonomous element in this superfamily usually shorter than 600 bp.

Name: cDNA
Definition: DNA synthesized by reverse transcriptase using RNA as a template.

Name: stop_codon_redefined_as_selenocysteine
Definition: A stop codon redefined to be the new amino acid	 selenocysteine.

Name: V_D_DJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one D-gene	 one DJ-gene and one J-gene.

Name: histone_acetylation_site
Definition: A histone modification where the modification is the acylation of the residue.

Name: RTE_LINE_retrotransposon
Definition: RTE retrotransposons are LINE elements (SO:0000194) that contain a domain with homology to the apurinic-apyrimidic (AP) endonucleases in addition to the previously identified reverse transcriptase domain.

Name: isoleucyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has an isoleucine anticodon	 and a 3' isoleucine binding region.

Name: conserved
Definition: A region that is similar or identical across more than one species.

Name: gene_with_polyadenylated_mRNA
Definition: A gene that encodes a polyadenylated mRNA.

Name: zinc_repressed_element
Definition: A promoter element that has the consensus sequence GNMGATC	 and is found in promoters of genes repressed in the presence of zinc.

Name: DJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA in rearranged configuration including at least one D-J-GENE	 one J-GENE and one C-GENE.

Name: RNApol_I_promoter
Definition: A DNA sequence in eukaryotic DNA to which RNA polymerase I binds	 to begin transcription.

Name: VD_gene_segment
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in partially rearranged genomic DNA including L-part1	 V-intron and V-D-exon	 with the 5' UTR (SO:0000204) and 3' UTR (SO:0000205).

Name: H3K56_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 56th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: five_methoxycarbonylmethyl_two_prime_O_methyluridine
Definition: Five_methoxycarbonylmethyl_2_prime_O_methyluridine is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: N6_N6_dimethyladenosine
Definition: N6_N6_dimethyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: antisense_RNA
Definition: Antisense RNA is RNA that is transcribed from the coding	 rather than the template	 strand of DNA. It is therefore complementary to mRNA.

Name: DPE1_motif
Definition: A promoter motif with consensus sequence CGGACGT.

Name: compound_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome structure variant where a monocentric element is caused by the fusion of two chromosome arms.

Name: chloroplast_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a chloroplast	 a green plastid for photosynthesis.

Name: engineered_fusion_gene
Definition: A fusion gene that is engineered.

Name: IG_J_gene
Definition: A joining gene that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the joining region of the variable domain of an immunoglobulin chain.

Name: sequence_attribute
Definition: An attribute describes a quality of sequence.

Name: mitochondrial_DNA_read
Definition: A sequencer read of a mitochondrial DNA sample.

Name: rRNA_5S
Definition: 5S ribosomal RNA (5S rRNA) is a component of the large ribosomal subunit in both prokaryotes and eukaryotes. In eukaryotes	 it is synthesised by RNA polymerase III (the other eukaryotic rRNAs are cleaved from a 45S precursor synthesised by RNA polymerase I). In Xenopus oocytes	 it has been shown that fingers 4-7 of the nine-zinc finger transcription factor TFIIIA can bind to the central region of 5S RNA. Thus	 in addition to positively regulating 5S rRNA transcription	 TFIIIA also stabilizes 5S rRNA until it is required for transcription.

Name: rho_independent_bacterial_terminator
Definition: A transcription terminator that is not dependent upon Rho. Rather	 the mRNA contains a sequence that allows it to base-pair with itself and make a stem-loop structure.

Name: minus_2_translational_frameshift
Definition: The region of mRNA 2 bases long that is included as part of two separate codons during the process of translational frameshifting (GO:0006452)	 causing the reading frame to be different.

Name: helix_turn_helix
Definition: A motif comprising two helices separated by a turn.

Name: lysidine
Definition: Lysidine is a modified cytidine.

Name: SNV
Definition: SNVs are single nucleotide positions in genomic DNA at which different sequence alternatives exist.

Name: glutaminyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a glutamine anticodon	 and a 3' glutamine binding region.

Name: copy_number_gain
Definition: A sequence alteration whereby the copy number of a given regions is greater than the reference sequence.

Name: U5_snRNA
Definition: U5 RNA is a component of both types of known spliceosome. The precise function of this molecule is unknown	 though it is known that the 5' loop is required for splice site selection and p220 binding	 and that both the 3' stem-loop and the Sm site are important for Sm protein binding and cap methylation.

Name: guide_RNA_region
Definition: A region of guide RNA.

Name: H3K23_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification	 whereby the 23rd residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: Bel_Pao_LTR_retrotransposon
Definition: LTR retrotransposons in the Bel-Pao superfamily are similar to LTRs in the Gypsy and Retrovirus superfamilies. Mainly described in metazoan genomes	 this superfamily contain elements coding for specific proteins in this order: GAG	 AP	 RT	 RH and INT. GAG is a structural protein for virus-like particles. AP is aspartic proteinase. INT is a DDE integrase. RT is a reverse transcriptase. RH is RNAse H.

Name: dicistronic
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence that contains the code for two gene products.

Name: mt_gene
Definition: A gene located in mitochondrial sequence.

Name: mt_rRNA
Definition: Mitochondrial ribosomal RNA.

Name: SL8_acceptor_site
Definition: A SL2_acceptor_site which appends the SL8 RNA leader sequence to the 5' end of an mRNA. SL8 acceptor sites occur in genes in internal segments of polycistronic transcripts.

Name: engineered_foreign_transposable_element
Definition: A transposable_element that is engineered and foreign.

Name: enzymatic
Definition: An attribute describing the sequence of a transcript that has catalytic activity with or without an associated ribonucleoprotein.

Name: floxed_gene
Definition: A transgene that is floxed.

Name: partial_genomic_sequence_assembly
Definition: A partial DNA sequence assembly of a chromosome or full genome	 which contains gaps that are filled with N's.

Name: processed_pseudogenic_tRNA
Definition: The pseudogene has arisen by reverse transcription of a mRNA into cDNA	 followed by reintegration into the genome. Therefore	 it has lost any intron/exon structure	 and it might have a pseudo-polyA-tail.

Name: histone_ubiqitination_site
Definition: A histone modification site where ubiquitin may be added.

Name: biological_region
Definition: A region defined by its disposition to be involved in a biological process.

Name: engineered_foreign_transposable_element_gene
Definition: A transposable_element that is engineered and foreign.

Name: mathematically_defined_repeat
Definition: A mathematically defined repeat (MDR) is a experimental feature that is determined by querying overlapping oligomers of length k against a database of shotgun sequence data and identifying regions in the query sequence that exceed a statistically determined threshold of repetitiveness.

Name: base_pair
Definition: Two bases paired opposite each other by hydrogen bonds creating a secondary structure.

Name: A_minor_RNA_motif
Definition: A region forming a motif	 composed of adenines	 where the minor groove edges are inserted into the minor groove of another helix.

Name: allopolyploid
Definition: A polyploid where the multiple chromosome set was derived from a different organism.

Name: two_methylthio_N6_hydroxynorvalyl_carbamoyladenosine
Definition: 2_methylthio_N6_hydroxynorvalyl_carbamoyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: cleaved_initiator_methionine
Definition: The initiator methionine that has been cleaved from a mature polypeptide sequence.

Name: mitochondrial_sequence
Definition: DNA belonging to the genome of a mitochondria.

Name: tandem_repeat
Definition: Two or more adjacent copies of a region (of length greater than 1).

Name: elongated_out_of_frame_polypeptide_N_terminal
Definition: A sequence variant with in the CDS that causes out of frame elongation of the resulting polypeptide sequence at the N terminus.

Name: tRNA_intron
Definition: An intron found in tRNA that is spliced via endonucleolytic cleavage and ligation rather than transesterification.

Name: Pho7_binding_site
Definition: A promoter element with consensus sequence [5'-TCG(G/C)(A/T)xxTTxAA]	 bound by the transcription factor Pho7.

Name: match
Definition: A region of sequence	 aligned to another sequence with some statistical significance	 using an algorithm such as BLAST or SIM4.

Name: three_prime_terminal_inverted_repeat
Definition: An inverted repeat (SO:0000294) occurring at the 3-prime termini of a DNA transposon.

Name: C_gene_segment
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene including C-region (and introns if present) with 5' UTR (SO:0000204) and 3' UTR (SO:0000205).

Name: mini_gene
Definition: By definition	 minigenes are short open-reading frames (ORF)	 usually encoding approximately 9 to 20 amino acids	 which are expressed in vivo (as distinct from being synthesized as peptide or protein ex vivo and subsequently injected). The in vivo synthesis confers a distinct advantage: the expressed sequences can enter both antigen presentation pathways	 MHC I (inducing CD8+ T- cells	 which are usually cytotoxic T-lymphocytes (CTL)) and MHC II (inducing CD4+ T-cells	 usually 'T-helpers' (Th)); and can encounter B-cells	 inducing antibody responses. Three main vector approaches have been used to deliver minigenes: viral vectors	 bacterial vectors and plasmid DNA.

Name: interior_exon
Definition: An exon that is bounded by 5' and 3' splice sites.

Name: CAAT_signal
Definition: Part of a conserved sequence located about 75-bp upstream of the start point of eukaryotic transcription units which may be involved in RNA polymerase binding; consensus=GG(C|T)CAATCT.

Name: integrated_mobile_genetic_element
Definition: An MGE that is integrated into the host chromosome.

Name: plasmid
Definition: A self replicating	 using the hosts cellular machinery	 often circular nucleic acid molecule that is distinct from a chromosome in the organism.

Name: polypeptide_turn_motif
Definition: A reversal in the direction of the backbone of a protein that is stabilized by hydrogen bond between backbone NH and CO groups	 involving no more than 4 amino acid residues.

Name: tRNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a  transfer RNA (tRNA).

Name: IG_V_pseudogene
Definition: A pseudogenic variable region which closely resembles a known functional imunoglobulin variable gene but in which the coding region has stop codons	 frameshift mutations or a mutation that effects the initiation codon that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the variable region of  an immunoglobulin chain.

Name: beta_turn_right_handed_type_one
Definition: Right handed type I:A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond	 which	 if present	 is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. It is characterized by the dihedral angles: Residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees. Residue(i+2): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees.

Name: miRNA_encoding
Definition: A region that can be transcribed into a microRNA (miRNA).

Name: transcript_attribute
Definition: An attribute describing a transcript.

Name: lncRNA_with_retained_intron
Definition: A lncRNA transcript containing a retained intron.

Name: pseudouridine
Definition: A modified RNA base in which the 5- position of the uracil is bound to the ribose ring instead of the 4- position.

Name: arginine_tRNA_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding arginyl tRNA (SO:0000255).

Name: microarray_oligo
Definition: A DNA sequence used experimentally to detect the presence or absence of a complementary nucleic acid.

Name: functional_gene_region
Definition: A gene_member_region that encodes sequence that directly contributes to the molecular function of its gene or gene product.

Name: supported_by_EST_or_cDNA
Definition: An attribute to describe a feature that has been predicted using sequence similarity to EST or cDNA data.

Name: MITE
Definition: A highly repetitive and short (100-500 base pair) transposable element with terminal inverted repeats (TIR) and target site duplication (TSD). MITEs do not encode proteins.

Name: GNA
Definition: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases attached to a repeating unit made of an acyclic three-carbon propylene glycol connected to a phosphate backbone. It has two enantiomeric forms	 (R)-GNA and (S)-GNA.

Name: LINE1_insertion
Definition: An insertion from the Line1 family of mobile elements.

Name: compound_chromosome_arm
Definition: One arm of a compound chromosome.

Name: miRNA_gene
Definition: A small noncoding RNA of approximately 22 nucleotides in length which may be involved in regulation of gene expression.

Name: modified_guanine
Definition: A modified guanine DNA base feature.

Name: tmRNA_gene
Definition: A bacterial RNA with both tRNA and mRNA like properties.

Name: H2AZK15_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 15th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H2AZ histone protein is acetylated.

Name: 2A_self_cleaving_peptide_region
Definition: A region that codes for a 2A self-cleaving polypeptide region	 which is a region that can result in a break in the peptide sequence at its terminal G-P junction.

Name: H3K36_acetylation_site
Definition: A kind of histone modification site	 whereby the 36th residue (a lysine)	 from the start of the H3 histone protein is acetylated.

Name: st_turn_left_handed_type_one
Definition: The peptide twists in an anticlockwise	 left handed manner. The dihedral angles for this turn are: Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi(1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 -90 degrees psi +120 degrees < +40 degrees	 residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees	 -90 < psi < +40 degrees.

Name: flanked
Definition: An attribute describing a region that is bounded either side by a particular kind of region.

Name: pathogenic_island
Definition: Mobile genetic elements that contribute to rapid changes in virulence potential. They are present on the genomes of pathogenic strains but absent from the genomes of non pathogenic members of the same or related species.

Name: genomically_contaminated_cDNA_clone
Definition: A cDNA clone invalidated by genomic contamination.

Name: RNAi_reagent
Definition: A double stranded RNA duplex	 at least 20bp long	 used experimentally to inhibit gene function by RNA interference.

Name: five_prime_UST
Definition: An UST located in the 5'UTR of a protein-coding transcript.

Name: read
Definition: A sequence obtained from a single sequencing experiment. Typically a read is produced when a base calling program interprets information from a chromatogram trace file produced from a sequencing machine.

Name: early_origin_of_replication
Definition: An origin of replication that initiates early in S phase.

Name: shRNA
Definition: A short hairpin RNA (shRNA) is an RNA transcript that makes a tight hairpin turn that can be used to silence target gene expression via RNA interference.

Name: tetraloop
Definition: A base-paired stem with loop of 4 non-hydrogen bonded nucleotides.

Name: endonuclease_spliced_intron
Definition: An intron that spliced via endonucleolytic cleavage and ligation rather than transesterification.

Name: TR_V_Gene
Definition: A variable gene that rearranges at the DNA level and codes the variable region of the variable domain of aT-cell receptor chain.

Name: delins
Definition: A sequence alteration which included an insertion and a deletion	 affecting 2 or more bases.

Name: episome
Definition: A plasmid that may integrate with a chromosome.

Name: V_spacer
Definition: 12 or 23 nucleotide spacer between the V-heptamer and the V-nonamer of a V-gene recombination feature of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: free
Definition: The quality of a duplication where the new region exists independently of the original.

Name: Okazaki_fragment
Definition: Any of the DNA segments produced by discontinuous synthesis of the lagging strand during DNA replication.

Name: operon
Definition: The DNA region of a group of adjacent genes whose transcription is coordinated onB one or several mutually overlapping transcription units transcribed in the same direction and sharing at least one gene.

Name: structural_alteration
Definition: An alteration of the genome that leads to a change in the structure of one or more chromosomes.

Name: three_prime_noncoding_exon
Definition: Non-coding exon in the 3' UTR.

Name: edited_transcript_feature
Definition: A locatable feature on a transcript that is edited.

Name: LOZ1_response_element
Definition: A conserved sequence (5'-CGNMGATCNTY-3') transcription repressor binding site required for gene repression in the presence of high zinc.

Name: resolution_site
Definition: A region specifically recognized by a recombinase	 which separates a physically contiguous circle of DNA into two physically separate circles.

Name: nc_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript that is never translated into a protein.

Name: monocistronic_primary_transcript
Definition: A primary transcript encoding for one gene product.

Name: retrogene
Definition: A gene that has been produced as the product of a reverse transcriptase mediated event.

Name: S_region
Definition: The switch region of immunoglobulin heavy chains; it is involved in the rearrangement of heavy chain DNA leading to the expression of a different immunoglobulin classes from the same B-cell.

Name: EST_match
Definition: A match against an EST sequence.

Name: modified_glycine
Definition: A post translationally modified glycine amino acid feature.

Name: protein_stability_element
Definition: A polypeptide region that proves structure in a protein that affects the stability of the protein.

Name: MNV_artifact
Definition: An MNV that is the result of base-calling or assembly error.

Name: polypeptide_manganese_ion_contact_site
Definition: A binding site that	 in the polypeptide molecule	 interacts selectively and non-covalently with manganese ions.

Name: contig
Definition: A contiguous sequence derived from sequence assembly. Has no gaps	 but may contain N's from unavailable bases.

Name: ref_miRNA
Definition: A ref_miRNA (RefSeq-miRNA) sequence is assigned at the creation of a new mature miRNA entry in a database. The ref_miRNA sequence designation remains unchanged even if a different isomiR is later shown to be expressed at a higher level. A ref_miRNA can be produced by one or multiple pre-miRNA.

Name: DNA_sequence_secondary_structure
Definition: A folded DNA sequence.

Name: polypeptide_secondary_structure
Definition: A region of peptide with secondary structure has hydrogen bonding along the peptide chain that causes a defined conformation of the chain.

Name: canonical_three_prime_splice_site
Definition: The canonical 3' splice site has the sequence "AG".

Name: N6_cis_hydroxyisopentenyl_adenosine
Definition: N6_cis_hydroxyisopentenyl_adenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: pyrimidine_transition
Definition: A substitution of a pyrimidine	 C or T	 for another pyrimidine.

Name: DMv4_motif
Definition: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters	 located immediately upstream of some TATA box elements with respect to the TSS (+1). Consensus sequence is YGGTCACACTR. Marked spatial preference within core promoter; tend to occur near the TSS	 although not as tightly as INR (SO:0000014).

Name: CpG_island
Definition: Regions of a few hundred to a few thousand bases in vertebrate genomes that are relatively GC and CpG rich; they are typically unmethylated and often found near the 5' ends of genes.

Name: loop
Definition: The loop portion of a stem loop	 which is not folded back upon itself.

Name: J_nonamer
Definition: 9 nucleotide recombination site (e.g. GGTTTTTGT)	 part of a J-gene recombination feature of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: uridine_five_oxyacetic_acid
Definition: Uridine_5_oxyacetic_acid is a modified uridine base feature.

Name: insertion_site
Definition: The junction where an insertion occurred.

Name: N6_acetyladenosine
Definition: N6_acetyladenosine is a modified adenosine.

Name: enzymatic_RNA
Definition: An RNA sequence that has catalytic activity with or without an associated ribonucleoprotein.

Name: deficient_translocation
Definition: A chromosomal deletion whereby a translocation occurs in which one of the four broken ends loses a segment before re-joining.

Name: gene_with_mRNA_with_frameshift
Definition: A gene that encodes an mRNA with a frameshift.

Name: V_VDJ_J_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one VDJ-gene and one J-gene.

Name: fosmid
Definition: A cloning vector that utilizes the E. coli F factor.

Name: splicing_regulatory_region
Definition: A regulatory_region that modulates splicing.

Name: uncharacterized_chromosomal_mutation
Definition: A chromosome structure variant that has not been characterized.

Name: stop_codon_signal
Definition: A recoding stimulatory signal that is a stop codon and has effect on efficiency of recoding.

Name: recombination_feature_of_rearranged_gene
Definition: A location where a gene is rearranged due to recombination during mitosis or meiosis.

Name: five_prime_D_nonamer
Definition: 9 nucleotide recombination site (e.g. GGTTTTTGT)	 part of a five_prime_D-recombination signal sequence (SO:0000556) of an immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene.

Name: recoding_pseudoknot
Definition: The pseudoknots involved in recoding are unique in that	 as they play their role as a structure	 they are immediately unfolded and their now linear sequence serves as a template for decoding.

Name: miRNA
Definition: Small	 ~22-nt	 RNA molecule that is the endogenous transcript of a miRNA gene (or the product of other non coding RNA genes. Micro RNAs are produced from precursor molecules (SO:0000647) that can form local hairpin structures	 which ordinarily are processed (usually via the Dicer pathway) such that a single miRNA molecule accumulates from one arm of a hairpin precursor molecule. Micro RNAs may trigger the cleavage of their target molecules or act as translational repressors.

Name: gene
Definition: A region (or regions) that includes all of the sequence elements necessary to encode a functional transcript. A gene may include regulatory regions	 transcribed regions and/or other functional sequence regions.

Name: group_II_intron
Definition: Group II introns are found in rRNA	 tRNA and mRNA of organelles in fungi	 plants and protists	 and also in mRNA in bacteria. They are large self-splicing ribozymes and have 6 structural domains (usually designated dI to dVI). A subset of group II introns also encode essential splicing proteins in intronic ORFs. The length of these introns can therefore be up to 3kb. Splicing occurs in almost identical fashion to nuclear pre-mRNA splicing with two transesterification steps. The 2' hydroxyl of a bulged adenosine in domain VI attacks the 5' splice site	 followed by nucleophilic attack on the 3' splice site by the 3' OH of the upstream exon. Protein machinery is required for splicing in vivo	 and long range intron to intron and intron-exon interactions are important for splice site positioning. Group II introns are further sub-classified into groups IIA and IIB which differ in splice site consensus	 distance of bulged A from 3' splice site	 some tertiary interactions	 and intronic ORF phylogeny.

Name: prolyl_tRNA
Definition: A tRNA sequence that has a proline anticodon	 and a 3' proline binding region.

Name: transcriptionally_regulated
Definition: An attribute describing a gene that is regulated at transcription.

Name: sORF
Definition: An open reading frame that encodes a peptide of less than 100 amino acids.

Name: CDS_supported_by_sequence_similarity_data
Definition: A CDS that is supported by sequence similarity data.

Name: engineered
Definition: An attribute to describe a region that was modified in vitro.

Name: chromoplast_chromosome
Definition: A chromosome originating in a chromoplast.

Name: splice_site
Definition: Consensus region of primary transcript bordering junction of splicing. A region that overlaps exactly 2 base and adjacent_to splice_junction.

Name: V_DJ_J_C_cluster
Definition: Genomic DNA of immunoglobulin/T-cell receptor gene in rearranged configuration including at least one V-gene	 one DJ-gene	 one J-gene and one C-gene.

Name: asx_turn_right_handed_type_two
Definition: Right handed type II (dihedral angles):- Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi (1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees	 +80 degrees < psi +120 degrees < +180 degrees. Residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees	 -40 degrees < psi < +90 degrees.
